title: caramel pie
directions: Mix sugar, sour cream, butter and salt in a skillet.
Cook, stirring constantly, until brown as you like.
When brown enough, stir in flour.
Let cool some.
Pour in sweet milk.
Put back and heat.
Let cook until it begins to thicken.
Then add egg yolks (well beaten).
Let cook until thick as you like.
Pour into a baked pie crust.
Put egg whites on top.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix instant pudding and 2 cups milk.
Let this mixture set for 15 minutes or until cool.
Add sour cream and Cool Whip to pudding.
Layer pudding on a 9 x 13-inch pan, then bananas and then wafers.
Keep refrigerated until served.

title: cherry coconut bar
directions: Press together 3 cups flour, confectioners sugar and butter and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Combine remaining ingredients and top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool and frost.

title: clam crisps
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Melt 1 tablespoon butter or margarine in skillet.
Add onion and cook 2 to 3 minutes.
Remove from heat. Add flour and whisk to blend.
Stir in Worcestershire, garlic, clams and clam liquid, stirring constantly.
Cook over low heat until thickened.
Boil 1 minute, stirring.
Let mixture cool. Flatten bread with rolling pin.
Spread each slice with clam mixture.
Roll like jelly roll, cut in half.
Place on baking sheet and brush with melted butter.

title: mirliton pie
directions: Cream together oleo and sugar.
Add eggs, Bisquick, milk and vanilla.
Add 2 cups mashed mirliton.
Pour into greased 12-inch pie plate.
Bake 55 minutes at 350° or until brown.
Serve hot or cold.

title: rhinoceros in orange sauce
directions: In a large heavy saucepan, brown the rhinoceros in the butter. Add the garlic, onions, parsley and seasonings and saute until the onions are golden.
Reduce the heat and add the chicken stock. Simmer for 4 days.
Just before serving, add the orange zest and flour to thicken the chicken stock.
Serve over fluffy rice with a tossed green salad and French rolls.

title: whipped cream pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter (or margarine).
Add eggs, one at a time, beat well after each one.
Add flour and cream alternately. Add vanilla.
Pour in greased and floured tube pan.
Place in cold oven and bake at 325° for one hour and fifteen minutes.

title: cream puff cake
directions: Bring butter and water to boil.
Stir in flour.
Cool and add eggs one at a time (beat with wooden spoon).
Spread in a 13 x 9-inch ungreased pan.
Bake 35 minutes at 400°.

title: just for kids: tiny turtle salad
directions: Empty syrup from canned pears into a small bowl.
Add a few drops of food coloring to syrup.
Soak pear halves in syrup until tinted green.

title: lemon jello mold
directions: Mix jello and cream cheese with hot water.
Let set.
Mix Cool Whip and pineapple into jello mix.
Let set.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix.
Pour in 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake 10 minutes at 400°.
Reduce to 350° and bake until done, about 40 minutes or until set.

title: chinese style daal(lentils)
directions: Wash daal.
Put daal and water on stove.
Add salt to taste and chicken broth seasoning.
Add red pepper and tomatoes.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and cover for 20 minutes.

In a fry pan, cook 1 garlic clove, onion, oil, red chillies and bay leaves. Pour cumin over daal; pour over fry pan and back to original pan. Add Worcestershire sauce, soy sauce and sugar when ready to serve.

title: water chestnuts bacon wraps
directions: Cut bacon into thirds.
Wrap chestnuts with bacon and secure with a toothpick.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for about an
hour.
Drain off grease.

title: easy peach salad
directions: Mix sour cream and Cool Whip.
Add dry Jell-O and mix well. Stir in drained pineapple.
Place in large dish and top with mandarin oranges.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Blend together the first 3 ingredients and salt.
Stir in shrimp and celery.
Chill thoroughly.

title: potato salad
directions: Peel and cube potatoes into bite-sized pieces.
Boil until done (soft).
Do not overcook.
Let cool.
Add mayonnaise, eggs, onion and other spices.
Serve.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Place chicken on waxed paper and pound to flatten.
Place one slice of Monterey Jack and 1 tablespoon of chiles on each breast; wrap breasts around filling and secure with a toothpick.

title: tempting tarragon tomatoes
directions: Cut tomatoes in half and arrange in shallow baking dish with sides touching (cut sides up).
Sprinkle with sugar.
Combine cheese, bread crumbs, pepper and tarragon.
Mix well. Spoon evenly over tomatoes.
Bake, uncovered, in a 375° oven for about 1/2 hour or until tomatoes are just soft when pierced with a fork.
Great with meat loaf or fish.

title: mama's italian breaded chicken breasts
directions: Mix cracker crumbs, Parmesan cheese, garlic, salt and oregano in a flat pan suitable for dipping chicken.
In another pan, mix beaten eggs and milk.
Dip chicken breasts into the egg, then dip firmly into the breading mixture, patting chicken so crumbs adhere.

title: ham-cheese balls
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and form in 3 to 4-inch balls. Roll in nuts.
Delicious with crackers.

title: sardine appetizer
directions: Drain and bone sardines.
Place on lettuce leaves.
Mix other ingredients;
pour over sardines and serve.

title: scrimmage spinach salad(makes 8 to 10 servings)
directions: In large clear glass bowl, layer spinach, tomatoes, mushrooms, eggs and cheese.
Chill until serving time.
In medium bowl, combine buttermilk, sour cream, onion, garlic, mustard and pepper.
Chill until serving time.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Fry hamburger and drain.
Add taco mix.
Cook yellow rice and put on top of hamburger in casserole dish.
Take can of Ro-Tel tomatoes and Velveeta cheese and melt together.
Pour over rice and hamburger.
Take Doritos and crumble on top. Bake at 350° until chips are brown and casserole is bubbly inside.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Mix everything together in a 9 x 12-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour, stirring occasionally.

title: pear bread
directions: Combine flour, soda, baking powder, salt, cinnamon and pecans in a large bowl.
In a separate dish, combine oil, eggs, sugar, pears and vanilla.
Add to dry ingredients, stirring just until moistened.
Spoon mixture into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until bread tests done.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes.

title: chicken and dressing
directions: Melt margarine and mix with stuffing mix. Place 1/2 of this in 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Next layer chicken. Mix sour cream and cream of chicken soup. Put this on chicken and add remaining stuffing mix. Put this on top. Pour hot chicken broth over top. Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: tomato biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In large bowl, combine all ingredients. Roll out the dough on a lightly floured surface to 1/4-inch thickness and cut into 2-inch rounds.
Transfer biscuits to a lightly greased baking sheet.
Sprinkle fresh herbs on top and bake 10 minutes, just until edges begin to brown.

title: apple crisp
directions: Arrange apples in a greased dish and sprinkle with 1 tbsp. sugar.
Combine flour, salt, cinnamon and remaining sugar and butter.
Mix until crumbly.
Sprinkle over apples bake at 375 degrees until brown and crisp.

title: cherry crisp(diabetic recipe)
directions: Fruit layer:
Drain cherries, reserving 3/4 cup juice. Combine small amounts of juice, cornstarch and sugar in saucepan; stir in remaining juice.

title: sausage balls
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Knead in a bowl to mix ingredients. Make into balls.
Very lightly grease a baking sheet.
Drain grease that builds up while cooking several times.
When a light golden brown, they are done.
Put 2 layers of paper towels on baking sheet.
Put sausage balls on the paper towel to soak up the grease.

title: country potatoes
directions: Mix all together.
Put in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with 1/4 cup corn flake crumbs on the top.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Bake uncovered.

title: mississippi mud pie
directions: Pour first ingredient in a large bowl.
Add pudding mix and instant coffee.
Beat with wire whisk or mixer for one minute. Let stand 5 minutes.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spoon into chocolate crust.
Freeze until firm (about 6 hours).
Remove from freezer. Let stand 10 minutes to soften.
Top with fudge sauce.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti according to package directions; drain, rinse and set aside to cool.
In large bowl, combine other ingredients. Add spaghetti; mix well.
Refrigerate.

title: impossible pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour.
Add beaten eggs and mix.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into 2 well-greased 9-inch pie pans and bake at 350° for 35 minutes, or until brown.
Forms its own crust.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients together well and pour into greased casserole dish.

title: chicken or turkey salad i
directions: Combine 3 cups of chopped chicken, celery, relish, onions and eggs.
Toss with the mayonnaise.
Refrigerate.
Serve on a lettuce leaf.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix together and top with Catalina salad dressing.

title: ham rolls
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Then spread on ham slices and roll. Chill.
Cut in thin slices about 1/4 inch thick.
Makes 3 to 4 dozen.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°. In a deep skillet, melt butter. Add onion and saute until tender. Mix in flour, salt and pepper. Stir until well blended. Gradually stir in broth and milk. Cook until thick and bubbling. Stir in chicken and vegetables. Heat through. Pour mixture into deep pie pan lined with crust. Top with second crust. Bake until golden brown, 30 to 40 minutes.

title: turkey and wild rice casserole
directions: Cover rice with water in a saucepan; bring to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Let soak 1 hour, then drain.
Melt 3 teaspoons of butter in a skillet.
Add mushrooms and onion; saute over medium heat until lightly browned.
In a large bowl, combine rice, mushroom mixture and all remaining ingredients, except butter. Turn into a buttered 2-quart casserole.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.
Remove the cover; dot with remaining butter.
Bake, uncovered, an additional 20 minutes.

title: best pie crust ever
directions: Knead flour and shortening together.
Add a little water at a time until it is all worked into dough.
Roll out to form pie crust.

title: los angelos sweet corn breadstilwell, kansas
directions: Mix cake and corn bread batters according to package directions.
Blend together and turn into 2 greased 9-inch square baking pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until corn bread springs back when lightly touched.
Serve with honey butter.

title: prune bread
directions: Mix ingredients in order and put in a greased and floured bread pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: holy cow cake
directions: Lightly mist a 13x9 in. pan with cooking spray. Set aside. Place the cake mix, water, oil and eggs in a mixing bowl. Blend with an electric mixer on low speed for 1 minute. Scrape the sides of the bowl, and beat at medium speed for 2 minutes. Pour the batter into the prepared pan. Bake at 350° for 35 to 38 minutes. Immediately poke holes in the top of the cake (I use the handle of a wooden spoon). Place the caramel and the sweetened condensed milk in a bowl and stir to combine. Spoon this mixture over the warm cake so that it can seep down into the holes. Measure out half of the crushed candy bars and sprinkle the pieces over the cake. Place the whipped topping and cream cheese in a bowl and blend with electric mixer on low speed until smooth and combined. Spread mixture over the top of the candy. Sprinkle the remaining candy pieces over the top. Place the pan, uncovered in the refrigerator to chill for about 20 minutes before cutting it into squares and serving. Store this cake, covered in waxed paper, in the refrigerator for up to 1 week.

title: veggie packet
directions: Prepare 10-inch square of heavy foil.
Place potato, onion and beans on foil.
Sprinkle with onion soup mix.
Top with pat of butter.
Seal in foil.
Bake on grill 30 to 35 minutes.

title: overnight egg omelet
directions: Butter one side of bread slices and cut into 1 inch squares. Place in pan.
Sprinkle bread with cheese.
Beat remaining ingredients together.
Pour over bread and cheese.
For variations:
add diced ham, green pepper, onions, bacon. Refrigerate overnight or up to 24 hours.
Bake in 325 degree oven, covered, for 45 minutes.
Uncover the last 5 - 10 minutes.

title: beef stuffed tomatoes
directions: Hold tomatoes at room temperature until fully ripe. Cut a thin slice from stem end of each tomato; scoop out pulp (use in soups, sauces, etc.). Invert shells to drain.
In a medium skillet, heat oil;
add
onion
and green pepper.
Cook until onion is
golden, 2
minutes.
Add ground beef; brown about 5 minutes. Spoon
off any
fat.
Stir in chili powder and salt. Place tomatoes
in
a shallow
baking
pan.
Fill
with
beef mixture;
top
with cheese strips in crisscross fashion. Bake in a preheated 350° oven until hot and cheese is melted, 12 to 15 minutes.
Yields 6 portions.

title: pie crust
directions: Cut Crisco into flour, sugar, baking powder and salt. Add 1/4 cup milk, then add enough water to make soft crust. Makes enough for 2 double pie crusts.

title: corn casserole
directions: Saute onion and pepper in margarine until tender.
Remove from heat.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Pour into a casserole dish.
Bake at 375° for 35 or 40 minutes.

title: basic meatballs
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Stir together all ingredients (except the ground meat) in a large mixing bowl.
Add the ground chuck and mix together thoroughly.
Using a portioning scoop or 2 spoons, shape the meat mixture into balls (about 2-inches in diameter or 1 1/2 ounces each).
Coat a baking sheet or shallow roasting pan with nonstick cooking spray.
Space the meatballs on the pan so they're not touching or crowded together.
Cover bottom of pan with beef broth.
Bake for 25 minutes or until the meatballs are just cooked through.
Reserve pan juices for sauce.

title: saucepan ginger cookies
directions: Mix flour and baking powder together; set aside.
In a 2-quart saucepan, at medium heat, bring margarine, sugar, molasses and spice to a boil, stirring well to dissolve sugar.
Remove from heat.
Cool.
With a wooden spoon, beat in egg.
Cover and chill several hours, even overnight.

title: six layer sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage in heavy skillet; drain.
Place sausage in bottom of a 2-quart casserole.
Cover with layers of potatoes, onions, carrots and rice.
Add tomatoes with juice.
Combine salt, pepper and sugar.
Sprinkle over top.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chicken salad
directions: Boil chicken breast with seasoning (optional), garlic, salt and pepper.
Cool and grind in a food processor to desired consistency.
Add chopped onion, apples, celery and walnuts or pecans.
Add Miracle Whip salad dressing to taste and enjoy. Refrigerate.

title: pork cake
directions: Chop or grind pork; add hot water over pork.
Add the remaining ingredients.

title: bacon noodle casserole
directions: Saute bacon and onion.
Add catsup and heat through.
Cook noodles until tender and drain.
Combine noodles and bacon mixture.
Heat through and serve.
Makes 6 average servings.

title: broccoli lasagna au gratin
directions: Combine broccoli, cottage cheese and eggs in a medium bowl; stir well (set aside).
Spoon 1/3 cup of spaghetti sauce into bottom of a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish; spread evenly.
Arrange 3 cooked lasagna noodles on top of sauce.
Layer one-third reserved broccoli mixture over noodles; top with one-third each of remaining spaghetti sauce, Mozzarella cheese, Parmesan cheese.
Repeat layers twice.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: bill's cookies
directions: Cream the sugar and oleo well.
Add beaten eggs; beat well. Add hot water with dissolved soda.
Add rest of ingredients and drop by spoonfuls.
Bake at 350° until light brown.

title: sauce for ice cream
directions: Mix ingredients together in pit and bring to boil.
Boil for 3 minutes.
Beat for awhile until it begins to thicken.
Cool and serve on ice cream.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Brown pork chops lightly and put in casserole dish.
Pour dry rice over pork chops.
Mix soup with 1 soup can of water and pour over rice.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cover and bake for about 1 hour at 350°.

title: mixed vegetables(european style)
directions: Mix ingredients in bowl and serve.

title: maple candied sweet potatoes
directions: Cut sweet potatoes in half and arrange in buttered baking dish.
Sprinkle with salt.
Brown butter slightly in small skillet.
Add syrup and orange rind.
Simmer until slightly thickened.
Pour sauce over sweet potatoes.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes, basting frequently.
Serves 6.

title: buttermilk cornbread
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients (corn meal, flour, baking powder, sugar and salt). Combine egg, buttermilk and oil, then stir into dry ingredients. Pour into a heated well-greased iron skillet. Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: bubble bread
directions: Thaw the frozen dough and knead well.
Mix sugar and cinnamon. Pinch off pieces of dough the size of a walnut and roll in melted margarine, then in sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Place into Bundt or angel food pan in layers until all dough is used.
Sprinkle nuts over each layer.
Pour melted butter and sugar over top if any is left.
Let rise until dough is doubled in size.
Bake at 325° for about 45 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes and invert pie on plate.
Rolls pull apart easily.

title: microwave oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix sugar, butter, milk and cocoa.
Cook in microwave on High for 4 minutes.
Remove and add oats, peanut butter and vanilla. Mix well.
Drop by teaspoon on wax paper to cool.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: *One can (17 ounces) vacuum-packed sweet potatoes, cut into 1/2-inch slices can be substituted for the fresh sweet potatoes.

title: easy chocolate cake
directions: Put butter, water and cocoa in saucepan and bring to boiling. Mix flour, sugar, soda and salt in bowl.
Add boiling mixture to flour mixture and mix.
Mix in eggs, vanilla and buttermilk.
Pour into greased and floured pans.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook whole chicken.
Remove from broth.
Bone chicken and cut into small pieces.
Cook 1 large package of spaghetti in chicken broth.
Add 2 chicken bouillon cubes and pepper.

title: purple cow
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender.
Blend until frosty.

title: banana cream pie
directions: Mix together milk and sour cream. Add pudding and beat until slightly thickened. Layer sliced bananas in bottom of prepared crust. Add filling. Before serving, top with Cool Whip.

title: chocolate pecan pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Microwave chocolate and margarine or butter in a large microwavable bowl on High for 2 minutes or until margarine or butter is completely melted.
Stir in corn syrup, sugar, eggs and vanilla until well blended.
Stir in pecans, reserving 8 halves for garnish, if desired.
Pour filling into pie shell.
Bake for 55 minutes or until knife inserted 1-inch from center comes out clean.
Cool on wire rack.
Garnish with whipped topping and reserved pecan halves, if desired.

title: angel food cake topping
directions: Mix Dream Whip.
Cream sugars and cream cheese until bubbly. Blend cream cheese into Dream Whip.
Make angel food cake and slice in half horizontally.
Spread topping on top and continue icing.
May spread a fruit topping on top of the cream cheese topping.

title: crock-pot hash
directions: Brown beef in skillet and drain off fat.
Put all ingredients into crock-pot.
Add water, if needed.
Stir thoroughly.
Cover and cook on low for 8 hours.
Serves 12.

title: fresh vegetable party tray
directions: Trim the bottom of cabbage so it will stand level.
Cut a 3-inch deep square in cabbage, leaving a 1-inch thick shell.
Lift square out to form a
well.
Place cabbage on a large serving plate, carefully folding outer leaves flat on plate.
Arrange vegetables around cabbage.
Just before serving, fill cabbage with dressing.
Serve as an appetizer.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: date pudding
directions: Mix 1 cup brown sugar, boiling water and butter until dissolved.
Mix together well 1 cup brown sugar, flour, baking powder, milk and chopped dates.
Pour this batter into a 9 x 9-inch buttered pan.
Pour liquid mixture over the batter.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Serve warm or cool with whipped cream.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Place lettuce in bowl; add cauliflower.
Spread mayonnaise evenly over the cauliflower.
Add sugar (sprinkle), onion and cheese (also sprinkled on top).
Refrigerate overnight (6 to 8 hours).
Toss.
Add Bac*Os and serve.

title: summer punch
directions: Combine ingredients except ginger ale. Pour over ice blocks in a bowl. Add ginger ale just before serving.

title: coconut macaroons
directions: Combine coconut, sugar, flour and salt.
Stir in whites and extract.
Mix well.
Drop from teaspoon onto lightly greased sheets.
Place cherry half on each.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes or until edges are golden.
Remove from sheet immediately. Makes about 1 1/2 dozen.

title: spicy peach halves
directions: Drain peaches.	Combine peach syrup, brown sugar, vinegar, orange peel, cloves and allspice.
Boil gently; add peach halves and simmer for 5 minutes.
Chill in syrup.	Drain; serve with parsley (optional) or on a lettuce leaf or meats.

title: lazy day soup
directions: Combine all ingredients into a large soup pot.
Salt and pepper to taste.
More water or juice may be added as desired. Cook all vegetables until tender.
Serve with crackers or sandwiches.

title: banana pudding
directions: Cook sugar, flour, milk and egg yolks slowly, stirring constantly. When thickened to pudding add vanilla.
Layer vanilla wafers, sliced bananas and pudding.
Beat egg whites for topping (do not beat in plastic bowl).
Add a little sugar and cream of tartar to whites and beat until it forms peaks.
Top pudding and brown in 350° oven until lightly brown.

title: no peek chicken
directions: Mix mushroom and chicken soup, milk and rice.
Pour small amount into greased 9 x 13-inch casserole dish until bottom is covered.
Place chicken pieces on mixture.
Pour remaining mixture over chicken.
Sprinkle onion soup over top.
Cover tight with foil.
Bake in 325° oven for 2 1/2 hours.
No peeking.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Bring apples with sugar and salt to a boil. Mix flour, baking powder, salt and sugar; cut in shortening, then add milk. May not need 1/2 cup milk; don't want it too wet.
Drop dumplings from the spoon (dip spoon in hot mixture each time before spooning out). Place burner on low and cover. Do not lift lid. Cook 15 minutes.

title: chicken dinner-in-a-dish
directions: Wash chicken; pat dry.
Combine crumbs, garlic salt and paprika on waxed paper.
Dip chicken in milk; roll in crumbs to coat evenly. Arrange in one section of divided cover.
Place potatoes at the end of other section.
Add peas to center of section.
Bake in oven at 350°, uncovered, for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: gary's potato candy
directions: Peel and boil potato.
When soft, remove and place in mixing bowl.
Mash potato.
After mashed, add powdered sugar to make dough.
Once you have a stiff dough, sprinkle powdered sugar onto flat surface and roll out dough to about 1/4-inch thick.
Cover top with peanut butter.
Roll up like a jelly roll.
When drier, slice roll.

title: dumplings
directions: Mix together and cook in beef or chicken broth.
Cook, uncovered, for 5 minutes.
Then cook, covered, for 5 minutes.

title: sausage broccoli casserole
directions: Combine sausage and onion in oil and cook 5 minutes.
Stir in potatoes, water, pepper and carrots; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally. Stir in broccoli and cheese.
Cover; cook 5 to 10 minutes more.

title: chicken tortilla casserole
directions: Layer in buttered large oblong dish (2 layers) the torn up tortillas, chicken, cheese and mixture of all other ingredients. Sprinkle with cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: coconut cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on box.
When cake is cooled, slice layers into 2 pieces each layer,
then mix sugar, sour cream and frozen coconut.
Pour between each cut layer.

title: escalloped apples
directions: Pare, core and thinly slice apples.
Arrange in 3 layers in buttered casserole.
Sprinkle each layer with sugar and dot with oleo.
Cover and cook in 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes or until apples are tender.
Serve warm with ice cream.

title: hush puppies
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add milk, egg and onion.
Drop by teaspoonfuls into deep hot fat.

title: fried green apples
directions: Do not peel apples.
Wash apples and slice into a pan and pour sugar and butter on top.
Cook until done.
They will be thick when done.

title: blueberry dessert
directions: Beat until smooth and liquid.
Pour over crust and bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven and cool.

title: good morning surprise
directions: Place cubed bread (about 11 slices) and ham in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan. Pour egg mixture over bread and ham. Refrigerate overnight. For breakfast, bake in a 325° oven for 1 hour.

title: swedish brown bread
directions: Mix yeast in small amount of warm water; set aside.
Mix water, molasses, sugar, oil and salt together.
Stir in flour. Add yeast mixture.
Stir in well.
Add egg white and fold in well. Let rise until double in size.
Knead.
Shape into loaves.
Place in well-greased loaf pans.
Grease top of loaf.
Let rise until double in size.
Bake at 350° until done and brown.
Great warm with butter.

title: cherry-pineapple dump cake
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Dump pineapple and juice, spreading evenly.
Pour cherry pie filling over the pineapple, spreading evenly.
Add dry cake mix and spread evenly over the fruit.
Add nuts, then slice butter and lay all over the top.
Do not mix!
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: "idiot proof" pralines
directions: Mix sugars and milk together in large heavy boiler or Dutch oven.
Cook together until mixture boils, stirring constantly. Add butter, vanilla and pecans and cook to 240° or the soft ball stage.
Remove from heat and beat mixture with a spoon until thickened.
Spoon onto wax paper.
Let cool, then flip.

title: tin plate special
directions: Wash beans; cover with cold water and let stand overnight. Bring beans to a boil and cook 1 hour.
Drain and discard water. Brown roast in fat in large Dutch oven or roast.
Add peppers and onions and cook until tender.
Add beans and remaining ingredients.
Cover and bake in a 350° oven for 2 1/2 to 3 hours or until beans are tender and meat is done.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: spiced coffee mix
directions: Place all ingredients in blender container. Cover and blend on high speed 15 seconds. Stir, cover and blend on high speed 15 seconds longer. Store in tightly covered container. Makes about 1/2 cup mix.

title: yam apple pie
directions: Grate apples and yams into a bowl.
(Use coarse grater.) Mix together with lemon juice the egg and cream. Beat well.
Add sugar and lemon peel. Add to apple/yam mixture.
Turn into pie shell. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix cocoa, sugar, flour, salt, butter and egg yolks together. Add small amount of water, just enough to moisten.
Heat the milk, but do not boil.
Cook all together until thickened; pour into baked pie shell.

title: hamburger-cheese dip
directions: Brown ground beef and melt Velveeta cheese together.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: spring cake
directions: Mix cake mix, oil and oranges together and bake as directed on the box.

title: cracker snack
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together.
Store in a closed container.

title: peach praline pie
directions: Combine peaches, sugar, tapioca and lemon juice in a large bowl.
Let stand 15 minutes.

title: honey fruit dressing
directions: In saucepan, heat together grapefruit juice, pineapple juice and orange peel.
Beat eggs until thick and lemon colored.
Very slowly add hot juices while beating eggs constantly.
Return mixture to saucepan; cook over low heat, stirring until thickened. Cool slightly.
Cover and chill.
Just before serving, fold in whipped cream.
Makes about 1 1/4 cups.

title: deviled salmon casserole(serves 4 to 6)
directions: Hard-cook the eggs.
Drain the salmon into a liquid measure. Break salmon into pieces.
Melt 2 tablespoons margarine in saucepan; add flour and mix well.
Add the liquid and stir well. Cook until thick and smooth, stirring constantly.
Add Worcestershire sauce, salt, chopped eggs and onions.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: In a bowl mix ground beef, eggs, bread crumbs, cheese, oregano, onion and garlic powder with 2 tablespoons mustard.
Shape into 1 1/2-inch meatballs.
Arrange balls in a shallow baking pan.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: milkless, eggless, butterless cake
directions: Except for flour and baking soda, boil all ingredients together for 5 minutes.
Pour into large mixing bowl.
Mix soda with a little hot water and add.
Then add flour a cup at a time; mix thoroughly.
Bake in a greased tube pan for approximately 1 hour in a 350° to 375° oven.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Mix all together and cook until bubbling.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Make and roll out paper thin a dough of eggs and flour enough to make a dough.
Salt and pepper.
Let dry for about an hour. Have chicken broth ready.
Dice potato and onion if desired.
Add broth to boiling point.
Drop pot pie, cut in squares into boiling broth.
Cook, covered, about 20 minutes or until done.

title: blender seafood souffle(servings:  4)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter bottom and sides of 1-quart souffle dish and dust with Parmesan cheese.
Set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients in blender container.
Cover and blend on medium speed until smooth (about 30 seconds).
Blend at high speed another 10 to 15
seconds.
Carefully pour into prepared dish. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.
Serve immediately.

title: pistachio pudding
directions: Combine pudding mix with pineapple and juice with a wire whisk or mixer until all ingredients are well blended.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Refrigerate for 5 minutes (dessert will be soft set).

title: southern hopping john
directions: Fry bacon until brown.
Add onion and green pepper and cook until tender.
Combine with peas and water.
Add salt, garlic and pepper.
Bring to boil and simmer, covered, for 30 minutes.
Stir in uncooked rice and simmer 30 minutes longer or until rice is tender and fluffy.
Serves 8.

title: frozen broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until barely tender; drain and chop in fairly large pieces.
Combine with onion slices.
Mix other ingredients together and pour over broccoli and onion.
Top with cracker crumbs and bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix cornstarch
and
sugar.
Cover
with
lemon
juice. (Boil the rind in
the hot water.) Add beaten egg yolks.
Then add the boiling water
with
lemon
rind.
Remove
and cook in double boiler.
Put in baked pie crust.
Beat egg whites until stiff. Add 6 tablespoons sugar to the 3 egg whites and spread over pie and brown.

title: edible finger paint
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch together.
Add the water.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until thick.
Divide into 4 portions and add food coloring to each.
If children are old enough to not eat, add a pinch of detergent for easier clean-ups. Will not harm if gotten in mouth.

title: sinful choco cake
directions: Mix everything together.
(Mixture will look muddy. Don't worry.)
Place in Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes. Dust with powdered sugar.

title: party chicken bake
directions: Remove 1 1/2 teaspoons of salad dressing mix and set aside. Combine remaining dressing mix and butter in large skillet.
Add chicken and brown slowly on both sides until golden. Place chicken in a 12 x 7-inch baking dish.

title: vegetable munch
directions: Place prepared vegetables in a large bowl.
Combine seasonings, oil, vinegar and sugar and pour over vegetables. Cover and marinate in refrigerator until cold.

title: hush puppies
directions: Sift together first five ingredients.
Mix well.
Add egg and milk.
Beat 5 minutes.
Add onion and corn.
Stir lightly, then form into 1-inch balls.
Deep-fry in hot oil until golden brown.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Pop corn and place in a brown paper grocery sack, measuring 3 to 4 quarts popcorn. Mix the coating ingredients in microwave. Melt the oleo first, then stir in other ingredients, except soda. Microwave 1 1/2 minutes on High or until boiling. Add 1/2 teaspoon soda and stir. Pour the hot liquid over popcorn; close the bag and shake it to coat popcorn. Microwave 1 1/2 minutes on High. Shake it again. Turn the bag over to the other side and microwave again on High for 1 1/2 minutes. Shake occasionally as popcorn cools.

title: lemon tea cookies
directions: Stir together the milk and 2 teaspoons lemon juice; set aside. Stir together flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
In a large mixer bowl, beat butter until softened.
Add 3/4 cup sugar; beat until fluffy.
Add egg and lemon peel; beat well.
Add flour mixture alternately, beating until well mixed.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in a 350° oven for 12 to 14 minutes, or until well done.

title: sausage roll
directions: After cooking sausage, stir in the softened cream cheese. Flatten out one can of rolls. Pinch seams together and make into a rectangle. Put 1/2 of sausage cheese mixture on dough and roll up (like a cinnamon roll). Repeat with second can of rolls. Beat 1 egg white with fork; brush over top of the two rolls. Sprinkle poppy seed on top. Bake at 350° about 20 minutes. Cool before slicing. If I freeze it, I wrap the rolls and freeze before baking. Thaw and bake.

title: chicken kosh posh
directions: Brown onion in shortening.
Add seasonings and chicken; brown for 10 minutes.
Add water; let simmer slowly until tender. Remove chicken.
Add sour cream to drippings.
Arrange chicken in pan; heat thoroughly.
Serve.

title: microwave crunchy cherry cobbler
directions: Spray 8-inch baking dish with Pam.
Place pie filling in dish. In small bowl, combine cake mix, butter, nuts and cinnamon. Sprinkle over fruit.
Microwave 5 to 6 minutes.
Any fruit pie filling may be substituted.

title: sour cream raisin pie
directions: Beat egg yolks and add sour cream, flour and sugar.
Cook over double boiler until thick.
Add vanilla and raisins.
Pour into cooked pie shell.
Make meringue from the 3 egg whites and spread over pie, sealing edges.
Cook at 425 degrees until meringue browns.

title: sweet and sour baked beans
directions: Saute onions and garlic drippings until soft, not brown.
Mix all ingredients and pour into baking dish.
Bake 45 to 60 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: turkey pie
directions: Parboil carrots, onion, cloves, celery and garlic in soup or stock.
Blend flour and butter.
Add vegetables and stock.
Cook until thick.
Add milk, diced turkey and lemon juice. Season to taste.
Place in deep pie pan or casserole.
Place rich pastry on top.
(Made from your favorite rich pastry recipe.) Brush with milk. Bake in a hot 400° oven for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat and continue to bake 10 minutes longer until brown.
Serves 8.
Serve with a green salad with pumpkin chiffon pie and coffee.

title: pecan krispies
directions: Cream shortening, butter, and sugar. Add eggs.
Sift dry ingredients and add to cream mixture.
Add nut.
Drop by teaspoonfuls about 2 inches apart onto a greased cookie sheet and bake at 352 degrees for 12 - 15 minutes.

title: pumpkin pudding
directions: In a saucepan, combine milk, pudding mix, margarine, salt, cinnamon and brown sugar.
Over medium heat, bring mixture to a boil, stirring constantly.
Allow to cool for a few minutes, then add pumpkin.
Mix well and spoon into six dessert dishes.
Top with whipped cream.

title: aunt betty's meatloaf
directions: Mix all ingredients, adding 1/2 cup of sweet and sour sauce. Cover the meatloaf with remaining sauce.
Bake at 300 to 375° depending on whether you use loaf or flat pan.
This is good sliced cold for sandwiches.

title: barbecue chicken wings
directions: Cut wings in 2 pieces.
Remove wing tip and save for other uses.
Make marinade of next 5 ingredients and marinate for 2 hours.
Bake chicken wings at 375° for 1 hour and 15 minutes. Watch for the last 15 minutes as they can burn easily.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all together and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix all ingredients and shape into balls.
Cover with melted chocolate bits.

title: grammie hedies hot milk cake
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar.
Sift together flour, salt and baking powder.
(Sift 2 or 3 times.)
Melt butter in milk.
Add last and stir quickly.
Bake in 375° oven.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream together.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Score crisscross with fork.
Bake in 350° oven until light brown.

title: pork and potatoes
directions: Cut pork into bite size pieces and brown in butter with crushed garlic. Add more butter and saute onions.

title: beef stir-fry
directions: Add carrots to oil, heated.
Stir-fry for 2 minutes.
Add thinly sliced zucchini and ground beef.
Stir-fry for 3 minutes. Combine beef broth, cornstarch, Worcestershire sauce and ginger. Add to hot mixture and heat to boiling, stirring.
One-half teaspoon salt may be added, if desired.
May be served over rice. Serves 4 or 5.

title: no-flour peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease cookie sheet.
Combine all ingredients in medium bowl and mix well. Form into 1-inch balls.
Arrange on sheet. Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned. Cool. Store in airtight container.
Yields about 30 cookies.

title: special blueberry muffins
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together; set aside.
In large bowl, cream together butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Add flour mixture alternately with milk, beating by hand just enough to dampen.
Add blueberries. Grease and flour muffin pans.
Grease top of pan also.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 35 minutes.
Makes 12 (3-inch) muffins.

title: tuna jackstraw casserole(delicious and quick!)
directions: Reserve 1 cup shoestring potatoes for top.
Combine remaining potatoes with other ingredients.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole. Arrange reserved potatoes on top.
Bake uncovered in 375° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: pasta salad
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in large bowl.
Pour dressing over mixture.
Refrigerate at least 3 hours before serving.

title: pineapple freeze
directions: Freeze and serve with cookies.

title: chile rellenos casserole
directions: 1. Line bottom of lightly greased 11 3/4 x 7 1/2-inch baking dish or casserole with 1/2 chiles. 2. Sprinkle 1/2 the grated cheese over chilies.
Top with remaining chilies.
Sprinkle the remaining cheese. 3. Combine eggs with milk & seasoning.
Pour over chilies, cheese in casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30-35 minutes or till lightly brown. 4. Cool 5 minutes before cutting into squares. Serves 6

title: june's chicken casserole
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Brown chicken just enough to get rid of pinkness.
Add onion and bell pepper.
Cover and cook about 15 minutes (may need to add 1/4 cup water).
Add chicken soup and 1/2 can of water.
Cover and cook about 10 minutes.
Serve with rice.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients.
Put in a 9-inch pie crust.
Top with 1 to 2 cups grated sharp cheese.
Mix together egg, milk, mustard and Worcestershire sauce.
Pour egg mixture over ground beef mixture.
Bake at 425° for 25 minutes or until brown.

title: peanut butter tandy cake
directions: Beat eggs until lemon colored.
Add vanilla, salt, flour, sugar, milk, baking powder and butter.
Mix all together.
Grease cookie sheet with butter; pour batter in and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
While cake is still warm, spread top with peanut butter. Refrigerate for 1 hour.
Melt Hershey bar; put on top of peanut butter.
Refrigerate until hard.

title: lemon lush
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients well and press into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° until lightly brown; cool.
Mix well the cream cheese, 1 cup Cool Whip and confectioners sugar; spread over cool crust.
Mix pudding and milk.
Beat lightly and spread over cream cheese layer.
Spread remainder of Cool Whip over pudding. Sprinkle with small can of Angel Flake coconut.

title: date balls
directions: Melt on low heat butter, brown sugar and chopped dates.
Remove from heat and add Rice Krispies, 1 cup chopped pecans and coconut. Mix thoroughly.
Cool.
Roll a rounded teaspoonful of mixture into a ball and roll in powdered sugar.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in bowl, mixing well.
Place in buttered 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Top with onion rings.
Bake for 15 minutes longer.
Yields 12 servings.

title: thaxton goulash
directions: Boil pork and beef roasts until tender; cool, then slice. Layer roasts, potatoes and onions.
Cover with broth and tomato juice.
Season to taste with salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce. Bake at 400° until potatoes are done.
Serve with homemade biscuits.

title: spinach-broccoli casserole
directions: Cook spinach and broccoli according to package directions. Drain. Combine sour cream and soup mix. Stir into spinach and broccoli. Place in casserole and cover. Bake at 300° for 40 minutes. Top with cheese and bake.
Serves 6.

title: bagel chips
directions: Slice each bagel horizontally in 6 pieces.
In small pan, saute garlic in 1 tablespoon butter or margarine until lightly browned.
Add remaining ingredients and stir until margarine is melted.

title: rice pilaff
directions: Heat oil or margarine in saucepan.
Break noodles into 1-inch pieces; put into saucepan.
Stir over medium-high heat until very brown.
Remove from heat and allow to cool for 1 minute.
Add beef broth; fill can with water and add to broth.
Bring to a boil. Fill can with rice; pour into boiling broth.
Cover and lower heat.
Simmer gently for 15 to 20 minutes.
Stir well and serve.

title: buckeyes (candy)
directions: Cream powdered sugar, margarine and peanut butter together. Form into 1/2 to 1-inch balls.
Melt chocolate chips and paraffin together in double boiler. Dip balls in melted chocolate mixture and place on waxed paper lined cookie sheet.
Set in refrigerator to set until firm.
Store in covered container.
May be frozen.

title: judy's heavenly hash cake
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, and oleo. Sift and add flour and cocoa. Blend well; add vanilla and nuts; blend. Pour into greased and floured 15 x 24 x 2 inch pan. Bake 35 minutes at 350°. Add topping while cake is still hot.

title: easy nachos
directions: Place 3 dozen chips on ungreased baking sheet.
Spread 2 teaspoons of refried beans on each chip.
Sprinkle with green onions and cheese.
Top each with a slice of pepper.
Bake at 350° for 5 minutes.

title: chinese cole slaw
directions: Mix oil, vinegar, and sugar in a saucepan.
Bring to boil. Remove from heat, and add flavor packet from noodles.
Toast almonds and sesame seeds in a small skillet in 1 Tbsp. margarine. Cool and add to slaw.
Break up noodles, and add to slaw along with dressing just before serving.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Spread chicken in a 9 x 13 baking pan. Mix soup, sour cream, sherry, salt and pepper in a bowl. Combine cracker crumbs and poppy seeds in bowl. Mix well. Layer soup mixture and crumb mixture over chicken. Drizzle with butter. Bake for 30 minutes. Serve with noodles or rice.

title: sara's apple chip cake
directions: Combine oil, sugar and eggs in large bowl.
Sift flour, salt and soda together.
Add to mixture.
Add apples, nuts and vanilla. Bake in jelly roll pan or 2 (9-inch) layer pans at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Heat together and store in refrigerator.

title: plum cake
directions: Mix all together for 5 minutes. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: curried pineapple and piggies
directions: Put sausage and pineapple chunks on toothpick.
Place on baking pan, sprinkle curry powder on each one and bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate oatmeal no-bake cookies
directions: In a large saucepan, mix sugar, cocoa, margarine and milk. Bring to a boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and stir in peanut butter, vanilla, salt and oats.
Spoon out onto waxed paper to cool and set.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Beat eggs well.
Combine mashed potatoes, brown sugar, pumpkin spice, milk and butter.
Mix well and add eggs.
Pour into 9-inch pie crust.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 375° and bake 40 to 45 minutes or until done.

title: my favorite cookies
directions: Let butter soften in a large mixing bowl.
Mix well with sugar. Add well beaten eggs, soda, salt, vanilla and pecans (broken) and mix well.
Gradually stir in flour.
Keep stirring or working until all is thoroughly mixed.
Tear off 6 pieces of waxed paper about 18 inches long.
Divide dough into 6 parts.
Shape each part on the sheet into a long roll, working the dough so that the roll is round and compact.
Store in the refrigerator until cold and firm.
Slice in thin slices and bake on the waxed paper.
Dough was rolled in on a cookie sheet.
Bake in 350° oven until light brown.
Remove and let cool on the waxed paper.
Each roll makes 3 to 4 dozen.

title: barney's peanut butter cream pie
directions: Into double boiler, place 2 1/2 cups milk and peanut butter. Heat and stir until mixture becomes smooth and thickens slightly. At this point, mix 1/2 cup milk and pudding powder.
Add to hot mixture.
Heat and stir often until pudding tracks 1/4-inch high across mixture.
Remove from heat.
Cool, stirring occasionally to prevent skinning.
When pudding is warm, pour into 9-inch pie shell.
Cover with waxed paper (prevents skinning).
When filling is firm and cool, top with Dream Whip or topping of your choice.

title: mother laser's spaghetti
directions: In frying pan, put ground round, bacon (cut in small pieces); cook until well done.
Saute onions and green peppers.
Put all ingredients in pan; simmer for 1 hour.
Stir frequently.
Cook spaghetti.
Place sauce over spaghetti.
Serve with Italian bread, green salad and red wine.

title: breakfast specials
directions: Layer white bread slices in an oblong casserole dish (3-quart).
Brown and drain sausage.
Layer on top of bread; then layer cheese.
Mix together eggs, milk, dry mustard, salt and pepper.
Pour over the top of sausage and cheese.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake in a moderate oven for 30 to 35 minutes, until lightly browned and firm.

title: creamy fruit dressing
directions: Mix milk and pudding together with rotary beater for 1 to 2 minutes.
Fold in sour cream.
Chill.
Serve on fresh fruit.

title: finger snack
directions: Boil the last 3 ingredients, stirring constantly for 2 minutes.
Pour over mixture.

title: kielbasa appetizer
directions: Boil a kielbasa link for about 10 minutes.
Cool and slice. Mix 1/2 jar apricot preserves and 1 jar of sweet and sour sauce. Add sliced kielbasa and heat.
Serve hot on toothpicks.

title: donna's mozzarella cheese dip
directions: Blend together all ingredients except for Mozzarella cheese. Add cheese and mix well.
Refrigerate for at least 2 hours or overnight.

title: blueberry crunch
directions: Grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Layer ingredients evenly as listed: pineapple, blueberries, sugar, cake mix, margarine and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Press crescent rolls into greased pizza pan.
Bake at 350° until light brown.

title: eric's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix the first 9 ingredients in a large bowl; mix well.
Mix in the flour one cup at a time.
Add the remaining ingredients (choose your wanted combination).
Do not grease cookie sheets!
Drop by tablespoonfuls onto cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes on center rack of oven.
For softer cookies, remove from cookie sheet within 2 minutes of removing from oven.
For crisper cookies, allow to cool 5 to 10 minutes before removing from cookie sheets.
Cool completely and then store in airtight containers.

title: green tomato mincemeat
directions: Wash tomatoes and put through food processor.
Put all ingredients in a pan except raisins; cook over low heat 1 hour, stirring frequently.
Add raisins and cook until mixture is thick. Fill hot jars and seal.
Makes 5 1/2 pints.

title: cauliflower and potato soup
directions: Peel and cut potatoes.
Cut cauliflower coarsely.
Cook together in just enough water to cover.
Saute onion and garlic in butter until onion is transparent.
Gradually add flour to the butter and onions.
Stir until pasty, over low heat.
Add milk, stirring constantly.
Heat until mixture thickens.

title: breakfast squares
directions: The night before, break bread into cube-size pieces.
Beat together eggs and milk.
Add bread cubes and allow to soak.
Cook sausage and drain well.
Lightly greased 11 x 7-inch glass baking dish.
Layer sausage and cheese in pan.
Pour egg mixture on top and mix gently.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: easy  chicken casserole
directions: Place cut up chicken in large casserole dish, set aside. Thoroughly mix soup and milk together and pour over chicken. Place bread crumbs over top of soup mixture and pour broth over top of bread crumbs.
Bake in 350 degree oven until casserole browns or starts to bubble.
This is great to freeze,
so make two and save time later.

title: barbecue smokies
directions: Place ingredients in crock-pot.
Cook approximately 4 to 6 hours.
Smokes sausage can also be used. Great for picnics or homecomings.

title: fudge cookies
directions: Bring to a boil for 1 to 1 1/2 minutes the sugar, margarine, cocoa, salt and milk; heat to 235° on thermometer.
Remove from heat.
Add oats, coconut, nuts, vanilla and flavoring; stir well. Drop by teaspoons onto wax paper.

title: numero uno bean dip
directions: Shells are used if serving escargot on stainless steel plates. If ceramic escargot plates are used, no shells or tongs are required.
And, if you're like me and don't have the fancy ceramic escargot plates or shells, use muffin tins.

title: fried okra
directions: Thaw okra.
Combine beaten eggs and milk.
Place thawed okra in milk and let stand for 15 minutes.
Drain okra a small portion at a time.
In a large freezer bag, combine flour, meal, salt, and pepper.
Add drained okra and shake to coat well.
Heat oil in a large skillet.
Drop a single layer of coated okra into hot oil. Cook until browned, turning only once with a spatula.
Drain on paper towels.
Repeat until all okra is cooked.
Serve while hot.

title: chicken breasts parmesan
directions: Mix tomato sauce, Italian seasoning and garlic salt in 2 cup measure.
Cover with waxed paper.
Microwave on High (100%) 2 minutes; stir.
Reduce power to Medium (50%).
Microwave 5 minutes, stirring once.
Set sauce aside.
Mix crushed cereal, 1/4 cup Parmesan and parsley flakes.
Dip chicken breasts in egg, then crumb mixture.
Place in 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
Cover with waxed paper.
Microwave at Medium-high (70%) until tender, 9 to 14 minutes; rearrange after half the cooking time (do not turn).
Pour sauce over chicken.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella.
Microwave at Medium-high (70%) until cheese melts and sauce is hot, 2 to 5 1/2 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook the chicken breasts; skin, bone and cut in chunks.
Add to chicken the chicken soup, mushroom soup, bread cubes and eggs. Melt oleo; add half to corn flakes and the other half with chicken.
Pour chicken mixture into a 9 x 13-inch pan and sprinkle corn flakes over top.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: escalloped oysters
directions: Drain liquid from oysters and reserve.
Be sure oysters are free from shell or sand.
Place 1 layer of oysters in large baking dish.
Sprinkle with salt and cover with a layer of crumbs. Repeat with another layer of oysters, salt and crumbs.
Dot with butter.

title: mammy's sugar cookies
directions: Cream the sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, vanilla, buttermilk, soda, salt and baking powder. Add flour until they can be rolled out nicely (approximately 2 1/2 cups).
Bake at 450° until lightly browned, 5 to 10 minutes.

title: charlie bread
directions: Mix ingredients; pour into greased pan.
Bake at 425° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: bean casserole
directions: Brown meat in skillet and mix with the rest of the ingredients.
Bake in oven at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: appetizer cheese puffs
directions: In saucepan, boil bouillon; add butter and salt and boil until melted.
Then add flour, all at once.
Remove from heat and stir in eggs very well, one at a time.
Stir in cheese and almonds. Preheat oven to 450°.
Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet and bake 8 to 10 minutes.
May be held after making and baked when needed. Also freezes well after baking.

title: heavenly apricot dessert
directions: Dissolve jello and sugar in boiling water.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Cream together the cream cheese and baby food apricots.
Beat in crushed pineapple with juice.
Add Cool Whip. Beat until blended well.
With spoon, stir gelatin mixture into cream cheese mixture.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch pan and refrigerate until firm.

title: corn crab soup
directions: Saute onions in butter.
Add flour, mixing well.
Slowly add whipping cream, half and half, broth and corn.
Simmer for 20 minutes.
Add crabmeat and cook on low heat for 20 minutes more. Season to taste.
Serves 10 to 12.
Very rich and thick.
May add water.
Can substitute low-fat milk for whipping cream and half and half to cut down on richness and calories.

title: creamy crunchy potatoes(great barbecue side dish)
directions: In a saucepan cook onion in 2 tablespoons butter until tender. In a bowl, combine thawed hash browns, sour cream, cream soup, onion mixture and jalapenos, if you like.
Transfer to a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle with cornflakes and drizzle with melted butter.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 45 minutes or until golden.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: clam chowder
directions: Cook small diced potatoes in small amount of water until tender.
Saute green pepper and onion in stick of margarine. Drain most of water from potatoes.
Add bottle of clam juice and juice of can of clams, reserving clams for later.
Cook over medium heat.
Add sauteed onion and potato flakes.
Add milk to desired thickness; heat thoroughly.
Add clams just before serving.

title: dish pan cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Make balls and flatten.
Bake at 325° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: pickles
directions: Cook until ingredients are dissolved.
Pour hot over pickles and stand for 24 hours.

title: rhubarb bread
directions: Pour into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake for 60 minutes at 325°. You may sprinkle 1/2 cup sugar and 1 tablespoon of butter over top before baking.

title: spicy carrot cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 12-cup fluted tube pan. In a large bowl, combine sugar and oil.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
In medium bowl, combine remaining ingredients.
Add the sugar mixture, mixing just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Cool completely on wire rack.
Drizzle with confectioners sugar icing, if desired. Makes 12 to 16 servings.

title: pinto bean pie
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° until pie is firm.

title: marion rowan's rice casserole
directions: Saute onion, celery and mushrooms.
Mix with rice, soup and sour cream.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for about 20 to 30 minutes.
Use large Pyrex loaf pan or two 1-quart Corning Ware casseroles.
Freezes well.
A meal in a dish.

title: hamburger enchiladas
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain.
Add 1 can of cream of chicken soup and 4 ounces of the Cheez Whiz.
Roll the hamburger mixture equally into the 12 tortillas.
In a saucepan, heat 1 can cream of chicken soup, Ro-Tel tomatoes/green chilies and other 4 ounces of Cheez Whiz together until cheese is melted.
Pour over the tortillas in a 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: hamburger noodle casserole
directions: Baking Temperature: 350°.
Baking Time: 1 1/2 hours.

title: potato tortilla
directions: Brown hamburger meat; drain grease.
Peel potatoes; cut and cook until done.
Mash potatoes.
Cool meat and potatoes.
When cooled, add shredded cheese.
Season to taste.
Wrap in tortilla corn shells.
Close with toothpick.
Deep fry for 3 minutes.

title: tuna chow mein
directions: Combine everything but noodles.
Place 1 can of noodles on bottom of pan.
Cover with tuna mixture.
Top with rest of noodles.
Bake for 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Mix chopped vegetables together.
Mix dressing ingredients until creamy and add to vegetables.

title: grape-nut pudding(lo-fat; no cholesterol)
directions: Stir all ingredients together.
Lightly spread a little margarine in a 2-quart casserole.
Pour in mixture.
Place casserole dish in a pan of water (about 1 cup in 13 x 9-inch pan). Bake in 350° oven for 40 minutes or until knife comes out clean.

title: baked lima beans
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for an hour.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat together first 4 ingredients; Add; flour, salt, cinnamon, ginger, baking soda, baking powder, nutmeg, and nuts. Mix well and then add zucchini. Pour into a greased and floured bundt pan. Bake 325°F. for 1 hour. To make it chocolate,
just add: 4 tbsp. cocoa.

title: crock-pot chicken
directions: Boil and debone chicken breasts.
Mix all ingredients together well and pour into crock-pot. Cook on low for 6 to 8 hours. Serve over rice.

title: easy baby food cake
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together real good.
Add last 3 ingredients and mix well.
Pour in greased and floured tube pan. Bake approximately 1 hour at 350°.

title: bake while you sleep cookies
directions: Set oven at 350°.
In a room temperature glass bowl, beat room temperature egg whites until foamy.
Add salt and cream of tartar. Beat until stiff.
Add sugar 2 tablespoons at a time.
Beat each time.
Add vanilla.
Then add chocolate chips and nuts.
Put by teaspoon on foil covered cookie sheets.
Turn oven off and put cookies in.
Must stay 8 hours.
Yield: about 4 dozen.

title: chow or relish
directions: Grind vegetables or chop fine.
Sprinkle with salt.
Mix.
Let stand overnight.
Rinse and drain well.
Combine the vinegar and other ingredients.
Pour over the vegetable mixture.
Heat to a boil and simmer 3 minutes.
Seal in hot sterile jars.
Makes about 8 pints.

title: blackberry salad
directions: Mix jello and water until dissolved.
Cool.
Add pineapple and pie filling.
Let chill until firm.
Spread top with cream cheese, sour cream and sugar that have been beaten until soft.
Sprinkle with nuts, if desired.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Spoon into 8-inch square baking dish.
Top with spaghetti sauce and cheese.
Combine biscuit mix, milk and eggs until smooth.
Pour over top of beef mixture.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 400°.

title: layered casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown meat and onion in large skillet sprayed with nonstick cooking spray.
Add tomato sauce and seasonings.
Simmer 7 to 8 minutes.
In large bowl, combine green pepper, cottage cheese, cream cheese and sour cream.
Mix thoroughly.
Spray a large casserole dish (9 x 13-inch) with nonstick cooking spray.
Cover bottom with pasta.
Add a layer of meat mixture.
Pour cottage cheese mixture for next layer and top with shredded fat-free cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: pineapple chess pie
directions: Combine all the ingredients.
Pour into an unbaked pie crust and bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes or until set.

title: striped delight(non bake)
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs, 1/4 cup sugar and melted margarine.
Press
firmly
into
bottom
of a 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: german slaw
directions: Grate cabbage.
Chop onion.
Toss all ingredients with several tablespoons sour cream.

title: coconut shoo-fly pie
directions: Mix together flour, sugar and coconut to form crumbs.
Reserve 1/2 cup of this mixture for topping in another bowl.
Mix egg, syrup and 3/4 cup hot water.
Add to dry ingredients.
Dissolve baking soda in remaining 1/4 cup hot water.
Add to mixture.
Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Sprinkle with remaining crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: apple strudel
directions: Mix ingredients with a dough blender.
Dough will be soft. Refrigerate overnight or for several hours.
Divide dough into 3 portions.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Cook and drain the sausage.
Mix well the eggs, sour cream, milk and seasonings.
Pour over the sliced cheese in a 8 x 10-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with the cooked sausage.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cherry cream cheese pie
directions: In a medium bowl, beat cream cheese until light and fluffy. Add Eagle Brand milk, slowly and beat until smooth.
Stir in lemon juice and vanilla until well mixed.
Pour into pie crust and chill for 2 hours.
Top with cherry pie filling.

title: vinaigrette
directions: Shake all ingredients in tightly covered container.

title: creole flounder
directions: Place fish in greased oblong baking dish, 13 1/2 x 9 x 2-inches.
Mix remaining ingredients, spoon onto fish.
Cook, uncovered, in 400° oven until fish flakes easily with fork, about 10 minutes.
Garnish with green pepper rings and tomato wedges, if desired.

title: perfect pot roast
directions: Wipe pot roast with damp paper towels.

In hot oil and butter in 5-quart Dutch oven or heavy kettle, over medium heat, brown roast along with sliced onion (onion browns and gives a good dark color and rich flavor to pan drippings), turning roast with two wooden spoons, until well browned on all sides, 25 minutes in all. Slow browning gives the meat and gravy a better flavor and color.

title: four fold delight
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: diabetic raisin cookies
directions: Combine eggs and Sucaryl and add ingredients in order given. Drop by teaspoon and bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: aunt lois' microwave hot bean salad
directions: Fry bacon in skillet until crisp; crumble bacon and reserve. Combine bacon drippings, sugar and cornstarch in glass baking dish; mix well.
Stir in vinegar, salt and red pepper.
Microwave on High for 3 to 4 minutes or until thickened.
Add beans and onion; mix well.
Microwave for 6 minutes, stirring once.
Let stand for 10 minutes.
Sprinkle with bacon to serve.
Yield:
15 servings.

title: apple butter spice cookies
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Set aside.
Combine sugar and shortening; cream until light and fluffy.
Beat in egg and stir in apple butter.
Add dry ingredients, mixing well.
Stir in raisins and nuts.
Drop onto lightly greased cooking sheets.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Remove to racks to cool.
Makes about 8 dozen.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix sugar and eggs.
Beat until fluffy (by hand).
Add oil. Mix in dry ingredients.
Add vanilla.
Mix well and then add apples and nuts.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake in preheated oven at 325° about 35 to 40 minutes.
Do not overcook.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar. Add eggs; beat well. Stir together dry ingredients; add to creamed mixture. Mash bananas and add to mixture. Beat well. Stir in walnuts.
Pour into well greased loaf pan. Bake in moderate oven at 350° about 1 hour or until done. Remove from pan and cool on rack.

title: chinese almond cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 2 large cookie sheets and set aside.
In large mixing bowl with electric mixer at medium speed, cream lard, shortening and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add 2 eggs and extracts and continue beating until well mixed, scraping sides of bowl occasionally.
In medium bowl put flour, baking powder and baking soda.
Gradually add dry ingredients to cream mixture; continue beating just until well mixed.
Dough will be dry and crumbly.
Roll dough into one inch balls.
Press a half almond in the center of each ball.
Brush top with beaten egg.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen, 130 calories each.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Mix with electric mixer.
Pour into baking dish and cook for 35 to 45 minutes at 300° or until firm.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix together.
Form into ball and roll in crushed pecans. Chill overnight.

title: corn muffins(6)
directions: Mix well.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: company casserole
directions: Brown crumbled beef in butter.	Remove from heat;
stir in tomato
sauce.
Salt
and
pepper to taste.
Combine onions and peppers with
cheeses
and sour cream. Cook noodles 7 to 8 minutes in	boiling, generously salted water.
Drain and rinse quickly in cold water.

title: peanut butter drop cookies
directions: Sift flour and	baking	soda;
set aside.
Cream peanut butter, butter and vanilla.
Add honey and sugar, beating well after each addition.
Then	add
2 well beaten eggs; mix well. Then add the sifted flour.	Drop
on
cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.	Cool.
Check
to
see that they do not brown too fast on bottom.

title: old-fashioned pancakes
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add milk, butter and dry ingredients which have been sifted.
Bake on a greased hot griddle or skillet until pancakes have bubbles. Turn over and continue to cook until golden brown. Extra shortening may be added while cooking.
Serve with syrup, molasses or honey.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: chicken with rice
directions: Combine oregano, pepper and salt (for the chicken) and rub over chicken.
Heat olive oil and add the chicken.
Brown chicken for 10 minutes at high temperature.
Add garlic, bell pepper, onion and tomato and cook for 2 minutes.
Add water, tomato sauce, cilantro and paprika and bring it to a boil.
Add rice and salt (for the rice) and cook uncovered until it dries.
Stir and lower temperature to low and cover for 20 minutes.
Cook for another 15 minutes (still at low), stirring occasionally.
Let stand for 5 minutes before serving.
Top with stuffed green onions and garnish with red bell peppers, finely sliced.

title: creamy gift fudge
directions: Open cream cheese and let sit in a bowl outside of the refrigerator for 1 hour.

title: mix-in-the-pan chocolate nut bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Put ingredients in an ungreased pan.
Stir with fork for 1 to 2 minutes.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: pork chops with rice
directions: Brown pork chops in shortening or fat.
Combine uncooked rice, tomato juice, salt, pepper, green pepper and onion.
Pour over chops and cook, covered, on low heat about 1 hour or until vegetables are thoroughly cooked.
Remove from skillet and thicken the vegetable liquid left in skillet for sauce to serve with chops.

title: percolator punch
directions: Take good ripe grapes and put into a porcelain kettle, add two quarts of water for every gallon of grapes.

Boil briskly for about ten minutes, then pour into a cheesecloth bag and drain, then put juice back into kettle and add one pint of water (this additional pint of water may be poured over the pulp in the bag to extract all the juice).
Sugar to taste, boil briskly for ten minutes.
Skim and put into glass fruit jars and seal.
Glass top fruit jars are best as no metal should come in contact with the wine.
This is an excellent beverage for the sick.

title: pedernales river chili
directions: Sear meat, onions and garlic in large, heavy skillet until lightly browned.
Add seasonings, tomatoes and hot water.
Bring to a boil.
Lower heat and simmer about 1 hour.
As chili cooks, skim off fat.

title: barbecue spareribs
directions: Place ribs in baking pan.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 1 hour.
Chop onion and brown in oil.
Add juice, vinegar, Worcestershire sauce, brown sugar, water, catsup, salt and pepper. Cook slowly for 20 minutes.
Pour over ribs.
Continue baking for 1 hour.

title: sticky buns
directions: Combine yeast, milk, sugar, vinegar and 1 1/2 c. flour; allow to stand until bubbly.

title: kiss cookies
directions: Beat sugar, margarine and vanilla until light.
Beat in flour and add nuts.
Divide
dough
and
shape
around Kisses. Bake 12 minutes at 350° on ungreased sheets.

title: lime chiffon salad
directions: Drain pineapple reserving the juice.
Dissolve jello in boiling water; add reserved juice.
Cool until slightly thickened; beat until frothy.
Fold in pineapple, cottage cheese, mayonnaise and nuts.
Place in bowl or mold.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: canned spaghetti sauce
directions: Cook tomatoes in hot water bath.
Remove peeling.
Quarter and put in large canning pot.
Cook tomatoes and garlic until tender. Chop peppers and onions.
Add with spices and cook on medium-low until thickened.
Pour into containers and turn upside-down.
They will seal on their own!

title: american pierogi
directions: Layer 9 x 13-inch pan with small amount of onions, then noodles, then mashed potatoes.
Place on top slices of cheese; repeat ending top layer with cheese.
Bake at 350° until brown on top (20 to 30 minutes).

title: stuffed cabbage rolls
directions: You will need a 6-quart pressure cooker.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Brown hamburger and onions.
Drain.
Stir in salt and pepper. Place in bottom of greased 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle with cheese. Combine milk, Bisquick and eggs.
Beat until smooth.
Pour over meat and cheese and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Roll meat in flour and brown in hot grease in a large frying pan.
Remove meat; add onion, garlic, pepper and mushrooms.
Cook slowly until onions are a light golden color.
Add remaining ingredients except meat and sour cream.
Simmer until thick and bubbly.
Return meat to sauce and simmer, covered, stirring occasionally.
Add water as needed, if sauce becomes thick.
Cook until meat is tender and sauce is blended.
Add sour cream.
Serve over rice, noodles or mashed potatoes.
Serves 6 people.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Boil potatoes.
Whip with butter and milk as desired.
Brown hamburger. Layer hamburger, green beans and soup in an 8 x 8-inch casserole dish.
Cover with mashed potatoes; seal to the edges of the dish. Cover with aluminum foil and bake 40 minutes in moderately hot oven.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: mom's pizza sauce
directions: Saute onion in olive oil.
Add garlic, oregano, basil, sugar, tomato sauce and water.
Bring to a boil, then simmer, uncovered, until thick, stirring often (about 1/2 hour or until desired thickness).
Cool.
Pour over dough in cookie sheet.
Top with your favorite pizza toppings.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: walnut pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Combine pumpkin, sweetened condensed milk, egg, 3/4 teaspoon cinnamon, ginger, nutmeg and salt; mix well.
Turn into pie crust.
Bake 15 minutes; remove pie.
Reduce oven temperature to 350°.
Combine sugar, flour and remaining 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon; cut in margarine until crumbly.
Stir in walnuts.
Sprinkle walnut mixture evenly over pie.
Bake 40 minutes or until knife inserted 1-inch from edge comes out clean. Cool and refrigerate.

title: herbed carrots
directions: In a saucepan combine first three ingredients.
Add carrot sticks.
Cover tightly; cook on low heat 15 to 20 minutes.
Season to taste.
Sprinkle in parsley flakes.
Don't drain.

title: swiss butterhorn crescent rolls
directions: Combine flour and salt; cut in butter and margarine.
Stir in egg yolk and sour cream.
Mix well.
Shape dough into ball and wrap in waxed paper.
Chill 1 hour or overnight.
Divide dough into 3 parts.
On lightly floured board, roll each into 12-inch circles.
Cut into 12 pie shaped wedges.
Blend each wedge with sugar mixture.
Starting at wide edge, roll up.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Remove from oven and frost with frosting made out of powdered sugar, 2 tablespoons hot water and 1/4 teaspoon vanilla.
Drizzle on.

title: tiny fruit tarts
directions: Have oleo and cream cheese at room temperature.
Mix well with flour.
Chill.
Shape into balls the size of walnuts.
Make well in center; put about 1/4 teaspoon jelly into well.
Bake at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: reception punch
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Add orange and lemon slices, if desired.
Pour over ice in an elegant punch bowl.
Serves 100.

title: recipe for happiness
directions: Mix work well with patience.
Pour in love.
Add sympathy. Stir well with the spoon of understanding.
Sift in humor.
Bake thoroughly in an atmosphere of loyalty and trust.

title: scalloped potatoes au gratin(microwave)
directions: Arrange 1/2 of potatoes in bottom of greased 8-inch casserole dish.
Combine flour and salt; sprinkle 1/2 of it over potatoes in dish.
Spread 1/2 of cheese over flour and salt; repeat layers of potatoes, flour and salt and cheese.
Pour hot milk over potatoes; dot with butter and sprinkle with paprika.
Cook, uncovered, in microwave for 12 to 14 minutes, turning several times.
Makes 4 servings.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter.
Cook broccoli.
Mix all ingredients together.
Sprinkle cheese on top. Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 375° in covered casserole dish.

title: easy party punch
directions: Mix sugar, water and juice of 3 lemons until sugar dissolves. Add orange, cranberry and pineapple juice.
Stir well.
Makes about 24 servings.

title: layered chocolate dessert
directions: Follow directions on the box of cake.
Cool.
Follow directions on the box of pudding, too.
Get a large bowl for layering.
Cut the cake in small pieces. Put some pudding on the bottom of the bowl.
Then the cake, chocolate pudding, whip cream and then the Heath bars.
Continue till all of the ingredients are layered.
Put in the fridge to let it settle, about one hour. Grab a big spoon.
Serves about 10 people.
Enjoy!

title: tangy fruit salad
directions: Drain canned fruit well.
Slice bananas; chop unpeeled apples and peaches into bite-sized pieces.
Mix fruit gently; set aside. Combine dry pudding with milk, orange juice and sour cream.
Beat with wire whisk until smooth (mixture will thicken).
Fold fruit into sauce; stir well and chill.

title: skillet cookies
directions: Melt margarine over low heat.
Blend in brown sugar, dates, salt and egg.
Add vanilla.
Cook for 6 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add Rice Krispies and chopped pecans.
When cool enough to handle, roll into balls and then roll each cookie in powdered sugar or coconut.
Yields 40 cookies.

title: steak and rice
directions: Brown steak cubes, then add in beef broth, Lipton savory herbs with garlic and A.1.
Cook for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: Cook together the onion and squash.
Drain squash and onion mixture.
Mash well.
Pour squash into buttered baking dish. Add and mix well the remaining ingredients.
Bake in a 375° oven.

title: english toffee
directions: Boil the first 3 ingredients 10 minutes until brown and stir constantly.
Add the vanilla.
Pour thin layer on cookie sheet. Layer the Hershey bars on top.
Let set a few minutes and spread with a knife.
While warm, spread with chopped nuts.

title: sour cream sugar crisps
directions: Soften yeast in warm water. Sift together flour and salt in a large mixing bowl. Cut in butter/margarine and shortening.
Blend in the beaten eggs, sour cream, 1 teaspoon vanilla and yeast.
Mix thoroughly and chill at least 2 hours. Combine 1 1/2 cups sugar and 2 teaspoons vanilla. Set aside.

Roll out 1/2 of chilled dough on surface sprinkled with 1/2 cup vanilla sugar. Roll out into an 8 x 16-inch rectangle. Sprinkle with 1 tablespoon vanilla sugar. Fold one end over dough over center, then fold the other end to make 3 layers. Turn 1/4 of the way around and repeat rolling and folding twice, sprinkling surface with additional vanilla sugar each time as needed.
Roll again out to an 8 x 16-inch rectangle, 1/4-inch thick.
Cut into 4 x 1-inch strips.
Twist each strip 2 or 3 times.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Repeat with remaining dough.

title: foolproof dark chocolate fudge
directions: In heavy saucepan over low heat, melt chips with milk and salt.
Remove from heat.
Stir in walnuts and vanilla.
Spread evenly into wax paper-lined 8 or 9-inch pan.
Chill 2 hours or until firm.
Turn fudge onto cutting board; peel off paper and cut into squares.
Store loosely covered at room temperature.
Makes about 2 pounds.
This fudge can also be made in the microwave.

title: corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs. Sift corn meal, flour, baking powder and salt together.
Add alternately with milk.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan for 30 minutes.

title: marzetti
directions: Brown in skillet the meat, onion and pepper.
In a large kettle, add the mushrooms, tomatoes, cheese and noodles.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: chipped beef on toast
directions: Tear beef in small pieces, melt butter in frying pan.
Add beef, saute until beef is hot and turning brown.
Sprinkle flour and pepper over beef.
Stir to coat meat.
Add milk slowly, stirring.
Cook and stir constantly over low heat, until mixture thickens and boils.
Spoon on hot toast.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chicken pot pie i
directions: Place 1 pie crust in pie plate.
Mix chicken, soup, vegetables and broth in bowl.
Salt and pepper.
Pour into pie crust.
Cover with other pie crust and slit to allow for steam. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: chips and salsa
directions: In a mixing bowl combine peppers, onion, cilantro, lemon juice and garlic. Set aside. Place half of the tomatoes in the blender and blend till smooth. Pour over mixture in bowl and add the rest of the tomatoes. Cover and chill at least 3 hours before serving. Can be stored in the refrigerator up to 1 week. Wonderful as a dip for Chips or over any of your favorite Tex-Mex dishes.Makes about 2 cups.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix marshmallow cream, peanut butter and vanilla.
Set aside. Mix sugars and milk in a pan, bringing to a boil for 4 minutes. Pour cooked mixture over peanut butter mixture and keep stirring, until well mixed.
Pour into a buttered dish and let set to firm.

title: cucumber relish
directions: Chop and grate cucumbers, cabbage and onions.
Sprinkle salt over them and let stand overnight.
Drain.
Cook vinegar, sugar, mustard, celery seed, turmeric and flour.
Pour over the vegetables; cook together for a short time over low heat.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Melt butter, seasoning packet and chicken broth.
Boil a few minutes.
Mix soup, onion, celery and stuffing.
Mix well.

title: before dinner things
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Separate rolls into thirds (36 total).
Top each with mixture and slice of water chestnut.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: baked apples
directions: Core and halve apples.
Melt butter; stir in sugar, cornstarch and cinnamon.
Add water and cover.
