Cook in oven at 350° until tender, spooning sauce over the apples frequently. Cook in an ovenproof baking dish.

title: cranberry spice nut bread
directions: Combine sugar,	milk and egg.
Add salt, ginger, cinnamon, lemon
extract
and
biscuit
mix; beat until well mixed. Fold in cranberries
and
nuts.
Grease a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan. Bake in moderate
oven
at	350° for 60 to 65 minutes.
Remove from pan; cool before slicing.

title: swedish apple pie
directions: You will also need a buttered 9 to 10-inch pie plate.

title: strawberry yum yum
directions: Mix flour, margarine, brown sugar and nutmeats.
Press into an 8 x 11-inch pan and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Stir until crumbly and set aside to cool.

title: chocolate chip cookies 2
directions: Mix flour with baking powder; set aside.
Combine margarine, the sugars, vanilla and pudding mix and beat until smooth and creamy.
Beat in eggs.
Gradually add flour mixture; stir in chips and walnuts (batter will be stiff).
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto a cookie sheet, slightly greased.
Bake in a 375° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix sugar and oil together.
Add beaten eggs.
Mix dry ingredients and add to sugar mixture.
Mix well.
Add vanilla, apples and nuts; mix well.
Pour into a 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: 7-up salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water; add cream cheese and stir until dissolved.
Add other ingredients.
Place in refrigerator and chill until firm.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: creole country soup
directions: Wash, core and cut peppers into small pieces.
In small bowl, using a fork, crush and break tomatoes into edible pieces.
Stud onion with cloves; cut scallions into pieces.
Put water and chicken broth into large pot.
Bring to boil over high heat.
When liquid is at full rolling boil, add peppers, carrots, tomatoes, onion, scallions, celery, basil, thyme, turmeric, bay leaf and pepper flakes.
Return to boil; reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for 30 minutes.
Shrimp should thaw before using and add to liquid after 30 minutes cooking time. Add lemon juice; simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes.
Add crabmeat (it might unroll, not to worry) and cook for 5 minutes.
Add parsley at end of cooking time.

title: cowboy stew
directions: Note: Add bacon drippings for taste.

title: wasabi tuna steaks
directions: Whisk all ingredients together. Marinate tuna in refrigerator at least 4 hours.
Grill to desired doneness.
Serve with wasabi (horseradish).

title: ham and egg piroshki(little russian pies)
directions: Cook onions in butter until wilted.
Add ham, eggs, parsley, dill and sour cream to moisten.
Roll out pastry thin and cut into 3-inch rounds.
Put a spoonful of ham mixture on each round and moisten edges; fold and pinch edges together.
Brush with beaten egg and bake in preheated 400° oven until brown.
Makes 24 appetizers.

title: go west cole slaw
directions: Grate together cabbage, carrot, onion and bell pepper in a large mixing bowl.
Add mustard, vinegar, sugar and milk to cabbage.
Stir well; let set overnight.

title: wacky cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients into 8 x 11-inch cake pan.
Make a rounded hole in dry ingredients and add liquids.
Stir with fork, do not beat.
Cook for 35 minutes at 350°.

title: pickled oysters
directions: Combine all ingredients and let stand for 2 hours.
Serve cold.

title: tomato soup cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and egg.
Add soup and dry ingredients.
Bake at 350°.
Cool slightly and glaze.

title: homemade chili with beans
directions: Brown hamburger and onions.
Then drain.
Mix all other ingredients together.
Season with red pepper and chili powder to taste.
Simmer 45 minutes.

title: blueberry bread pudding
directions: Lightly spray with Pam an 8 x 8 inch baking pan.
Mix all ingredients in a bowl, then pour over bread allowing the bread to absorb the liquids.
Mix lightly and smooth.

title: tomato aspic
directions: Bring tomatoes to a boil.
Remove from heat and dissolve jello in tomatoes.
Add remaining ingredients and pour into mold; congeal.

title: box oven breakfast pizza
directions: Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Spread crescent roll dough on bottom.
Pinch seams together to form crust.
Sprinkle cooked bacon or sausage over crust.
Mix eggs, milk and salt and pepper.
Pour over top of ingredients on crust.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes in box oven at 425° (until eggs are set).

title: easy chicken pot pie
directions: Place contents of vegetable/seasoning packet and butter in bowl. Add water; stir partially. Melt butter.
Add stuffing crumbs; stir gently to mix.
tags: Stove Top chicken flavor stuffing mix

title: pineapple drop cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, pineapple, vanilla and nuts.
Sift flour, soda and salt together.
Add to creamed mixture. Mix well and drop by small spoonfuls on a greased cookie sheet. Place about 2 inches apart.
Bake in a 375° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.
Have ready a thin powdered sugar icing and frost while warm.

title: buffalo chip cookies
directions: Mix margarine, sugars, eggs and vanilla in one bowl.
Combine remaining ingredients in another bowl.
Mix dry ingredients with creamed ingredients.
Drop by big plops onto greased cookie sheet. These babies spread out a lot! Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes. Makes 3 dozen.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Cream the cream cheese and margarine.
Mix with flour.
Cut in one inch strips or rounds.
Beat egg and brush each piece.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Whip cream cheese until creamy.
Add sugar and peanut butter; mix and add milk slowly. Mix together.
Fold in whipped topping. Pour into pie shell and chill.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients for filling together, adding pecans last. Pour
into shell and bake 15 minutes at 400°, then bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: oh henry bars
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients and spread on jelly roll pan. Bake 12 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: italian green bean casserole
directions: Boil, cook and drain green beans.
Saute mushrooms in 2 tablespoons of butter and set aside.
Melt 4 tablespoons of butter over medium heat.
Add flour, salt and pepper.
When mixed, add milk.
Stir over medium heat until thickened.
Add 1 cup Cheddar cheese.
When melted, add mushrooms and remove from heat.

title: cream cheese dessert
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients into dough and press on cookie sheet or pizza pan and bake for 15 minutes in 350° oven.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese, La Creme and confectioners sugar and spread on cooled crust.
Put cherries or whatever fruit you want on top and serve.

title: fruit punch
directions: Mix altogether frozen juices, then add Hawaiian Punch, then ginger ale to taste.
Add ice and you're ready.
Very refreshing.

title: best-ever biscuits
directions: In a medium mixing bowl stir together flour, baking powder, sugar, cream of tartar, and salt.
Mix well to distribute the baking powder and the salt.

title: tartar sauce for fish
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Put leftovers in a fruit jar for a couple of days.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place apples or other fruit in a buttered baking dish.
Sift dry ingredients together and with a fork cut in the butter.
The mixture should be fine and crumbly.
Now sprinkle this crumbly mixture over the apples (or fruit) and put the dish in the oven. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: potatoes chantilly
directions: Peel and cut in thin slices as for French fries.
Place in center of a large piece of foil.
Pour whipping cream over potatoes.
Dot with butter, sprinkle on seasonings, parsley and cheese.
Fold foil over making tight package.
Place on shallow pan in oven for 40 minutes at 425°.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Drain vegetables.
Mix ingredients and place in 2-quart casserole.

title: cheese roll-up
directions: Roll out Velveeta cheese between 2 sheets of wax paper. Spread 4 ounces of cream cheese thinly over the Velveeta (8 ounces of cream cheese can be used if desired).
Sprinkle with garlic salt.
Cover with diced onion and chopped jalapeno peppers.
Roll all this up like a log.
Chill for 2 hours.
Sprinkle the outside with paprika before serving.

title: pot roast with mushroom gravy
directions: Cut slits in roast, using a sharp knife; push a garlic slice into each slit.
Sprinkle roast with salts and pepper; lightly dredge in flour, patting off excess.
Brown meat on all sides in hot oil over medium-high heat in a large Dutch oven.
Stir together coffee, undiluted soup, and Worcestershire sauce; pour over roast. Top with onion slices.
Reduce heat, cover, and simmer 4 hours or until tender.
Transfer roast to a serving platter, reserving drippings in Dutch oven; keep roast warm.
Combine cornstarch and 3 tablespoons cold water, and stir into drippings. Bring mixture to a boil, and cook, stirring constantly, 1 minute or until thickened.
Pour gravy over roast.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all together and shape in a ball.
Roll in chopped nuts.

title: chocolate buckeyes
directions: Dip balls in chocolate mixture.
Makes about 19 dozen.

title: freezer corn
directions: Mix together and cook for a few minutes.
Cool with ice water, placing pan in water.
Stir corn until cool.
Put in containers and freeze.

title: lime pickle
directions: Add slack lime to cucumbers and cover with cold water.
Let stand 24 hours.
Drain and rinse well in two or three cold water baths and then soak for 3 hours in clear cold water.
Drain well. Mix vinegar, sugar, celery seed, salt, cinnamon sticks, mace, turmeric and cloves.
Pour over pickles cold and let stand 24 hours.
Then cook pickles and vinegar mixture for 20 minutes (cook slowly).
Let simmer while filling jars.
Seal while hot.

title: mexican dip
directions: In a clear glass bowl, layer ingredients in order given, ending with thin layer of scallions.
Serve with corn chips or plain taco chips.
Dig deep.

title: new orleans pralines
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients in a heavy saucepan until soft ball stage, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in pecans and vanilla, continuing to stir until mixture begins to thicken.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Let set until hardens.

title: cheese roll
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Use garlic salt and chili powder to taste.
Shape into a ball or roll and chill.

title: thin vegetable soup
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Combine all ingredients together in soup pot.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat, cover and simmer until all vegetables are tender.
Serves 10.

title: sausage rice casserole
directions: Spread
rice evenly in a lightly greased 3 quart casserole dish, sprayed.
Spoon vegetables over rice.
Pour chicken broth and
water
over
the
vegetables.
Cook
sausage until browned; drain
well.
Spoon
sausage over vegetables.
Cover and
bake
at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and stir well.
Cover
and bake an additional 30 minutes.
Garnish with mushrooms and parsley, if desired.

title: marinated cauliflower salad
directions: Cook cauliflower according to directions on package and drain. Combine cauliflower and remaining ingredients; stir well.
Cover and chill for 3 hours, stirring occasionally.
Serve on lettuce leaves.
Yields 2 servings.

title: crab salad
directions: In a large bowl, mix all the ingredients, ending with a mixture of 1/2 cup mayonnaise, stirring into 1/4 cup pickle juice or to taste.
Refrigerate at least 3 hours for the flavors to blend.
Before serving, add salt and pepper to taste.

title: wassail
directions: Combine the lemon and orange juices and set aside.
In a saucepan heat the water and sugar until sugar dissolves, add cinnamon, allspice and the rinds.
Simmer for 1 hour.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Heat until hot but not boiling.
Serve with individual sticks of cinnamon.

title: beefy baked beans
directions: Prepare ground beef by frying.
Add ground beef and beans together into ovenproof dish.
Mix mustard, brown sugar, molasses and onion.
Add mixture to beans and ground beef.
Place in oven. Preheat oven to 350° and heat for approximately 1 1/2 hours.

title: red, white and blueberry delight
directions: Combine crumbs, sugar and margarine.
Press on bottom of 12 x 7-inch dish.
In bowl, combine sweetened condensed milk, lemon juice, yogurt, marshmallows and nuts.
Spread half the mixture over crust.
Top with half the berries, remaining yogurt mixture, then remaining berries.
Cover; freeze 6 hours or until firm. Remove from freezer 10 minutes before serving.
Freeze leftovers. Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: apple crumble
directions: Set oven at 325°.
Cook apples until slightly soft.
Put in baking dish (shallow) and let cool.
If desired, they can be sprinkle with cinnamon-sugar.
Combine the flour, margarine and sugar, making "crumble."
Cover apples with crumble and bake for 1 hour.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix well and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together and chill in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Drain liquid from salmon and add enough milk to make 1 1/2 cups liquid. Add liquid to bread cubes.
Stir in salmon, macaroni, butter, eggs, parsley, onions, salt and paprika.
Turn into loaf pan that has been buttered, foil lined and again buttered. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: potato soup(vichyssoise)
directions: Heat onion, bouillon cubes, water and salt in large saucepan and mixture boils.
Reduce heat; cover tightly and simmer 10 minutes.
Remove from heat; stir in 1/2 cup milk.
Mix in potato puffs with fork; beat until fluffy.
Stir in 1 1/2 cups milk gradually.
Heat just until soup boils.
Cover and chill thoroughly.
Five minutes before serving, have ready 1 cup light cream and snipped chives.
Mix into soup the cream.
Top with chives.

title: pickles
directions: Put cucumbers in churn with about 2 cups salt to 1 gallon water until egg floats.
Let set 7 days.
Take out of churn and wash well.
Cut up.
Put 4 tablespoons alum to 1 gallon water and pour over cut up cucumbers.
Let set overnight and wash well.
Put back in churn.
Pour 1 gallon vinegar over them and let set 6 hours. Pour vinegar off and throw away.
Put sugar and spice in layers. Let set 2 days.
Do not seal.
When adding spice, put in a thin cloth.
Use 5% vinegar (Heinz).

title: skillet baked beans
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Remove from pan.
Fry onion until tender (but not browned).
Return bacon to pan (drain some of drippings, if desired).
Add remainder of ingredients and cook and stir over low heat 20 minutes.
If longer cooking is desired, cover and continue cooking until ready to serve.
Add water to tomato juice during cooking if too much liquid is boiled away. Stir several times to prevent sticking.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Pour boiling water over shortening, sugar and salt.
Beat until shortening is melted.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add eggs and beat well.
Dissolve yeast in 1 cup warm water and add.
Stir in flour.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Knead well; make into rolls.
Let rise in warm place for 2 hours.
Bake at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Dough will keep in refrigerator for 10 days.

title: spamburgers
directions: Place all ingredients through food chopper or grater and into a large bowl.
Add grated cheese and tomato sauce.
Mix well. Place a good portion on each wiener bun and wrap in wax paper and bake in slow oven at 200° at least 1 hour.
Serve and enjoy.
May be frozen and used later.
Makes 24 servings.

title: potato salad
directions: In top of double boiler, mix flour, sugar, dry mustard, salt and eggs.
Slowly add vinegar and milk, stirring constantly.
Cook over hot water until thick; cool.
When ready to use, mix cooked mixture with Miracle Whip and French's prepared mustard to taste. Pour over potato mixture and refrigerate several hours to blend flavors.
Salad dressing can be thinned with cream.

title: chocolate no bake cookies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, oleo and milk.
Bring to boil for about 1 1/2 minutes.
Add (have ready) vanilla, salt and peanut butter. Stir in and add oats.
Stir until mixture starts to thicken. Spoon on wax paper.
Leave to cool.

title: easy chili
directions: In a large, heavy skillet, heat the oil.
Brown the meat in the oil with the onion and garlic.
Add whole tomatoes, barbecue sauce, chili powder, salt, hot pepper sauce, cumin and kidney beans; mix well. Cover and simmer for an hour, stirring occasionally.
Serve hot with warm, crisp tortilla chips and, if desired, a side dish of jalapeno peppers.
Chili tastes best after refrigerating overnight and reheating.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: harvard beets
directions: In small saucepan, stir together cornstarch, sugar, salt and pepper.
Gradually stir in 2/3 cup beet liquid and vinegar.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and boils.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Add beets and heat through.

title: gladys' cranberry salad
directions: Prepare jello as directed.
When slightly jelled, add the ground cranberries, pecans, pineapple, sugar and marshmallows. Mix well.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: garden fresh chicken waldorf salad
directions: Blend together mayonnaise and apple juice.
Add remaining ingredients.
Toss gently to coat.
Serve chilled.
Store refrigerated.
Makes 5 servings.

title: seafoam salad
directions: Heat pear juice.
Add jello and stir until dissolved.
While still hot, pour juice/jello mixture over the cream cheese which has been blended with 2 tablespoons cream.
Stir until uniform. Refrigerate until the jello begins to thicken, then add pears which have been mashed with a fork.
Fold in whipped cream.
Pour into mold and refrigerate until firm.

title: skillet vegetables
directions: Saute zucchini, carrots and onion in oleo until tender.
Add water and basil; bring to a boil.
Stir in uncooked rings.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer 10 minutes or until rings are tender.
Season to taste.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: oven french fries
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cut potatoes into 1/2-inch strips. Place in strong Ziploc bag along with oil.
Toss in closed bag. Put in single layer on cookie sheet.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Sprinkle with desired seasoning.
(To remove starch from potatoes, put sliced potatoes in ice water for an hour, then drain and pat dry before mixing with oil.)

title: large chocolate cake
directions: Cream sugar and oleo together.
Add eggs.
Add rest of ingredients except boiling water.
Mix together.
Add boiling water and mix.
Put in greased cake pan (9 x 13-inch) and bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: chinese green beans
directions: Place uncooked green beans in casserole dish.
Combine all the other ingredients (except noodles) and pour over frozen green beans.
Bake 45 minutes at 375°.
Remove from oven; stir gently. Top with noodles and bake 10 minutes more.
Serves 6.

title: holiday fruit balls(makes 100 balls)
directions: Melt butter and marshmallows in milk over low heat, stirring constantly until melted. Mix rest, except coconut. Pour milk mixture over and stir until well mixed. Form into small balls and roll in coconut.

title: gooey chicken
directions: Mix all sauce ingredients together.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until chicken is cooked.
Serve with rice. Serves 6.

title: hamburger and tater tot casserole
directions: Cook hamburger meat. Drain fat. Put in casserole dish. Layer the remaining ingredients in casserole dish with Tater Tots on top. Cook at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: quick dinner in a pan
directions: Place all ingredients in order in a large, deep casserole dish.
Cover and heat for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: chili
directions: Brown onion, green pepper and hamburger.

Add tomato sauce, tomato paste, tomatoes and catsup, then add Worcestershire sauce, hot sauce, Italian seasoning, oregano, garlic powder or minced garlic, onion salt, salt and pepper to taste, chili powder and 2 cans chili beans (red kidney).
Simmer for 2 hours.

title: fancy green beans
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Add green beans, soup, bean sprouts and almonds; cook for 10 minutes.
Transfer to casserole dish; bake at 325° until it bubbles with lid off.
Just before serving, sprinkle with cheese and Durkee fried onions.
Heat through.

title: cornmeal pound cake
directions: Cream and mix oleo, sugar and vanilla; add eggs and dry ingredients, mixing well!
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: crepes
directions: Sift flour and salt in a bowl.
Add water, a little at a time, whisking constantly.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Finally, add milk, stirring vigorously, until batter is smooth.

title: 5 flavor pound cake
directions: Cream oleo and oil; add sugar.
Beat in eggs one at a time; beat well.
Add baking powder and flavorings.
Alternately add flour and milk.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: scrumptious lemon lush
directions: Mix together flour, margarine and half the nuts.
Pat into 9 x 13-inch baking dish and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until slightly brown.
Cool.
Mix powdered sugar, cream cheese and 1 small carton of Cool Whip together.
Spread on crust.
Mix together pudding and milk; let stand until thick.
Pour on top of cream cheese mixture.
Cover with the second carton of Cool Whip. Sprinkle with remaining nuts.
Chill 15 minutes, covered.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
With a wooden spoon, beat together the first 4 ingredients for 30 seconds.
Drop by heaping tablespoon on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake in center of oven until golden, 10 minutes.
Mix together the melted butter, garlic powder and parsley flakes.
Brush generously over tops as soon as they come out.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Bring sugar and syrup to boil.
Remove from the heat and add the peanut butter and Rice Krispies.
Drop by spoonfuls onto ungreased platter.

title: broccoli cheese dip
directions: Melt butter.
Add onion.
Microwave 1 minute.
Add cheese and microwave until melted.
Mix thoroughly.
Thaw broccoli in microwave and add to cheese mixture.
Stir in mayonnaise.
Cut out center of rye bread.
Break into bite-sized pieces.
Pour cheese mixture into hollow of bread.
Dip bread into cheese mixture.

title: southern peanut brittle
directions: Heat sugar, syrup, water and salt to a rolling boil in a heavy 2-quart saucepan.
Add peanuts.
Reduce heat to medium and stir constantly.
Cook to hard crack stage (293°).
Add butter and the baking soda (for safety's sake, keep in mind that the mixture will dramatically increase in volume and could spill over the sides of the saucepan).
Beat rapidly and pour onto a lightly greased baking sheet, spreading to 1/4-inch thickness.
When cool, break into pieces.
Store in an airtight container.
Makes about 2 pounds.

title: cucumber dressing
directions: Blend all ingredients.
This dressing will keep well in refrigerator.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, nuts and bananas.
Sift flour and soda.
Add to mixture.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake 50 minutes to 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: cream of potato-broccoli-cheese soup
directions: In large saucepan, combine chicken broth, onion, potatoes and broccoli.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and cover pan.
Simmer until all vegetables are tender.
Place half of vegetable mix in blender until smooth.
Pour blended vegetables back into the other vegetables.
In another pan, melt the butter, blend in flour and salt.
Add milk, cook stirring until mixture is thickened.
Stir in cheese.
Pour all into vegetable mixture.
Add pepper and heat thoroughly.
Serve hot!

title: bacon-wrapped dove breast
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (or cook on grill). Split and bone dove breast. Cut each strip and wrap in a piece of bacon. Fold dove breast around jalapeno strip and wrap in piece of bacon. Secure with toothpick. Bake for about 50 minutes or until bacon is done.

title: lemon yum-yum
directions: Cream together and press in casserole with hands.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: cream cheese mints
directions: Mix cream cheese and peppermint; gradually add powdered sugar. Knead until no longer sticky.
Divide into 4 portions; knead in food color of your choice.
Shape into 3/4-inch balls.
Roll in sugar and flatten with a fork.
Let dry at room temperature. Store in a sealed container in the refrigerator.
(An added touch to your table for special occasions and holidays.)

title: peach and currant compote
directions: In a medium saucepan, combine orange juice, currant jelly and nutmeg; stir in peaches and currants.
Bring to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 5 to 8 minutes or until the fruit is just tender.
Serve the compote warm or let it cool to room temperature.
If desired, garnish with fresh mint leaves.

title: cabbage and cheese
directions: Brown hamburger with onion.
Add tomato sauce and seasonings and bring to a boil.
Spray casserole with Pam.
Put cabbage in casserole and pour hot meat mixture over it.
Cover and bake in 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours.
Take out and sprinkle cheese on top. Return to oven to melt cheese.
Cool and cut into servings.

title: chocolate eclair
directions: Mix pudding according to package directions. Add Cool Whip to pudding. Layer graham crackers in 9 1/2 x 11-inch container, alternating pudding and graham crackers, ending with a layer of crackers. Top with chocolate supreme frosting that has been melted in microwave.

title: abalone saute
directions: Take the steak and flour it.
Season the beaten egg. Place the steak in the egg (a pie plate serves well for this).
Use a good saute pan.
Bring the oil to a slight smoke point.
Spread the steak and egg mixture and turn fast.
Cook for no more than 4 seconds a side.
Serve immediately.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla with electric mixer until blended.
Add eggs; mix until blended.
Pour into crust.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: bloody mary(serves 8)
directions: Mix all ingredients. Serve cold over ice.

title: swiss steak
directions: Mix flour, salt and pepper. Roll steak in flour and pound the flour into both sides of steak.
In a Dutch oven, heat Crisco. Brown steaks on both sides.
Add vegetables, cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours.

title: water chestnuts-bacon hors d'oeuvres
directions: Drain the water chestnuts.
Wrap each chestnut with 1/2 slice of bacon and secure with toothpick.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until done.
Drain fat.
Mix up sauce and pour over hors d'oeuvres.
Heat until warm.

title: peach pie
directions: Bake pie shell and cool. Drain peaches and reserve juice.
Mix the cream cheese, sugar and peach juice together.
Put in cooled pie shell.
Lay sliced peaches on top of mixture.
Put Cool Whip on top of peaches.
Put in refrigerator until cold.

title: corned beef dish
directions: Arrange bread cubes in a greased 9 x 13-inch dish.
Shred a corned beef layer over the bread.
Sprinkle with cheese.

title: microwave eggplant parmesan
directions: Pierce skin on eggplant several times.
Place eggplant on paper towel on glass oven tray.
Cook at High 6 to 7 minutes, or until eggplant is almost tender; roll over twice.
Let cool.
Peel, if desired, and cut into 1/2 inch slices.
Meanwhile, combine bread, Parmesan cheese and butter.
In 8-inch square dish, alternately layer spaghetti sauce, eggplant, crumb mixture and Mozzarella cheese.
Cover with wax paper.
Cool at High 15 to 17 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Let stand, covered, 5 minutes before serving.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Cream oil and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Mix flour, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Add to the oil, sugar and eggs a small amount at a time.
Add vanilla.
Stir in apples and nuts.
Spread in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan and bake for 40 to 60 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean.
Immediately poke holes in cake and pour the icing over it.

title: applesauce nut bread
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a large bowl; beat at medium speed of mixer for 1 minute.
Set aside.
Combine flour, soda, baking powder, 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon, salt and nutmeg.
Add to applesauce mixture.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in pecans and vanilla.
Spoon batter into a greased and floured 5 x 9 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Combine remaining pecans, brown sugar and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon.
Sprinkle over batter and bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Remove from oven and cover loosely with foil; return to oven for 40 minutes.
Uncover and let cool 10 minutes in pan, then remove.

title: hot pineapple salad
directions: Layer pineapple, cream cheese and marshmallows.
Make sauce of reserved juice, egg, sugar and flour.
Pour over layers.
Top with cheese.
Microwave 6 to 8 minutes on High or heat in oven at 450° for 10 minutes.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease square baking dish.
Arrange chilies in single layer.
Sprinkle with tomatoes and cheese.
Beat remaining ingredients until smooth.
Pour over top.
Bake for about 40 minutes.

title: custard pie
directions: Beat eggs well, then add milk; beat again.
Add 1/2 cup sugar; beat again.
Add vanilla.
Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Sprinkle cinnamon or nutmeg on top; bake at 400° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
Add 1 cup crushed cornflakes.
Mix well.
Pour into buttered casserole dish.
Mix remaining cornflakes with melted butter and sprinkle on top of casserole. Bake at 300° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: orange sherbet salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O; chill slightly, then fold in sherbet and fruits.
Pour into desired mold and refrigerate until firm.

title: meringue
directions: Beat egg whites, cornstarch and cream of tartar until real, real stiff.
Add sugar a little at a time and beat.
Add marshmallow cream and vanilla.
Beat real good.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Place ground beef in a greased casserole dish.
Add layer of celery, onion and cheese.
Mix soups and Worcestershire sauce with 1/2 soup can of water.
Pour soup mixture over all.
Top with a layer of Tater Tots.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: curried chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: hamburger-celery casserole
directions: Cook noodles until almost done.
Brown hamburger slightly with onion; drain fat.
Cook celery in water.
Mix all with cans of soup (including celery water).
Salt and pepper.
Bake in casserole dish at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Beat all ingredients 5 minutes.
Grease and flour a Bundt pan. Put some pecans on bottom of pan.
Pour batter into pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.
Let cool 10 to 15 minutes.
Invert and turn out of pan and finish cooling on wire rack.

title: chocolate ice cream
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into a gallon freezer. Freeze and serve.

title: chicken surprise
directions: Melt oleo; add onions and saute lightly.
Add soup and cheese. Cook until cheese is melted.
Add olives and chicken.
Mix with spaghetti and pour into 3-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
During the last 15 minutes of cooking, sprinkle top with noodles.
Freezes well.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: philadelphia cream cheese mints
directions: Mash cream cheese; add coloring and extract.
Mix in sugar. First with fork, then knead with hands.
Roll into balls the size of a marble; roll in granulated sugar.
Press firmly into mold. Unmold at once on waxed paper to dry.
Makes 25 roses and 25 leaves.

title: mexican one dish meal
directions: Brown
ground
beef and onions.
Drain.
Combine ground chuck, onion,
beans, corn, peas, sauce and pepper.
Pour into large baking
dish or pan.
Cover with grated cheese.
Prepare muffin mix
as directed on box.
Spread over mixture.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: kids can do - edible necklace
directions: You will need 1 needle and 1 (18-inch) piece of string.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and beat for 2 minutes.
Pour into greased pans.
(Bake two loaf pans, 350° for 1 hour, 1 sheet cake pan 350° for 35 minutes, 1 large Bundt, 50 minutes.)

title: peanut butter cookies(diabetic recipe)
directions: Cream together the margarine, peanut butter and sugar replacements.
Add egg, water and vanilla, beating until fluffy. Combine flour, baking soda and baking powder together; blend into creamed mixture.
Chill thoroughly, at least 2 hours or overnight. Drop by teaspoons onto lightly greased cookie sheets, 2 to 3 inches apart.
Press flat with a floured bottom of a small glass. Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream butter with sugar and add peanut butter.
Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: orange chess pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake 15 minutes at 300°, then 30 minutes at 350°.

title: texas hash for 2
directions: Heat oven to 350° (moderate oven).
Brown onions and green pepper in hot oil until yellow.
Add ground beef and fry until mixture falls apart.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased 1-quart baking dish.
Cover and bake 1 hour, removing cover last 15 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: mushroom casserole
directions: Saute coarsely sliced mushrooms in butter.
Butter 3 slices bread, cut into 1-inch cubes and put in casserole dish.
Combine mushrooms with onion, mayonnaise, salt, celery, green pepper and pepper.
Put it on bread squares.
Cut 3 more slices of buttered bread the same way.
Put them in and over it, pour the eggs, slightly beaten with the milk.
Refrigerate for at least 1 hour or overnight.
Spoon a can of undiluted mushroom soup over it; put 2 more slices of bread, diced smaller.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: spinach even kids will have(serves 4)
directions: In a skillet, brown onions and bacon until cooked.
Then add vinegar and water and bring to a boil.
Add salt and pepper and 1/2 teaspoon of sugar, then taste.
If still sour, add 1/2 teaspoon of sugar until a mild flavor is achieved (not sweet or sour).
Then to this, add the fresh or frozen spinach and cook until done or heated through.
Serves 4.

title: pull-apart parmesan bundt bread
directions: Thaw bread dough.
Slice each loaf into 12 equal pieces. Blend cheese and onion soup mix together.
Dip each bread slice into melted margarine, then the cheese-soup mixture.
Place dipped pieces of dough side by side in a greased 12-cup Bundt pan.
Cover and let rise in a warm draft-free area until doubled in size. Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until golden brown and the loaf sounds hollow when tapped.
Remove immediately from the pan and cool on wire rack.
Serve while warm.

title: poppy chicken
directions: Layer boiled and deboned chicken in bottom of small casserole dish.
Mix and pour soup; add sour cream over chicken.
Mix margarine, crackers and poppy seed; sprinkle over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: rawleigh's 5 flavor pound cake
directions: Cream together butter, shortening and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs which have been beaten until a lemon color. Sift flour, baking powder and salt, then add to creamed mixture, alternating with milk.
Stir in flavorings.
Then spoon or pour into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.
(Stoves may vary in baking time.)

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Dot a pie tin or 8-inch square pan with butter.
Pour in fresh or thawed fruit (apples, peaches, etc., or whatever you choose). Pour batter over fruit.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Do in layers the lettuce, cauliflower, onion and bacon bits in a bowl.
Then spread salad dressing over this.
Sprinkle cheese over next.
Then sprinkle 1/4 cup sugar over last.
Let sit in refrigerator for 12 to 24 hours and mix.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Melt oleo and break pretzels in dish.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Whip the Dream Whip; mix with cream cheese and sugar. Pour cream cheese mixture over pretzels.
Cover pretzels completely.
Dissolve jello in boiling liquid.
Add pineapple and strawberries; cool slightly.
Pour over cream cheese. Refrigerate.

title: hamburger and rice casserole
directions: Combine ingredients.
Pour into greased casserole dish. Cover and bake for 2 hours at 325°F.
May be sprinkled with cheese 10 min. before removing from oven.

title: tortilla wrap
directions: Place tortilla on flat surface.
Spread cream cheese evenly and place onion blade in center.
Roll into a wrap and place a toothpick through the center to hold in place.

title: cole slaw
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate overnight.
Will keep 3 weeks in refrigerator.

title: pumpkin soup
directions: Melt butter in soup kettle.
Saute onion until golden.
Stir in pumpkin, stock, thyme and bay leaf.
Cook over low heat 15 minutes, stirring occasionally, until mixture is smooth.
Remove from heat and cool.
Stir in cream and sherry and heat thoroughly. Remove bay leaf.
Garnish with chopped parsley or chives.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: chocolate zucchini bars
directions: In large bowl, combine margarine, oil and sugar.
Mix well. Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Stir in sour cream and zucchini.
Mix well.
Sift together flour, cocoa, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon and cloves.
Add to zucchini mixture.
Sprinkle chips over batter in pan.
Bake in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes, or until done.
Makes 2 dozen bars.

title: simple fruit cobbler
directions: Melt butter in casserole dish and set aside.
Mix flour, sugar and milk; beat well.
Pour over butter.
Do not stir.
Pour heated fruit over flour mixture.
Bake at 375° until brown, approximately 30 minutes.

title: bread pudding
directions: Mix eggs, cinnamon, vanilla and sugar with 1 cup milk.
Warm 2 cups milk and butter in a pot.
Add other ingredients.
Add raisins.
Slowly add remaining cup of milk.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: lazy day stew
directions: Do not brown meat.
Cut potatoes, carrots, onion and celery in chunks and lay on top of meat.
Mix tomato sauce, water and sugar. Pour over meat and vegetables.
Add salt and pepper and scatter tapioca on top.
Seal with foil.
Cook in oven for two hours at 325°.
Do not peek.

title: jello chocolate pie
directions: Beat chocolate pudding mix with milk for 2 minutes. Pour into pie crust. Cover and put in refrigerator for 1 hour.

title: prune nut cake
directions: Mix sugar and spices.
Add oil, eggs and prunes.
Add flour, a small amount at a time, until all is added.
Mix in nuts.
Pour into a well-greased tube pan.
Start in cold oven set at 300°. Bake for 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: hush puppies
directions: Sift the dry ingredients together and add the egg, milk and water.
Stir in the chopped onion.
Mold into desired shapes and fry in oil until well done.

title: b.b.q. brisket
directions: Put brisket in roaster.
Pour approx 3 inches water in pan. Add 1/3 can beer. (drink the rest)
Add sliced onion, garlic, salt and pepper.
Bake 275 degrees 3 - 4 hours until fork tender. Remove from oven.
Pour off 1/2 water.
Transfer meat to plastic container.
Add your favorite BBQ sauce to marinate.
Refrigerate overnight.
Next day slice thin.
Add more sauce and cover.
Bake at 350 degrees 30 minutes.
Remove cover and bake an additional 30 minutes.

title: hungry jack casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except biscuits together and put in casserole.
Cut biscuits in half and place on top of meat mixture. Bake in 375° oven for 25 to 30 minutes or until biscuits are done.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat well.
Drain off fat.
Add other ingredients tomatoes, tomato sauce, garlic and spaghetti sauce mix.
Cook 8 ounce package lasagna noodles.
In pan put 1 layer noodles, 1/3 sauce, layer cottage cheese and Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat again twice.
End with layer sauce.
Sprinkle Parmesan on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let set 15 minutes.
Serve.

title: chunk sweet pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers in cold water and slice 1/2 to 3/4 inch thick. Soak for 3 days in salt brine strong enough to hold an egg (pickling salt and 1 gallon water).
Pour off salt water, then soak for 3 days in clear water, changing water every day.
Remove from water; put in kettle and add vinegar, alum and enough hot water to cover.
Simmer for 1 hour; gently stir several times.
Drain.

title: strawberry-pineapple chiffon pie
directions: Mix together in saucepan, eggs, sugar and crushed pineapple. Cook until thick; remove from heat.
Stir in 1 small package strawberry jello.
Place mixture in refrigerator to cool.
Remove the can of evaporated milk from freezer.
It should have been there at least 1 hour.
Pour milk into bowl and beat until stiff.
Fold into the cooked mixture.
Pour into 2 (9-inch) baked pie crusts and place in refrigerator until set (about 30 minutes).

title: no-bake clark bar cookies
directions: Combine graham crackers, peanut butter, powdered sugar and margarine.
Squeeze dough into balls.
Melt chocolate and wax on top of double boiler. Dip each ball into chocolate and place on wax paper until set.
Makes about 6 dozen.

title: fresh strawberry pie(sugar-free recipe)
directions: Crush crackers and add margarine, sugar substitute and cinnamon.
Press into pie pan or plate.
Bake at 350° for 5 to 7 minutes.
Cool

title: apple cake
directions: Fill casserole dish with pie filling, water, 1 cup sugar and cut 1/2 stick butter up evenly into mixture.
Pour 3/4 cake mix over mixture.
Pour remaining sugar and evenly distribute butter over cake mix.
Bake at 350 degrees until brown.

title: banana refresher
directions: Place drink mix, 1 cup of the water and bananas in blender; cover.
Blend on high speed until smooth.
Pour into large plastic or glass pitcher.
Stir in remaining 4 cups of water and ice. Serve at once or refrigerate and stir before serving.

title: sweet potato pecan pie
directions: Cream butter with brown sugar.
Beat in eggs, one at a time; blend in corn syrup, vanilla and mashed sweet potatoes.
Stir in pecans and turn into unbaked pie shell.
Bake in 400° oven for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 30 minutes longer, until filling is set and pastry browned.
Cool.
Serve with whipped cream, more pecans or ice cream.
Serves 8.

title: pork chops and sauerkraut
directions: Place sauerkraut in casserole.
Season pork chops.
Place chops over kraut.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 hour.
Bake, uncovered, for 20 minutes longer or until pork chops are brown.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles.
Combine tuna, mayonnaise, celery, onions, green pepper, pimento, and salt.
Blend cream of celery soup with milk and add to combined ingredients and heat.
Add shredded cheese; stir until melted.
Add noodles.
Pour into greased casserole bowl. Bake uncovered at 425° for 20 minutes.

title: pina colada fruit dip
directions: Combine all ingredients together.
Beat for 30 seconds. Refrigerate several hours or overnight to blend flavors.
Serve with fresh fruit.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: easy cheesy lasagna
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Brown Italian sausage (or ground beef), onions and garlic.
Drain.
Return meat mixture to pan and stir in spaghetti sauce and water.

In a 13 x 9-inch baking dish, layer 1/3 of sauce mixture, half the uncooked noodles, half the combined Ricotta or cottage cheese and parsley and 1/2 of Mozzarella cheese. Repeat layers, ending with sauce mixture.
Cover with foil.
Bake 1 hour, uncover and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Let stand 10 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook chopped broccoli for 5 minutes.
Drain.
Add and mix with broccoli all the listed ingredients.
Cover with Pepperidge Farm herb dressing/stuffing.
Dot with butter.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: lemon garlic sprouts
directions: In a skillet, saute Brussels sprouts and onion in butter for 5 minutes.
Add garlic, lemon juice and lemon peel, salt (if desired) and pepper; saute for 1 minute.
Reduce heat to medium.
Cook and stir for 5 to 6 minutes or until sprouts are tender.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: cajun burritos
directions: Mix the hamburger, chorizo, turkey, cheese and beans into a large mixing bowl.
Spread a large spoonful of the mix onto each of the tortillas.
Roll and bake at 375° for fifteen minutes or until the tortillas begin to brown.

title: squash fritters
directions: Mix together and drop by rounded tablespoon into greased hot skillet.
Brown on both sides.
Serve hot.

title: meat loaf
directions: In large bowl combine hamburger, onion, celery, green pepper, cracker crumbs, tomato soup, 1/2 cup ketchup, eggs, salt, pepper, oregano and garlic.
Bake at 375° for 1 1/2 hours.
One half hour before removing from oven, spread remaining ketchup over top of loaf.

title: taco salad(low-fat)
directions: Mix all the ingredients except sour cream after cooled.
Dollop sour cream on top when ready to serve.

title: cherry yum yum
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs, 1 cup sugar and margarine.
Mix well and set aside.

title: asian chicken
directions: Heat oil in large skillet and brown chicken on all sides, adding garlic and peppers toward the end. Add remaining ingredients and cook over medium-high heat until chicken is done and sauce has reduced, about 30 to 40 minutes. Serve with rice or Chinese noodles. Garnish with green onions.

title: party dip
directions: Blend cream cheese and milk in bowl.
Finely chop dried beef. Add beef, green pepper, onion, garlic salt and pepper.
Mix well. Stir in sour cream.
Spread evenly in 8-inch pie plate or other pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes.
Garnish with chopped nuts and serve warm with crackers.

title: red stew
directions: Cut meat in bite size pieces.
Brown in 1 tablespoon of oil. Course chop vegetables.
When meat is browned, drain off excess oil.
Add celery, bell pepper, tomato paste and water.
Simmer until thickened.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Serve over rice. Serves 4.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook together water, sugar, salt and cornstarch, stirring until thick and clear.
Remove from heat.
Add jello and 2 to 3 drops of red food coloring. Cool.
Pour over 1 quart strawberries in pie shell.
Refrigerate.
Can top with Cool Whip.

title: cheesy pepper burgers
directions: Grate cheese and finely chop onion.
In medium bowl, combine beef, onion, sauce, 1/4 teaspoon pepper and salt and mix gently. Divide into 4 equal portions.
Flatten into patty and press 1/4 of cheese into center.
Pull sides of patty up and over cheese to enclose it.
Make sure cheese does not poke out.
Sprinkle with rest of pepper, pressing into meat.

title: layered taco dip
directions: Layer 1:
Cook and drain hamburger.
Add taco seasoning and taco sauce.
Spread on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread refried beans over hamburger.

title: barbecued trout
directions: Brush trout inside and out with lemon juice. Combine the lemon juice with the remaining ingredients. Place fish in a shallow glass dish.
Pour marinade over fish and let stand for 1 hour. Place fish in well-greased hinged wire basket.
Reserve marinade. Grill over flame at medium setting for 12 to 15 minutes, turning often and brushing frequently with the marinade.

title: beef brisket
directions: Place brisket in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix all other ingredients and pour over.
Seal with foil and bake for 3 hours at 325°. Slice thin when cool and reheat.
Great with mashed potatoes, noodles or on hard rolls as sandwiches.

title: ham baked with tomatoes and cheese
directions: Place ham in a baking dish.
Cover with tomatoes.
Cover tomatoes with cheese.
Cover the dish.
Bake at 350° until ham is tender, about 30 minutes.
Uncover it for the last 10 minutes of cooking.

title: make ahead mashed potatoes
directions: Mix altogether and place in a buttered casserole dish (2-quart or larger).
Refrigerate overnight.
Before putting in oven, brush with melted butter or dot with butter.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers and slice very thin.
Chop onions and peppers. Combine with salt and let stand 3 hours.
Drain.
Combine remaining ingredients in large kettle; bring to a boil.
Add cucumbers and heat through, but do not boil.
Pack in sterilized hot jars while still hot.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Skin and bone the chicken; tear into bite-size pieces.
Mix together the soup, sour cream and chicken pieces.
Set aside. Crush the crackers.
Melt the oleo and add to the crackers.
Stir in the poppy seed.
Place half of the cracker mixture in the bottom of a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour the chicken mixture on top of crackers.
Top with the remaining crumb mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes until bubbly.
May be frozen until baked.
Serves 6.

title: autumn surprise cake
directions: Mix apples (Lodi or early Harvest work best!) with sugar and let stand until juice forms.
Add sifted flour, salt and soda to apple mixture.
Add remaining ingredients and mix thoroughly. Bake in 8 x 8-inch pan for 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.
Ice cake while hot with powdered sugar.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Boil shrimp in water, seasoned with Tony Chachare seasoning, use 1/2 can tomato sauce for color.
Drain and refrigerate to chill.

title: apple cake
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and oil together.
Mix together vanilla, cinnamon, flour, soda and salt.
Combine remaining ingredients. Bake in 9 x 13 pan for 45 minutes at 350°.
Dust with 4xxxx sugar when cool.
Very moist.

title: corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 435°.
Mix dry ingredients together.
Add buttermilk and mix well.
Add egg and stir.
Add hot grease; stir and pour into hot skillet where grease was heated.
Bake for 20 minutes and test with fork.
(Uncooked mixture should be thick; decrease buttermilk, if necessary.)

title: cheezy rye bread dip
directions: Mix all with blender and serve cold.
Spread on small deli rye.

title: chicken fettuccine
directions: Saute first 4 ingredients in 2 tablespoons butter in a large skillet over medium heat until vegetables are tender.
Add chicken and cook until thoroughly heated.
Set aside and keep warm.
Cook fettucine; drain and place in a large bowl.
Combine whipping cream and 1/2 cup butter in a small saucepan; cook over low heat until butter melts.
Stir in Parmesan cheese, chopped parsley and white pepper.
Pour whipping cream mixture over hot fettuccine; add chicken mixture.
Toss until fettuccine is thoroughly coated. Serves 6 to 8.

title: wes webb's bean sprouts
directions: Saute onion and meat; add 1 cup of water to start and enough soy sauce to give desired taste.
Add bean sprouts, cooking over medium heat.
Season to taste.
Cook to desired doneness.
Keeps well overnight.

title: date nut bread
directions: Cut up dates, add baking soda and over that pour boiling water.
Stir and set aside to cool.

title: gozabki(stuffed cabbage)
directions: Steam cabbage in water to which has been added a little vinegar and sugar.
Steam until you can easily take leaves from head. Save the water and steam or cook rice in this water.
Mix meat, onion, seasonings and rice together.
In each cabbage leaf, place a small amount of meat mixture and roll up, tucking ends in securely.
Use toothpicks to hold.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix tomato sauce, lemon juice and brown sugar together.
Pour over cabbage rolls. Cover with aluminum foil.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
(You may cook on stove top instead, if desired.)
Serves 6 to 8.

title: butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream the butter and sugar.
Mix in egg, slightly beaten.
Sift flour and salt and combine with egg mixture.
Add vanilla and mix until batter is smooth.
Drop batter by teaspoonfuls onto a greased and floured baking sheet, leaving some space between cookies. Bake 10 to 15 minutes or until edges of cookies turn brown.
Makes about 2 dozen.

title: banana cream pie with graham cracker crust
directions: Roll crackers until crumbs are fine. Add sugar and mix well, then add Crisco.
Line grease pie plate with crumbs.
Save some crumbs for top.
Make Cream Filling and pour over crumbs. Top with Meringue and sprinkle remainder of crumbs.
Bake in a 325° oven for 15 minutes.

title: enchiladas, mexican style
directions: Heat tortillas in hot fat until softened and golden brown in color.
Heat the chili sauce.
Dip hot tortillas in hot chili sauce, remove to plate; sprinkle with cheese and finely chopped onion.
Serve in stacks of 3, topped with a fried egg and 2 to 3 tablespoons of chili sauce.

title: beer battered onion rings
directions: Preheat oven to 400.

title: potatoes au gratin
directions: Combine ingredients.
Bake, covered, for 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.
Remove cover and bake 10 to 15 more minutes.

title: creole red beans and rice
directions: Sort and wash beans.
Place beans in a large Dutch oven; cover with water.
Add ham bone, onion, celery and bay leaf.
Cover; bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 2 hours or until beans are tender, stirring occasionally.
Add salt and hot sauce to taste. Serve over hot cooked rice and smoked sausage links.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: gooseberry pie
directions: Heat gooseberries and water to boiling. Mix and moisten remaining ingredients. Stir into the hot fruit and cook until thickened. Pour into 10-inch pastry-lined pan. Cover with top crust. Bake in 400° oven for 10 minutes and continue for 35 to 40 minutes at 350° until crust is lightly browned.

title: spinach souffle
directions: Combine soup, Cheddar cheese and nutmeg in saucepan.
Heat slowly until cheese melts.
Beat egg yolks until thick and lemon colored; gradually stir into soup mixture.
Cook spinach according to package and drain well.
Add to soup mixture.
Beat egg whites until stiff in a large bowl.
Fold in soup mixture.

title: mary todd lincoln cake
directions: Cream sugar, butter and vanilla; sift together cake flour and baking powder in 3 additions.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with milk.
Stir in almonds.
Gently fold in egg whites.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 1 1/2-inch round pans.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Cool for 10 minutes before removing from pans. Cool completely before frosting.

title: butterfinger cake
directions: Follow directions on box to cook cake.
Let cool.
Punch holes in cake with fork.
Pour caramel over cake.
Crush 2 candy bars and sprinkle over cake.
Spread whole bowl of Cool Whip on cake. Crush the other 4 candy bars and sprinkle over the Cool Whip.
Put in refrigerator until about an hour before you want to serve it. Set out so caramel and Cool Whip will warm slightly.

title: beef dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Great on party rye.

title: apple pie
directions: Butter pan; put in apples. Add cinnamon and 3/4 cup sugar. Mix and cover with foil. Bake 20 minutes; remove foil.
Cream all topping ingredients. It will be thick. Spread over apples and return to oven without foil. Bake for 20 minutes. Better cold.

title: crabbies
directions: Allow cheese and margarine to soften.
Mix with seasonings and add crab.
Spread on English muffins.
Cut each muffin half into eighths before baking or leave whole if serving for a meal.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
(These can be frozen before baking and are still delicious!)

title: meat balls
directions: Mix all ingredients and roll into balls.
Place in baking dish.
Combine the sauce ingredients and pour over meat balls.

title: "old virginia wassail"
directions: Combine ingredients and bring to a simmer, 5 minutes.
Strain and serve hot.
You can tie your spices in a bag.
Saves straining.

title: bailey's irish cream
directions: Blend each ingredient as you add another.
Keeps well in refrigerator.
Serve over crushed ice.
Makes a nice substitute for dessert after a big dinner.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Drain pineapple and cottage cheese well.
Put dry Jell-O over cottage cheese and mix in the rest of ingredients.
Chill and serve.

title: almond bark treats
directions: Sandwich two Ritz crackers together with a generous amount of peanut butter.
Using tongs, dip crackers into melted almond bark. Place on wax paper to harden.
Refrigerate 1/2 hour or place briefly in freezer to harden more quickly.

title: almond bark cookies
directions: Heat almond bark candy in slow oven at 200°, just long enough for soft to touch.
Mix all dry ingredients together and pour candy coating over dry ingredients.

title: pot pie
directions: *We like chicken and beef, also good with that leftover Thanksgiving turkey.

title: no bake cheese cake
directions: Mix sugar, crackers and melted butter.
Press in a 13 x 9-inch pan and chill.
(You can also use two pie shells, prepackaged.)

title: shrimp and rice
directions: Fry rice, onion, garlic and celery in hot cooking oil.
Add tomatoes, seasoning, shrimp, Tabasco sauce and water.
Cover tightly and cook slowly for about 50 minutes or until rice is soft; stir occasionally.
Serve on large dish, garnished with tomatoes and green peppers.

title: once sour-now sweet pickles
directions: Pour off liquid and remove pickles from jar.
Slice pickles and put back into jar, layering alternately with sugar.
Slice garlic and add it and the celery seed as you put pickles back into jar. Pack down each layer as you go.
Put top of jar and turn it over several times during next day until sugar is dissolved.

title: beef noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles in boiling salted water; drain and rinse.
Brown meat in fat; add onions, pepper and celery.
Alternate layers of noodles and meat mixture in greased casserole dish.
Mix Worcestershire sauce into soup and pour over layers in casserole. Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: salsa
directions: Chop well drained tomatoes with wire whisk.
Add rest of ingredients and mix well.
Add chopped jalapeno peppers to your taste.
Refrigerate until ready to use.
Salsa tastes best after two or three days.
Yield:
Approximately 2 cups.

title: cherry glaze
directions: Put graham cracker crust in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix Cool Whip, sour cream and sugar.
Pour into crust.
Let stand 15 minutes. Cover with cherry pie filling and chill.

title: sweet pepper steak
directions: Cut steak into 2 in. squares. Cut onion into bite size pieces. Remove the seeds from the peppers and cut into 1 in. squares. Pour cooking oil into a large frying pan and heat over medium heat. Add steak and cook on both sides until well done. Add remaining ingredients. Turn up the heat slightly and cook for 3 minutes. Serve with rice.

title: holiday cranberry cake
directions: Blend cake mix, cream cheese and milk; beat 2 minutes.
Add eggs; beat 2 minutes.
Combine cranberries, walnuts, sugar and mace.
Fold into cake batter.
Pour into well-greased and floured 10-inch tube or Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool 5 minutes.
Remove from pan and dust with confectioners sugar.

title: oyster dressing
directions: Remove black portion of oyster and discard.
Mix all ingredients together and stuff bird.
Roast bird as usual.

title: easy cheese ball
directions: Add together everything, except crackers, and set aside 1/2 of the chopped meat.
Shape into a ball and add the chopped meat all over the ball.
Place on a dish and add the crackers surrounding the cheese ball.

title: leftover chicken vegetable soup
directions: In a large kettle, combine cabbage, peas, corn, carrots, celery, onion, parsley, chicken broth, chicken and enough water to almost cover them.
Bring to a boil and simmer until veggies are tender.
Add macaroni and cook until done.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: cottage cheese fruit salad
directions: Sprinkle dry Jell-O over cottage cheese and mix.
Fold in remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: homemade sloppy joes
directions: Brown ground beef in oil.
Pour in 1 bottle chili sauce and 1 tablespoon Worcestershire sauce.
Add pinch of salt and 1 1/2 teaspoons sugar.
Stir.
Add 1/2 cup water.
Stir.
Cook slow for 15 minutes.
Serve on roll.

title: mexican wedding cake
directions: In large bowl, mix all ingredients, adding walnuts last.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 49 minutes in a 9 x 11 x 2-inch floured and greased pan.

title: hot fruit compote
directions: Drain fruit and put in casserole.
Combine brown sugar and curry powder.
Sprinkle over top of fruit.	Dot with butter. Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: easy tuna casserole
directions: Place large casserole dish on burner.
Heat water to boiling; add salt and oil.
Add dry macaroni.
Cook over medium heat until macaroni is firm but tender.
Drain macaroni.
Add other ingredients except crumbs.
Stir until well blended.
Turn into large greased casserole dish.
Cover with crumbs.
Bake in medium oven for 30 to 45 minutes.
Cool slightly before serving.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: turkey tetrazzini
directions: Cook spaghetti; drain.
Place in greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch dish. In 2-quart casserole, place butter, mushrooms, onion and lemon juice.
Cook 2 to 3 minutes.
Stir in flour, paprika and nutmeg until smooth.
Cook 1 minute.
Stir in gradually in broth.
Cook 6 to 8 minutes, stirring after 3 minutes, until thickened.
Mix in half and half and turkey.
Cook 7 to 9 minutes.
Pour over spaghetti.
Sprinkle with cheese and paprika.
Cook 7 to 9 minutes until hot.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat together eggs and sugar.
Add vegetable oil and vanilla. Sift dry ingredients together.
Add to egg mixture.
Add zucchini. Pour into 1 large greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: lemon cheese cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Sift flour and baking powder.
Add flour mixture alternately with milk to the butter and sugar. Beat good.
Add vanilla and fold in egg whites but do not beat. Makes 5 layers.

title: oven brisket
directions: Day 1:
Sprinkle brisket with 1/3 bottle liquid smoke and generous amounts of sliced celery, onion and garlic.
Wrap tightly with foil and refrigerate overnight.

title: carrot cake
directions: Blend together sugar and oil.
Add eggs and mix well.
Combine flour, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
Gradually add to egg mixture, mixing until blended.
Stir in carrots and walnuts.

title: country-style pancakes
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Beat egg, add milk and blend into flour mixture.
Drop batter on hot griddle.
Turn pancakes when bubbles appear.
Makes 16 (4-inch) pancakes.

title: german potato salad
directions: Mix vinegar, sugar, salt, pepper and onions; let stand.
Cook potatoes in peelings.
When done, cool slightly; peel and slice. Cook bacon until crisp; drain.
Turn heat down under bacon drippings.
Add cornstarch to vinegar mixture.
Stir well and add to bacon drippings.
Stir until thick and transparent.
If too thick, add more water.
Add bacon crumbs to sauce.
Pour hot sauce over sliced, peeled potatoes (may add sweet pickle vinegar as part of vinegar).

title: apple bars
directions: Combine the 2 cups flour, 1/2 cup sugar, baking powder and salt. Cut in butter until crumbs are size of peas. Stir in egg yolks. Press half in 9 X 13 pan. Add apple mixture. Add remaining crumb mixture on top. Brush lightly with egg white. Bake 350° for 40 minutes. Drizzle with powdered sugar icing, if desired.

title: diabetic sugarless cookies
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and boil for 3 minutes.
Cool.
Add flour, soda and vanilla.
Add nuts last.
Mix well and chill. Drop by spoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.
Keep refrigerated in tight container.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: frozen fruit punch
directions: Boil and cool the sugar and water mixture. Add the lemonade, orange juice and pineapple juice.
(If using frozen juice, add water to its mixture.)
Add crushed bananas, strawberries and pineapple.
Stir and freeze in grip-lock Baggies. Serve in punch bowl.
Pour 7-Up or ginger ale over frozen punch and chop to make slushy.
Add other bags of frozen punch as needed.

title: beef and gravy
directions: Combine all ingredients with the stewing beef and shake in a bag.
Then brown meat on all sides.
Add 2 cups of water, cook slow for 2 hours or until meat is tender.

title: chicken perliou
directions: Boil chicken in pot of water until done.
Brown sausage in pan.
Debone chicken.
Place 2 cups rice in big pot; add 4 cups chicken broth from pot that chicken was boiled in.
Add chicken, sausage, salt and pepper.
Bring to boil, then cut down on low and let rice cook until done.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream shortening and brown sugar.
Add eggs.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to creamed mixture.
Add nuts or raisins.
Pour into loaf pan that has been greased and floured. Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: brisket
directions: Sear meat on all sides.
Place onion soup and water in bottom of roaster, then place meat in pan and sprinkle with spices. Cover and cook for 3 to 4 hours at 350°.
The meat will make its own gravy.

title: holiday cheese balls
directions: Mix all ingredients, but 1 cup of pecans, together.
Work into a ball, then roll in the other 1 cup of pecans. Chill for several hours or overnight.
Serve with crackers.

title: easy meat loaf
directions: Mix ingredients and add salt and pepper to taste.
Pour in pyrex dish and cover top with tomato catsup.
Bake at 400° for 45 min. to 1 hr.

title: peanut butter fingers
directions: Cut crust from frozen bread.
Cut each slice into 6 finger size pieces.
Place bread on cookie sheet.
Remove crust from bread and allow to dry out slowly in 225° oven for 30 minutes.

title: holiday nuggets
directions: Mix butter and sugar.
Flour nuts and mix together.
Roll in small balls.
Beat at 425° for about 15 minutes.
Roll in xxxx sugar while hot.

title: hawaii toast(hot sandwich)
directions: Toast the Texas toast until lightly brown.
Preheat oven to 400°.
On a jelly roll pan or cookie sheet, lay out your slices of toast.
Next, place a slice of ham on each toast, then place a slice of pineapple on each.
Top off with a slice of Swiss cheese on each.
Place in oven for 15 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: mombo congo squares
directions: Mix together and spread in 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: mama's tortillas
directions: Combine dry ingredients in a medium-size mixing bowl and cut in shortening.
Make a well in center of ingredients.
Add water, a small amount at a time; work mixture into a dough.
Knead dough until smooth, cover and set aside for 10 minutes.
Form dough into balls the size of an egg.
Roll each ball of dough into a circle, 6 inches in diameter.
Heat a griddle or skillet on medium-high heat.
Place each tortilla on griddle and cook for approximately 1 minute on each side.
(Tortilla should be lightly speckled.)

title: carrot walnut bread
directions: Sift together flour, baking soda, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt. Set aside.
Combine sugar, oil and eggs in mixing bowl.
Beat with electric mixer.
Add dry ingredients, stirring until moistened. Stir in carrots and walnuts.
Pour batter into greased loaf pan. Bake 55 minutes at 350°.

title: ms. ann fryman's deer patties and gravy
directions: Make
patties
with
ground deer
meat.
Add
salt
and flour; fry in frying pan until
brown.
Make
flour
and
milk gravy and put patties into gravy and serve while hot.
You can cook as many patties and as much gravy as needed, depending on the number of people you plan to	serve
and
how
hungry they are.

title: pecan candy
directions: Beat
egg white until stiff.
Add brown sugar and salt. Coat pecan halves and drop onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 275° approximately
minutes.
If
large
pecan halves are used, drop
one
at
a time on the sheet.
If small halves are used, drop 2 or 3 in a cluster.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in a casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together including the oats.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: apple mix-in-the-pan cake
directions: Place chopped apple in an ungreased, 8-inch, square baking pan.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Combine flour, cinnamon, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Add to apples; toss gently.
Combine coffee, oil, egg and vanilla; stir well. Add to apple mixture in pan.
Stir gently until well blended. Stir in nuts.

title: mueller's classic lasagne no. 138
directions: In large pan, lightly brown beef and onion in oil.
Add tomatoes (put through blender), paste, water, parsley, salt, sugar, garlic powder, pepper and oregano.
Simmer, uncovered, for 30 minutes.
Cook lasagne noodles as directed on box; drain.
In a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan, spread 1 cup sauce.
Alternate layers of lasagne, sauce, Ricotta, Mozzarella and Parmesan cheeses.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Yields 8 servings.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Peel and slice cucumbers into dish.
Salt each layer.
Place in refrigerator for 4 to 6 hours.
Take out and pour off juice. Squeeze by hand remaining juice from cucumbers.
Place squeezed and drained cucumbers in serving bowl.
Add sour cream and stir. Add half and half and stir.
Add vinegar to taste.
Let set 30 minutes to thicken.
Top with paprika and serve.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions; drain and put in 2 1/2-quart dish.
Cover broccoli with cubed chicken.
Add water chestnuts after draining them.
Then mix cream of chicken soup and mayonnaise and add on top of water chestnuts.
Add cheese on top of chicken soup and mayonnaise mixture.
Crush Ritz crackers into 1 stick margarine and put on top of casserole.
Cook for 30 to 45 minutes in oven at 375°.

title: cheese freeze
directions: Whip softened gelatin in cold water.
Heat together egg yolk, flour, 1/4 cup sugar and scalded milk. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until custard thickens.
Add gelatin and stir. Cool. Add cheese, lemon flavoring, vanilla and whipped cream. Add 1/2 cup sugar to beaten egg whites and fold into cheese mixture.
Pour into your favorite cookie crumb crust. Chill until set.

title: the cake that won't last
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add all the rest of the ingredients.
Do not beat.
Just stir until blended.
Bake at 350° in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan for 1 hour.
Note: You can add about 4 ounces additional pineapple extra if you want to make the cake extra moist.

title: microwave scrambled eggs
directions: Cooking Time is 45 to 60 seconds

title: chocolate pies(makes 2 pies)
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together.
Add yolks to cocoa mix. Add milk.
Cook until thick.
Add butter or margarine and vanilla. Pour into cooked pie crusts.
Top with beaten egg whites.
Brown in oven.

title: onion-cauliflower bake
directions: Cut up any large pieces of cauliflower; set aside. In a saucepan, combine frozen onions, water and butter. Cover; bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer for 4 minutes, stirring occasionally. Remove from heat. Stir until sauce is smooth. Stir in cauliflower, cheese, almonds and parsley. Turn mixture into a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Bake, uncovered, at 350° until bubbly, about 35 minutes. Top with crumbled French-fried onions. Bake, uncovered, 5 minutes longer. Makes 8 servings.

title: lura's salad
directions: Mix tomatoes, peppers and onion.
Add sugar and vinegar.
Toss together.
So simple, yet so good!

title: tostado soup
directions: Brown
beef
with
onion
and
simmer, then drain well. Drain and
puree tomatoes reserving juice.
Then add tomatoes and juice to	saucepan along with beans, water, picante sauce and cumin. Bring
to boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 10 minutes. Ladle
into
soup bowls.
Top with corn chips and shredded cheese. Serves 4 to 6.

title: pickled eggs and beets
directions: Bring beets, sugar and vinegar to boil.
Pour beet mixture over eggs.
Refrigerate at least 24 hours.

title: mexicali burgers
directions: Combine ground beef, catsup and salt with 1 1/2 tsp. chili powder and 1 1/2 c. onions.
Make 6 patties.
Broil 5-inch from heat, 5 min. each side.
Top with cheese that has been mixed with remaining chili powder.
Return to broiler until cheese is slightly melted, 1 - 2 min.
Top with remaining onion rings.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl.
Refrigerate.

title: terry's cheese dip
directions: Melt cheese in microwave.
Add taco sauce. Brown meat, onion and pepper. Add to cheese and taco sauce.
Keep warm and use chips to dip.

title: corn souffle
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: avocado salsa(servings:  4)
directions: Saute onion in oil.
Cut tomatillos in half and add to onion, lime juice and seasonings.
Cook 2 minutes, then set aside to cool.
Peel and put avocados in.
Add tomatillos with onion mixture to food processor.
Puree until smooth.
Allow sauce to stand 1 hour before serving.

title: dill pickles
directions: You will also need one quart Mason jars.

title: cream cheese fruit squares
directions: Roll graham crackers into crumbs between two sheets of waxed paper.
Place in bowl.
Add 1/4 cup sugar and melted margarine. Press into bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix Dream Whip and refrigerate.
Mix 8 ounces cream cheese, 1/2 cup confectioners sugar and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Add to Dream Whip and beat 5 minutes.
Put in pan.
Top with pie filling.
Refrigerate.

title: drop sugar cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees F.

title: vanilla nut bread
directions: Combine flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt; set aside. Combine 2 tablespoons butter with walnuts, brown sugar and 1 teaspoon of the vanilla. Mix with a fork until mixture is crumbly; set aside.

title: lime pickles
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Soak overnight in large crock. Rinse and put in clean water for 3 hours.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Soak in mixture overnight.
Boil for 30 minutes. Seal in jars.

title: frozen corn
directions: Husk, silk and wash corn.
Cut from cob into a large roaster. Add butter and half and half.
Put in 325° oven.
Cook for 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Remove from oven.
Cool down by placing roaster in sink with ice water under it.
Divide corn into 2 containers for faster cooling.
When cool, package and freeze as quickly as possible.
To serve, heat corn through.
Add salt and a bit of sugar, if desired.

title: squash casserole
directions: Boil
sliced
squash
and
diced
onion
until	tender. Season to taste with salt and pepper.
In baking dish spread a layer of cooked squash
and	onions,
then
a layer of crushed Fritos, then a layer
of
grated cheese.
Repeat until dish is full with cheese topping
the
casserole.
Bake at 400° until slightly brown.

title: corncob jelly
directions: Run water over cobs to take off last of shaff.
In a roaster oven cover the cobs with water and boil 30 minutes.
Use a lot of water, then cobs absorb a lot.
Stir 3 cups of the red corn "likker" into a pan.
Add one package or Sure-Jell.
Let this come to a boil, then add 3 cups sugar.
When this comes to a hard boil, let it boil a minute or until it starts to jell.
Test by dipping a fork in, if the liquid holds a second it's ready for jars.

title: hawaiian meatballs
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees.
In a large bowl, combine beef, crumbs, salt, ginger, 2 teaspoons honey, soy sauce, and egg.
Mix well and form into small balls about 1 inch in diameter. Place in baking pan that is about 1 inch deep.
In medium bowl, combine the barbecue sauce, pineapple topping and remaining 1 tablespoon of honey.
Mix well and set aside.

title: baptist pound cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar. Add 1 egg at a time, beating well after each. Sift flour.
Add baking powder and sift again. Add flour and milk alternately to mixture. Add vanilla. Pour into a greased and floured tube or Bundt pan.
Start baking in a cold oven. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: cheese zucchini casserole
directions: Cook zucchini until barely tender in salted water.
Saute beef and chop onion until beef is lightly browned.
Add rice and seasonings.
Place zucchini in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cover with beef mixture.
Spoon in cottage cheese and all remaining zucchini. Spread soup over top and sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until bubbly.

title: praline ice cream sauce
directions: Spread pecans on a baking sheet; bake at 300° for 15 minutes. Set aside.

title: peanut butter brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Beat until smooth.
Pour into a 8 x 12-inch greased pan and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chess bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Melt butter in large saucepan over low heat; remove pan from heat. Stir in remaining ingredients, except confectioners sugar, in order listed.
Mix well after each addition, using large spoon to mix not mixer.
Spread batter in prepared pan.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes or until cake begins to pull away from sides of pan.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes.
Sift confectioners sugar over top.
Cool completely and cut into bars or squares.
Makes about 12 to 15 servings.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add salt.
Add 1/2 milk and 1/2 flour; mix well.
Add eggs, one at a time, alternating with remaining flour.
Put baking powder in remaining 1/2 cup of milk and add to batter.
Add flavoring.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: peach schnapps slush
directions: Add sugar to hot tea to melt sugar.
Add all ingredients together and stir well.
Freeze with lid 24 hours.
Spoon out and add 7-Up.

title: skillet chicken
directions: Cut chicken into bite size chunks.
Sprinkle on lemon pepper, salt and garlic powder.
Put in skillet over medium high heat. Pour Worcestershire sauce, onion and chestnuts over chicken.
Cook about 10 minutes or until chicken is done.
Serve over rice or with vegetables.

title: boursin cheese spread
directions: Blend all ingredients together.
Serve with crackers.
(Can be frozen.)

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Tear up lettuce and put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add each layer as it is called for, one on top of the other.
Do not toss. Refrigerate 24 hours before serving.

title: snow and gold salad
directions: Drain peaches (save juice for something else).
Whip cream; fold in dry jello, peaches, cottage cheese and nuts.
Put into square pan.
Chill until firm; serve on lettuce.
Any combination may be used to vary recipe.

title: easy pear pie
directions: Make a layer of pears. Sprinkle with cinnamon and layer cake mix over pears. Drizzle butter over all cake mix.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: granny's sugar cookies(use with cookie cutters.)
directions: Cream together butter and sugar. Blend in egg. Sift together and add to mixture flour, powder, salt and vanilla. Divide dough into 2 parts. Chill for 1 to 2 hours. Roll dough to 1/8-inch thickness and cut out cookies. Preheat oven to 375°. Bake 8 to 10 minutes.

title: how to freeze corn
directions: Cut raw corn from the cob. If your corn is mature enough make two cuts down the cob instead of cutting close to the cob.

I use the blade of the knife and scrape the cob. Place the corn in a large heavy pot to prevent the corn from scorching and add the water, salt and sugar. Bring to a boil and simmer for 15 minutes. Remove from heat and cool at room temperature then chill in refrigerator over night before bagging and freezing.

title: coconut-pecan frosting
directions: Combine milk, sugar, egg yolks, butter and vanilla in a saucepan. Cook and stir over medium heat until thickened, about 12 minutes. Remove from heat. Add coconut and pecans. Beat until cool and thick enough to spread. Makes 2 1/2 cups or enough for tops of three 8 or 9-inch layers.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Cook to hard boil stage.
Stir in teaspoon of vanilla.
Enough for about 5 quarts of popped corn or 15 or 20 balls.

title: cream potato casserole
directions: Layer ingredients in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish until all ingredients are used up.
Bake at 375° until potatoes are tender. Garnish with paprika, if desired.

title: scotcharoos
directions: Combine sugar and syrup in saucepan. Cook over moderate heat. Stir frequently until bubbles. Remove from heat.
