Stir in peanut butter. Mix well. Add to cereal (in big bowl). Stir well. Press into buttered 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat egg whites until fluffy.
Slowly beat in sugar and vanilla.
Stir in chips.
Place by teaspoon on foil-lined cooking sheet.
Turn off oven and leave in overnight.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except the cheese and melted margarine.
Put in a greased 9 x 13-inch dish.
Pour melted margarine over the top and then cover with the shredded cheese. Bake uncovered for 1 hour at 325°.

title: homemade potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes and onion; do not drain water off.
In a large pot, melt butter.
Add flour.
Stir until smooth.
Add half and half.
Beat until thick, stirring constantly, then add to potato, onion and water.
Cook for 1/2 hour on low heat, stirring often (do not boil).
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add parsley for looks.

title: potato-onion bake
directions: Alternately layer potatoes and onions in a greased 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over. Bake at 450° for 50 to 60 minutes or until tender.

title: garlic bread
directions: Slice bread as if serving, but not slicing all the way through.
Mix together all ingredients.
Spread on both sides of each slice.
Wrap loaf in foil.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes or until melted.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Combine potatoes, onion and cheese, stirring until evenly mixed.
Stir in soups and sour cream.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle (spread) the combined melted butter and Corn Flakes over the potato mixture.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix broccoli, onion, rice, chestnuts and celery. Pour into 8 x 12-inch baking dish which has been greased. Mix soup and cheese; pour over broccoli mix. Bake at 350° until hot, about 15 minutes. Do not overcook.

title: low-fat mushroom soup
directions: In a medium saucepan, saute mushrooms in margarine until just tender; gently mix in strained chicken broth.
Add lemon juice, vermouth, sherry and Tabasco sauce and heat until warm.
Makes 5 one cup servings.
Contains 95 calories per serving.

title: jellied spanish relish
directions: Dissolve the two gelatins in boiling water.
Add vinegar, pepper and salt and dissolve.
Add cold water.
Chill.
When slightly thickened, fold in remaining ingredients.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill and let set until firm.
Cut into squares. Serves 8.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients and put in baking dish.
Mix sugar, flour, butter and nuts.
Sprinkle on top of potatoes.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Mix chocolate cake mix as directed, but put more butter in one pan than you do the other.
In a big bowl, put the smallest cake whole in the bottom.
Cook 4 packages of pudding by directions. Put into bowl by layers.
Then scrape chips of candy bar on top. Refrigerate overnight.

title: sweet gherkins pickles
directions: Heat to boiling; pour over pickles.
Will only be 1/2 covered. In the afternoon, drain in saucepan; add 2 cups sugar and 2 cups vinegar.
Heat to boiling; pour over pickles.

title: zucchini crustless quiche
directions: Mix all ingredients together until zucchini is well coated. Pour into a buttered 10 x 6 x 1 3/4-inch oblong dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: isabel's oven chicken
directions: Bring
all
ingredients
to
a boil.
Pour mixture over chicken
and marinate for about 1 hour.
Bake in this juice in 350° oven for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: hawaiian macadamia coconut squares
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch baking pan; set aside.
In a large mixing bowl, beat butter, 1 cup brown sugar, instant coffee powder, 1/4 teaspoon cinnamon and 1/4 teaspoon salt until light and fluffy.
Stir in flour 1/2 cup at a time, blending well after each addition.
Spread evenly in prepared pan. Bake 20 minutes.
Cook in pan on rack 15 minutes.

title: easy mideastern pilaf
directions: Stove: Combine broth, onion, butter, raisins and salt in saucepan.
Bring to a full boil.
Stir in rice.
Cover; remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Stir in almonds and parsley.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except crackers and butter.
Pour into an 8 x 11-inch glass baking dish.
Melt butter and mix in crushed crackers.
Set aside.
Bake casserole at 350° for 20
minutes. Remove from oven and sprinkle crushed crackers over top.
Return to oven and bake 10 more minutes.
Serve hot.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion in skillet.
Add other ingredients and simmer 10 minutes.
Add the cooked macaroni.
Pour into 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: banana cake
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and eggs.
Add mashed banana and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients and sour milk.
Stir in nuts.
Bake at 350 for 45-50 minutes in a greased
9 X 13 pan.

title: lasagna
directions: Crumble ground beef in bowl.
Microwave 3 to 4 minutes on High until brown.
Drain.
Add sauce and 1/2 cup water.
Microwave 3 to 4 minutes on High until hot.

title: candied yams
directions: Scrub sweet potatoes.
Boil until tender.
Cool and peel and cut in half.
Make simple syrup by putting sugar in pot and cover with water.
Cook until the consistency of syrup.
Place potatoes in casserole and pour syrup over potatoes.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and nutmeg, then dot with butter.
Bake on low heat for 1/2 hour. Add marshmallows and cherries; place back in oven and bake until marshmallows are browned.
Keep warm until ready to eat.

title: breakfast cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until done.
When hot, spread with butter and sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Cut up fruits and nuts and coat well with one or two cups of flour.
In a large bowl, cream butter and sugar in mixer and add eggs, one at a time.
Sift remaining flour with soda and cinnamon. Alternate adding milk and flour to the mixture.
Pour over fruit and nuts and stir well by hand with a wooden spoon.
Drop by tablespoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° for 20 minutes or until done.

title: chocolate kahlua pie
directions: Whip butter until creamy.
Add the melted chocolate, then mix in the sugar.
Slowly add the Kahlua, then the eggs.
Pour mixture into prepared pie crust and refrigerate 2 hours or until set. Garnish with whipped cream.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: little tree salad(daddy's favorite!)
directions: Cut off broccoli stems and separate florets.
Mix together mayonnaise and honey and add garlic salt (to taste) for dressing. Mix dressing into broccoli.
Slice onion into rings.
Add to broccoli along with croutons.
Toss and serve.

title: sauteed greens and black-eyed peas
directions: Cut kale and broccoli rabe leaves into two pieces.
In large saucepan of boiling, salted water, cook kale and broccoli 15 minutes until tender.
Drain in colander.
In same saucepan in olive oil over medium heat, saute garlic, crushed pepper flakes, shredded yam and diced red pepper 5 minutes.
Stir in kale mixture, black-eyed peas and salt.
Cover; cook 10 minutes or until vegetables are tender, stirring occasionally.
Serve garnished with lemon wedges.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Sift flour, cinnamon, soda and sugar together. Put water, margarine, oil and cocoa in a boiler; bring to a boil and pour over dry mixture. Mix well. Add to this the buttermilk, eggs and vanilla. Mix well and pour into a sheet pan, greased and floured. Cook at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Peel squash and cut into chunks.
Place in water; cover and cook until tender. In mixing bowl, mix butter, eggs and squash; beat thoroughly.
Add pineapple, evaporated milk, brown sugar, bourbon and walnuts.
Pour into casserole or small individual oven dishes.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.

title: jeannette's pound cake
directions: Grease a cake pan or a 12-cup Bundt (10 x 4-inch) pan.
Beat on low speed the sugar, margarine, vanilla, lemon flavoring and orange flavoring.
Beat on high speed for 5 minutes.
Add milk; mix well.
Slowly add the flour, salt and baking powder.
Pour into pan.
Bake for 70 to 80 minutes at 350°.
Cool for 20 minutes, then roll in confectioners sugar until coated good.
Wrap in foil.

title: corn casserole
directions: In 1 to 1 1/2-quart casserole, melt margarine in microwave. Drain whole corn, mix in dish with remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, uncovered.

title: blueberry tapioca
directions: Stir together all ingredients in 2-quart saucepan; let stand 5 minutes.
Stirring constantly, bring to full boil.
Ladle into 5 (1-cup) individual dessert bowls.
Serve warm or chilled, topped with whipped cream.
Yields 5 servings.

title: shrimp treats
directions: Mix butter, Old English spread and shrimp together, making it a creamy mixture.
Cut English muffins in 1/2; spread mixture over top.
Broil until golden brown.
Cut up into bite sizes.

title: no-fat buttermilk yogurt dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in a wide mouth jar or small bowl. Mix well until uniformly blended.
Chill.
Store in a covered container in refrigerator.

title: biscuit pudding(with caramel apple sauce)
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Melt butter in a 9x13x2 inch baking pan. In large bowl, combine biscuits, milk, and raisins. Stir to mix. In medium bowl, combine eggs, sugar, and vanilla. Beat well. Add to biscuit mixture and mix well. Pour into baking pan. Bake for 1 hour. Serve with Caramel Apple Sauce.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta; drain and rinse in cold water.
Chop remaining ingredients.
Add to pasta.
Add dressing.
Mix and refrigerate.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni.
Run cold water over macaroni; drain.
Mix all ingredients.
Refrigerate 2 hours before serving.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix together the Eagle Brand milk, egg yolk (beaten), and 1/2 cup lemon juice.
Pour into pie crust.
Cover with Cool Whip and chill.

title: strawberry salsa
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Cover; refrigerate overnight.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Measure salt and flour	into
large mixing bowl. Cut in shortening	with
pastry
blender
until particles are size of peas.
Beat
egg;
add
water
and	vinegar.
Pour	into flour mixture
and
mix. Divide into 4 balls. Roll on floured board. Makes 2 double crusts.

title: hot chicken salad casserole
directions: Put layer of potato chips in buttered 9 x 9-inch baking dish. Combine chicken, peas, soup, celery, onion and mayo; add to casserole dish.
Cover with potato chips.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: delma's shrimp dip
directions: Chop or process shrimp. Mix cream cheese and salad dressing until well blended; add onion and bell pepper. Season with a small amount of Tony's seasoning if desired. Chill. Serve with crackers. Good!

title: potato candy
directions: Mix the sugar and potatoes to form a paste; roll it out and spread with peanut butter.
Roll up like jelly roll and slice in 1/2-inch pieces.

title: *orange pineapple cake*
directions: Thoroughly blend together the cake mix, eggs, oil and orange slices.
Pour into greased and floured 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool completely, then mix together the remaining ingredients and frost cake.
Refrigerate for 2 hours before serving.

title: kraut salad
directions: Drain kraut overnight.
Cut into small pieces; add other ingredients.
Cook sugar and vinegar, just enough to dissolve sugar.
Pour over kraut mixture and marinate overnight.
Toss with a fork.

title: chicken stir-fry
directions: Marinate chicken in 1 teaspoon of soy sauce, white pepper to taste and salt to taste.
Cut bok choy stems into 1/4-inch slices and leaves into 2-inch pieces.
Heat wok or large skillet.
Add 1 tablespoon of oil and rotate pan to coat sides.
Add chicken and cook until it turns white; remove.
Add remaining oil.
Add ginger root and garlic; cook until garlic turns light brown.
Add bok choy stems, mushrooms, carrots, broccoli and water chestnuts. Stir in chicken, boy choy leaves, chicken broth, oyster sauce and white wine.
Cover and cook for 2 to 5 minutes.
Mix 1/4 cup of water with 2 tablespoons cornstarch and add to skillet.
Cook and stir until thickened.
Serves 6.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Mix all together and put in a 2 1/2-quart dish.
Bake for 50 minutes at 350°.

title: butter icing
directions: Mix ingredients.
Will keep, covered, in refrigerator for an indefinite time.

title: 6-week bran muffins(can be doubled for large batch)
directions: Pour boiling water over bran and let stand. Cream the shortening or oil, sugar, eggs, buttermilk and bran mixture.

Sift flour, soda and salt. Add all at once to creamed mixture along with All-Bran. Fold only to mix all dry ingredients until moist. Bake in greased regular size muffin tins for 20 minutes at 375°. Fruit like raisins, dates, etc., can be added.
Keep in refrigerator for 6 weeks.

title: baked pineapple and cheese
directions: Partially drain pineapple and mix with grated cheese.
Mix sugar and flour and add all together. Butter lightly a 9 x 13 x 2-inch dish.
Pour mixture in dish and top with cracker crumbs. Pour melted butter over crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Reduce sugar if pineapple is sweetened.

title: baked swiss chicken
directions: Place chicken in a greased 13 x 9 baking pan. In a bowl, combine the soup and wine or broth. Pour over chicken. Top with cheese. Sprinkle with croutons. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until done. Yields 6 servings.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat the first 6 ingredients until the mixture is smooth.
Fold in chips and pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Delicious!

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and marinate for at least 6 hours.

title: diabetic banana nut bread
directions: Grease and flour a 9 x 5 x 2-inch loaf pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix butter, eggs, Sugar Twin and nuts.
Add vanilla; mix well.
Add flour, stirring well.
Stir in bananas.
Spoon into pan.
Bake for 55 minutes or until done.

title: baked asparagus
directions: Cook until thick first 7 ingredients.
Place in layers, asparagus, eggs, then sauce.
Top with bread crumbs and cheese. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Add taco seasoning, juice, corn and beans.
Simmer.
Serve by crushing chips in bowl before adding soup, then top with cheese.

title: chicken casserole with asparagus
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Drain the mushrooms and reserve liquid. Melt the butter in a large frypan.
Add the mushrooms and onion and cook over medium heat until onion is transparent.
Remove from heat.
Add the flour, salt, pepper and curry powder and stir until blended.

Add enough water to reserved mushroom liquid to make 1/2 cup liquid and add to mushroom mixture, slowly stirring constantly. Blend in milk and cook over medium heat, stirring until thickened. Add chicken and noodles.
Cook the asparagus according to package directions and drain.
Add to chicken mixture and mix.
Turn into a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole and top with cheese.
Bake for 20 to 30 minutes or until heated through and cheese is melted.

title: chicken zucchini marinara
directions: Mix bread crumbs and 1/4 cup of Parmesan cheese.
Coat chicken pieces with flour.
Dip into egg. Then coat both sides with crumb and cheese mixture.
Heat oil in 10-inch skillet with cover. Add chicken.
Brown on both sides over medium heat.

title: potato-ham bake
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
In a large mixing bowl, combine cream of chicken soup (undiluted), butter, sour cream, chopped onion and Cheddar cheese.
Add the cooked ham and bag of frozen hash brown potatoes.
Mix all together and spread in pan.
Bake approximately 1 hour in a 350° oven.
Serve with green salad and hard rolls.
Yields 6 to 7 large portions.

title: maple butter glazed carrots
directions: Bring water and salt to boiling in a medium size heavy saucepan.
Add carrots; return to boiling.
Cover; simmer 15 minutes or until carrots are just tender.
Drain thoroughly.
Cook maple syrup, butter, marjoram, salt and pepper in a large skillet over low heat 2 to 3 minutes or until bubbly and caramel-like in consistency.
Add carrots; toss gently to coat in the maple butter. Cook over high heat, tossing gently, until carrots are glazed and liquid is absorbed.

title: cheese and pineapple hedgehog
directions: You will need a package of wooden sharp ended toothpicks (cocktail sticks in England).

title: white frosting
directions: Cook sugar, water, and syrup in saucepan until mixture spins a 6 to 8-inch thread.
Beat egg whites until stiff and continue to beat while pouring in syrup mixture.
Add vanilla.
Beat until thick.

title: the ultimate chocolate chip cookie
directions: Combine Crisco, brown sugar, milk and vanilla in a large bowl. Add egg into creamed mixture.
Combine flour, salt and baking soda and mix into creamed mixture until blended.
Stir in chocolate chips and pecans.
Drop rounded tablespoonfuls 3 inches apart on an ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes for chewy cookies.

title: orange julius
directions: Pour orange juice into blender.
Add ice cubes.
Add milk until ice is completely covered (be sure to leave mixing room at the top of the blender).
Add vanilla and sweetener or sugar to taste.
Blend until ice is crushed.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Stir first 3 ingredients over low heat in saucepan.
When butter melts, add in peanut butter, oats and vanilla.
Then stir and drop tablespoonful on wax paper. Let cool.

title: homemade brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Generously grease a square pan (8 x 8 x 2-inch).
Bake 30 to 35 minutes until top has dull crust.
A slight imprint will remain when touched lightly with finger.
Cool slightly; cut in 2-inch squares.
Makes 16 brownies.

title: pineapple cherry dump cake
directions: Sprinkle cake mix over cherry pie filling and pineapple, not drained.
Add each ingredient and smooth.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Fry hamburger with onion and drain.
Mix meat with lettuce, cheese, beans and tomatoes.
Add Doritos and then Catalina dressing.
Mix well.
Top with salsa, guacamole and sour cream, if desired.
Serve immediately.

title: green peas with celery and onion
directions: Cook peas as directed on package, except cook with celery and onions.
Drain.
Stir in margarine and salt.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Bake crescent rolls after pressing into a 10 x 15-inch pan as directed on can and cool.
Mix cream cheese, sour cream and salad dressing.
Pour onto cooled dough.
Top with chopped broccoli, cauliflower, black olives, grated carrots and shredded Cheddar cheese.

title: cheddary scalloped potatoes
directions: Layer sliced potatoes and onion. Salt and pepper each layer. Dot each layer with butter or margarine. Cover with broccoli-cheese soup and 1/2 cup milk.
Bake casserole for 45 minutes to 1 hour in a 350° oven.
Serves 4.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Combine sugars, pumpkin, oil and eggs.
Beat until well blended.
Sift together flour, baking soda, salt and spices.
Add to sugar mixture and mix well.
Stir in raisins, nuts and water. Spoon into well-greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 65 to 75 minutes or until well done when tested.
Take out of pan and place on cooling rack so as to cool thoroughly.

title: chicken-sausage gumbo
directions: Cut up chicken and boil in separate pot.
Make a dark roux of flour and drippings in iron Dutch oven.
When dark enough, immediately fill halfway with water.
Add onion and celery.
Add chicken parts when almost done and sausage, cut up in 1/4-inch pieces.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer until done.
May have to skim off any excess oil from sausage.
Serve over mounds of rice with crackers, hot sauce, green salad and iced tea.

title: kiley's seasoned chicken
directions: Place chicken in a baking dish; salt and pepper.
Pour in melted butter and water.
Sprinkle with seasoned salt.
Place in a 350° preheated oven and bake for about 2 hours or until done. Cover with foil.

title: chicken macaroni en casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a buttered 2-quart baking dish. Bake 1 hour.

title: bul ko kee
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Refrigerate about 20 minutes. Bake in cake pan at 350° for about an hour, until meat is well done.

title: cream cheese squares
directions: Cream butter and brown sugar.
Add flour and nuts; mix until crumbly stage.
Save 1 cup for topping.
Press remainder in 8-inch pan; bake 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.
Blend sugar and cream cheese; add milk, lemon juice, egg and vanilla.
Beat well.
Spread over crust and put remaining crumbly mixture on top.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: ware neck clam chowder
directions: Place all ingredients except bacon into large cooking pot and bring to boil.
Microwave bacon about 6 to 7 minutes.
Pour drippings and bacon into pot.
Simmer until potatoes are done.

title: baked chicken breasts
directions: Melt butter in a 8 1/2 x 14-inch baking dish.
Stir in flour; add sour cream.
Sprinkle chicken with garlic salt, salt and pepper and place, skin side up in baking dish with other ingredients.
Pour sherry over chicken. Bake at 350° for 2 hours. Add water to avoid dryness.

title: tartar sauce
directions: Mix everything together, except mayonnaise, place in colander and allow to drain well (over 1/2 hour).
Measure, then combine cabbage mixture with equal amount of mayonnaise to make 4 cups.

title: "harvest zucchini"
directions: Prepare 4 cups sliced zucchini as directed.

In large skillet, cook and stir zucchini and onion in butter until butter is melted. Cover; cook, stirring occasionally, until zucchini is tender. Mix remaining ingredients; gently stir into zucchini and heat through.

title: watergate salad
directions: Combine pudding, pineapple juice, Cool Whip, and cream cheese; mix very well.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours before serving.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Mix sugar, milk and margarine in large saucepan.
Bring to a hard boil, stirring constantly.
Boil for 8 minutes, still stirring.
Remove from heat and add chocolate chips and marshmallow cream.
Stir to dissolve.
Add vanilla.
Pour in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool.

title: pecan cookies
directions: Into the stiffly beaten egg whites, fold sugar, vanilla and pecans until all are moist.
Drop small spoonfuls on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Preheat the oven to 400°, then turn off the oven and cook 12 to 15 minutes.
(Be sure that the sugar is well moistened.)

title: danish puffs
directions: Cut margarine into flour until like coarse meal.
Add water and stir until well blended.
Divide dough in half.
Press each half into a 3 x 12-inch oblong size on an ungreased cookie sheet.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice, curry and drained chestnuts.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, spread beans and cover with chicken.
Pour soup mixture over and bake until bubbly.
Take out of oven and cover with grated cheese and potato chips.
Return to oven and bake until cheese is melted and chips are brown.

title: corn spoon bread
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Do not cover.
Add cheese and bake 10 to 15 minutes longer or until knife comes out clean.
You can also saute chopped onions to put on top when you add cheese.

title: quick stew
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Cover and bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: blueberry muffins(12 muffins)
directions: Combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Stir in blueberries gently.
Add milk, egg and butter.
Mix just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Do not overbeat.
Batter will be lumpy.
Spoon batter into twelve paper-lined muffin cups.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: australian cookies
directions: Melt butter and molasses in saucepan; add soda mixed with water.
Pour over dry ingredients which have been mixed together in bowl.
Take small teaspoons of mixture and roll in hand.
Place on greased cookie sheet and bake at 300° for 20 minutes.
Remove from pan when cool.
Store in airtight container.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease 2 loaf pans.

title: boiled custard
directions: Mix sugar
and
flour together.
Stir in milk and eggs. Cook over low heat, stirring continuously until thickens.
Add vanilla. Serve hot.
Serves 2.

title: french dressing
directions: Put all ingredients in a blender and blend until smooth.
Keep in refrigerator.
Makes about 2 1/4 cups.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Combine all ingredients except baking soda and popcorn.
Mix in large micro-safe bowl.
Bring to boil in microwave.
Boil 2 minutes on High.
Add baking soda.
Place popped popcorn in large brown grocery bag.
Pour caramel sauce over popcorn into brown bag.
Shake.
Put in microwave.
Cook on High 1 1/2 minutes. Remove.
Shake and cook on High 1 1/2 minutes more.
Remove from microwave.
Dump on cookie sheet.
Cool.
Enjoy.

title: favorite oatmeal cookies
directions: In a large mixing bowl, beat butter, sugar, brown sugar and baking soda. Beat until combined, scraping sides of bowl occasionally. Beat in eggs and vanilla until combined. Beat in flour. Stir in rolled oats, walnuts and raisins with a wooden spoon. Drop by rounded teaspoons 2-inches apart onto an ungreased cookie sheet. Bake in a 350° oven for 8 to 10 minutes or until edges are lightly browned.

title: chicken pie
directions: In medium saucepan, cook onion in margarine until tender. Blend in flour and salt.
Add broth.
Cook and stir until thickened.
Add chicken and vegetables.
Pour into casserole dish. Set oven temperature according to canned biscuit directions. Before adding biscuits, get casserole good and hot by heating in oven until it bubbles around the edges.
Top casserole with biscuits and continue cooking according to biscuit can directions or until biscuits start to brown and are not doughy. Serves 6.

title: chocolate pie(no cooking)
directions: Cream butter, sugar and vanilla.
Beat in 1 egg for 5 minutes. Beat in other egg for 5 minutes.
Add chocolate.
Add nuts.
Pour into crumb or regular crust.
Chill.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: chili cheesy rice pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In a medium bowl stir together rice and soup.
Transfer rice mix to greased 9-inch pie plate.
Press rice evenly over bottom and up sides to form "pie crust".
Pour chili into rice crust.
Bake, uncovered, for 25 to 30 minutes or until very hot.
Remove from oven; let sit 5 minutes before cutting.
Top with sour cream and onion, if desired.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni; drain.
Melt margarine in heavy saucepan; blend in flour.
Stir in milk slowly and cook, stirring constantly until mixture is thickened.
Add seasonings and cheese, stirring until cheese is melted.
Add macaroni; mix well and transfer to a serving dish.

title: apricot jam
directions: Place the chopped apricots in a saucepan.
Cover with water. Simmer until the apricots are soft and tender, about 1/2 hour. Add water if necessary to keep apricots covered.
With slotted spoon, remove fruit pulp and measure.
Return to pan.
For every cup of fruit, add 1/3 cup sugar and 1/3 cup honey.
Add lemon juice.
Simmer 1/2 hour until thickened.
Stir in the almond extract.
Pour into hot, sterilized jars and seal with paraffin.

title: monster cookies for a monstrous crowd
directions: Mix ingredients as listed.
Drop on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Recipe may be cut down.

title: fudgy banana ice cream dessert
directions: Layer graham crackers in pan.
Next, lay sliced bananas on top. Spread ice cream over bananas.
Freeze until firm.
In saucepan, melt butter and chocolate chips together.
Add Pet milk, powdered sugar and vanilla.
Cook until thick; this may take up to 10 to 15 minutes.
Stir often.
Cool.
Pour over ice cream.
Freeze until firm.

title: miracle mayo
directions: Drain tofu in several layers of paper towels for at least 2 hours.
Change paper towel once or twice.
Whip egg in food processor until creamy, pour into small dish and set aside.
Place drained tofu in food processor and mix until creamy, scraping sides frequently.
Add remaining ingredients and egg mixture.
Mix well and chill.
Use as needed for mayonnaise.
Five tablespoons = 1 ounce protein.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Thoroughly combine flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and baking soda in large bowl.
Stir in raisins and caraway seed.

Stir in buttermilk to make a soft and sticky dough. Turn out onto lightly floured surface and knead lightly 3 times. Shape dough into a round loaf and place on greased baking sheet. Cut an "X" 1/4-inch deep in top of loaf.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until golden.

title: rhubarb crunch
directions: Mix flour, oats, brown sugar, butter and cinnamon.
Spread 1/2 of mixture on bottom of 12 x 9-inch cake pan.
Save rest for top. Place cut rhubarb into pan.
Sprinkle with nutmeg or cinnamon. Mix flour with sugar.
Add boiling water.
Cook until thick.
Pour over other ingredients.
Sprinkle crumb mixture over rhubarb. Cook at 350° until bubbly, 35 to 40 minutes.

title: apple nut cake
directions: Stir together eggs, sugar, oil and flour mixed with salt, soda and cinnamon.
Add apples and nuts.
Stir together and pour into greased and floured 9x13 pan.

title: cool whip salad
directions: Mix jello in Cool Whip.
Add cottage cheese. Mix well. Add pineapple and nuts.
Chill before eating, 2 hours.

title: english peas and asparagus casserole
directions: Mix soup, onion, Worcestershire, salt and pepper to taste. Place layer of English peas, layer of asparagus in baking dish.
If preferred, cut water chestnuts and sprinkle over this.
Add layer of soup mix.
Top with grated cheese and bread crumbs buttered. Bake in moderate oven about 20 minutes or until bubbly and brown.

title: tenderloin steaks with mushroom sauce
directions: In 10-inch skillet over medium-high heat in 1 tablespoon hot salad oil, cook steaks until undersides of steaks are browned. Turn steaks; sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Cook to desired doneness.
Remove steaks to warm plate and keep warm.
Slice mushrooms.
In cup with fingers, blend margarine or butter with flour to form a paste.

title: black bing cherry salad
directions: Drain cherries and pineapple.
Heat the juice; add to jello and stir until dissolved.
Add Coca-Cola.
Stir and put in refrigerator.
When jello begins to set, stir in chopped cherries, pineapple and nuts.
Return to refrigerator until it jells.
Good with ham, chicken or turkey.

title: carrot fruitcake
directions: Combine nuts, fruit, dates and raisins with 1/2 cup flour; set aside.

In a large mixing bowl, combine sugar and oil; mix well. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Combine baking powder, soda, cinnamon, salt and remaining flour; gradually add to sugar mixture, beating until smooth.
Fold in carrots and fruit mixture.
Spoon into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes or until cake is done.
Cool for 15 minutes before removing from pan to cool on a wire rack.
Yield:
12 to 16 servings.

title: apple cake
directions: Cream shortening; add sugars gradually.
Add eggs and beat well.
Sift together flour, baking powder, cinnamon and salt; add alternately to creamed mixture with the sour milk to which has been added the soda.
Fold in apples.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 15-inch pan.
Spread topping.
Bake for 40 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: summer fruit salad
directions: Layer fruit in large bowl in order given.
Spoon orange juice on top.
Cover and chill for 6 to 8 hours in refrigerator.

title: puppy chow snack
directions: Combine margarine, chocolate chips and peanut butter.
Heat until melted.
Pour over Chex and stir until Chex are coated.
Add powdered sugar and stir until Chex are well coated.
Store in container with lid.

title: marilyn's lazy day lemon pie
directions: Combine Cool Whip, Eagle Brand milk and lemonade in mixing bowl.
Pour into a graham cracker crust.
Chill.

title: sandy's dinner rolls(famous p-w dinner rolls at school)
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients together and make sure you use a big bowl. Then add flour 2 cups at a time until you can handle it and the dough is not sticky to touch. Then put aside to double in size and punch down, then let raise again till double in size and then roll out and cut out with a doughnut cutter without the middle. Put on greased pan and let raise to double in size and bake at 350 for 20-25 min. or till golden brown and brush with butter.

title: apple-allspice muffins
directions: Cream 1/4 cup margarine in a medium bowl.
Gradually add 1/2 cup brown sugar substitute, beating at medium speed of an electric mixer until mixture is light and fluffy.
Add egg and mix well. Combine 1 1/2 cups flour, baking powder, 1/2 teaspoon ground allspice and salt.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with skim milk, stirring just until moistened.
Stir in finely chopped apple.

title: homemade oatmeal cake
directions: Boil water and add oatmeal and butter.
Mix well and set aside. Mix well the flour, brown sugar, white sugar, salt, eggs, cinnamon and baking soda.
Add to hot mixture in bowl.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Top with glaze as soon as it comes out of the oven.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg.
Sift dry ingredients together. Add to sugar mixture. Add remaining ingredients to this mixture. Blend.
Pour into a greased 5 x 9-inch loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: In bowl, mix hamburger and other ingredients together.
Mix well. Take peppers and cut off tops and take out center.
Stuff peppers with mix.
Take aluminum foil wrap.
Put in oven at 375°. Bake for 1 hour.

title: sourdough bread
directions: In a large plastic bowl, make a stiff batter of the ingredients. Grease another large plastic bowl. Put dough in and turn over to put oiled side up. Cover lightly with plastic wrap and let sit overnight or all day. Do not put in refrigerator. After it has sat all day or all night, punch down and knead some. Divide dough into 3 equal parts. Knead each part on a floured board a few times, 8 to 10. Put into greased loaf pans and brush tops with oil. Let rise in a warm place 4 to 5 hours or more; all day is fine. Cover with plastic wrap. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes. Remove. Brush tops with butter. Let cool in pans at least 10 minutes.

title: onion soup
directions: Melt oleo.
Add onion rings and cook until soft and golden brown.
Dissolve bouillon cubes in hot water.
Add to onions.
Cook over moderate flame 10 minutes.
Pour into bowls and sprinkle 1 tablespoon cheese over each.
Serves 4 at 115 calories per bowl.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients, except chips, in greased 10 x 13-inch baking dish.
Top with crushed chips.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: fish 'n chips(for 6 servings)
directions: Dip fish in milk.
Then roll fish in a mixture of potato chips, cheese and thyme.
Place fish in buttered baking dish. Sprinkle with any extra crumbs.
Drizzle margarine over top.
Bake in hot oven, 450° to 500°, for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: pickled eggs and beets
directions: Drain beets, reserving liquid.
Place beets and eggs in large bowl.
In medium saucepan, combine beet liquid and remaining ingredients.
Bring to boil and simmer about 2 minutes.
Pour over beets and eggs.
Cover and refrigerate 24 hours.
Drain and discard liquid.
Cut eggs in half lengthwise to show color.

title: barbecue dip
directions: Mix all ingredients in saucepan and bring to a boil.
Let simmer for several minutes and remove from heat.
Good sauce for chicken, pork chops, etc.
Sauce will keep several weeks in the refrigerator.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients; make a well in center and add eggs and oil, stirring only until dry ingredients are moistened.
Stir in berries, pecans and food coloring.
Spoon batter into two lightly greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until bread tests done.
Let stand overnight before slicing.

title: quick orange-glazed beets
directions: Heat beets in saucepan in their liquid.
Drain.
Add marmalade and vinegar.
Cook over low heat, stirring gently, until beets are glazed.

title: spinach balls
directions: Saute onion in margarine; mix all ingredients into onion (will be wet and moist).
Shape into balls (size of walnuts).
If hard to handle, set in refrigerator for awhile.
Set on cookie sheet, will be a full sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Can be frozen after baked, then heated on low temperature.

title: cinch-sational coleslaw
directions: In a small bowl mix mayo, vinegar, & sugar with a whisk until it turns into a dressing like texture. Check consistency and taste. Add bell pepper and onion if desired and salt and pepper. Check taste. Mix dressing into coleslaw until thoroughly covered.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients well and cook over low heat until begins to thicken.
Add 1 stick of butter while cooking.
After gravy thickens, remove from heat; add 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Serve hot over biscuits.

title: cranberry banana coffeecake
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Combine banana, milk, egg and shortening.
Add to flour mixture; stir to blend.
Pour into greased 9 x 9-inch baking pan.
Arrange cranberry slices on top and then pecan halves.
Sprinkle a little sugar over the top and bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: instant float
directions: Whip pudding according to directions on box.
Add Cool Whip, sugar, milk and vanilla.
If after this mixture sets a while it seems too thick, add more milk.

title: hungry jack casserole
directions: Brown beef.
Add rest of ingredients, except cheese and biscuits. Put in 2 quart casserole.
Cut biscuits in half.
Place cut side down around edge. Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple and add enough mandarin orange juice to make 1 1/2 cups juice.
Cook pudding with juice slowly until it comes to a boil.
It will thicken as it cools.
Cool thoroughly.
Spoon pudding over fruit as you layer it in a bowl.
If pudding is too thick, thin it by adding juice that is left over.
Serve.

title: raw vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a medium size bowl.
Chill at least 2 hours.
Suggested vegetables for dipping: carrots, celery, broccoli, peppers and cauliflower.

title: grilled chicken
directions: Shake until blended well or use blender to mix.
Enough for 2 or 3 chickens or 4-6 chicken halves.
Cook 1-1/2 hours on the grill.

title: weight watchers yum yum
directions: Cut
angel
food
cake
in squares.
Put in 9 x 13-inch dish. Drain
half
the
juice
off
large
can
of pineapple. Sprinkle pineapple
and remaining juice over cake.
Mix large box sugar-free Jell-O vanilla pudding with 3 cups of skim milk and put over cake mixture.
Take 1 banana, slice thin and put on top of pudding.
Spread medium box of Cool Whip over all.

title: easy bake stew
directions: Place meat in roasting pan.
Season with salt, pepper, paprika and onion soup mix.
Add potatoes, carrots and celery.
In a saucepan, blend celery soup with sherry and pour over meat and vegetables.
Cover and bake at 250° to 300° for 4 1/2 to 5 hours.

title: creamy cabbage soup
directions: In a 3-quart saucepan over medium heat, in hot butter, cook cabbage and onions until tender, stirring occasionally.
Add bacon; cook 2 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in soup, milk and water until smooth.
Heat through, stirring occasionally. Ladle into bowls; sprinkle with paprika.

title: buttermilk congealed salad
directions: Drain the juice from the pineapple into a small saucepan. Add the gelatin and cook over low heat, stirring until the gelatin is thoroughly dissolved.
Cool.
Mix the buttermilk and whipped topping. Add the pecans and gelatin.
Pour into a mold or casserole dish and refrigerate.
Serve when firm.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: mary's pecan tassies
directions: Mix cream cheese, margarine, flour and shape into dough for tassie pans or a very small muffin tin.

title: easy fruited chicken
directions: Remove fat from chicken; place in oven dish that has been lightly oiled.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until tender.

title: cheese souffle
directions: Make thick white sauce using milk, oleo, flour and salt.
Add cheese.
Add egg yolks, one at a time.
Beat well after each addition.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake in greased baking dish.
Place in a pan of water.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: chopped steaks and potatoes in mushroom gravy
directions: Brown steak.
Drain off fat and pat steaks with paper towels. In casserole dish spread one can of soup (do not dilute).
Add 1 can of potatoes, drained.
Put 4 steaks on top and add second can of soup and potatoes, then the remaining steaks.
Top with third can of soup.
Cover.
Bring to bubbly stage.
Reduce heat.
Simmer 20 to 30 minutes.

title: andrew's carrot cake and cream cheese frosting
directions: Mix oil, eggs and sugar.
Set aside.
Mix flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
Set aside.
Mix carrots, pineapple, walnuts and flavoring.
Mix all ingredients.
Grease and flour pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut each biscuit into 4 pieces.
Mix cinnamon and sugar in medium-size bowl.
Add a few pieces of biscuits at a time to sugar mixture and stir to coat.
Place half of the pieces in a greased Bundt pan.
Sprinkle with pecans or whatever.
Place the remaining biscuit pieces on top.
Boil brown sugar and butter in saucepan. Pour over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool 15 minutes.
Invert on plate.

title: golden cream potato soup
directions: Add water to potatoes, celery, onion, parsley flakes, seasoning and bouillon cube; cook until tender.
Blend flour with small amount of milk; stir in vegetable mixture.
Add remaining milk; cook until thickened.
Add Velveeta; stir until melted. Makes 6 to 8 servings.
Sprinkle remaining parsley flakes over each serving.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove stems from mushrooms.
Marinate caps for 1 hour in soy sauce.
Finely chop stems and mix with ground meat, onion, garlic, salt and pepper.
Drain caps.
Stuff with meat mixture, mounded high.
Brush tops with soy sauce.
Broil 8 to 10 minutes. Refrigerate or freeze.
When ready to serve, bring to room temperature.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: instant spice tea
directions: Mix together.
Add 4 to 6 teaspoons to a cup of very hot water.

title: cheesy gourmet potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes with skin, then peel.
Melt margarine and cheese.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Sprinkle with paprika. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: In Dutch oven cook ground beef or sausage, onion, green pepper and garlic until meat is browned and vegetables are tender.
Drain off fat.
Stir in undrained tomatoes, tomato paste, brown sugar, oregano, basil, thyme, bay leaf, 2 cups water and 1 teaspoon salt. Bring to a boil; reduce heat.
Simmer, uncovered, for 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until desired consistency, stirring occasionally.
Remove bay leaf.
Serve with spaghetti.
Use grated Parmesan cheese, if desired.
Makes 6 servings.

title: blueberry dessert
directions: Grease 9 X 13 pan.
Layer as listed.
After all layers have finished, bake in preheated oven at 350 degrees for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften cheese in bowl.
Add fried
crunched bacon.
Add next 3 ingredients; mix well.
Form into
a
ball.
Serve with crackers. Great for parties or snacks.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Blend in flour and vanilla. Carefully fold in potato chips.
Add pecans.
Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes just until barely browned.
Dust with confectioners sugar if desired.

title: caramel corn
directions: Boil the sugar, margarine and corn syrup for 5 minutes.
Add cream of tartar.
Pour over popcorn.
Place on baking sheet; bake at 225° for an hour.

title: enchiladas
directions: Heat soup, sour cream and chilies.
Spread part of the mixture over the bottom of pan.
Fill tortillas with cheese, onions and a little of the sauce.
(May add chopped chicken.)
Roll up and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° until sauce bubbles.

title: kentucky ham
directions: Place ham in shallow pan. Drain juice from sliced pineapple. Mix juice, brown sugar and mustard in saucepan. Cook over low heat to boil. Allow to boil until it thickens.
Place sliced pineapple on top of ham.
Pour 1/2 of the juice over ham.
Bake 45 minutes at 325°.
Pour remaining juice over ham. Bake another 30 minutes or so until done.

title: javon's fudge pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add melted margarine.
Blend well.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix well.
Spread in unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Cool.
Top with whipped cream.
"Enjoy!" So easy!

title: baked "stuff-it" potatoes
directions: Cut a thin slice from a potato.
Scoop out potato, leaving a thin shell.
In a small bowl, combine potato, cheese, milk, butter, egg, salt and pepper; mash until smooth.
Spoon potato mixture into shell; sprinkle with paprika.
In an 8-inch square microwave dish, arrange potatoes in a circle.
Cover with waxed paper.
Cook in microwave at Medium power for 4 to 6 minutes.
Let stand, uncovered, for 3 minutes before serving.

title: sausage cheese bites
directions: Cook and crumble sausage.
Drain.
In a large bowl, combine biscuit mix and cheese.
Add the sausage and stir until well blended.
Stir in water just until mixed.
Shape into 1 1/2-inch balls.
Place on greased baking sheets.
Bake at 375° for about 15 minutes or until golden.
These may be frozen.
Yield:
4 dozen.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Combine above ingredients together and Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350 degrees.

title: chicken tostados
directions: In shallow casserole dish, combine Lawry's chicken seasoning packet (follow directions on back) with a package of chicken breasts.
(Do not need to marinate.)
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until no longer pink inside.
(I do this the night before so that dinner the following night is quick and easy.) Refrigerate when cool.

title: peanut butter brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: celery casserole
directions: Melt 2 tablespoons margarine and cook celery until tender, about 15 minutes.
Stir in milk, soup and pimento.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Melt 1 tablespoon margarine and toss with cracker crumbs.
Pour over top.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: preston's cream cheese
directions: In
a
shallow
dish, place cream cheese and cover with the cheesecloth.
Make
a
tight fit.
Pour the wine over the cream cheese,
leaving
a
small
amount on the bottom of the dish.
Let chill
several days until the wine penetrates some of the cheese. Remove cloth and serve with crackers.

title: lettuce with hot bacon dressing
directions: In a skillet, cook bacon until crisp.
Remove the bacon and crumble.
Set aside.
Drain, reserving 1/4 cup drippings.
In a large bowl, combine greens, eggs, onion and bacon.
Add remaining ingredients to drippings and bring to a boil. Drizzle over the salad and toss to coat greens. Serve immediately.

title: million dollar pound cake
directions: Cream butter until fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time and beat well.
Add powdered sugar and beat.
Add flour one cup at a time. Beat until smooth after each cup.
Add flavor.
Cook at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: everlasting cole slaw
directions: Shred cabbage finely; chop onion.
Grate carrot and celery. Add sugar and set aside.
In saucepan, put vinegar, oil, mustard, celery seed and salt.
Stir to a full boil.
Pour boiling liquid over top of dry ingredients and let set for 24 hours.
Excellent and keeps very well.

title: punch
directions: Mix in a gallon container and fill the rest of the container with water.

title: rhubarb-strawberry jelly
directions: Cook and sweeten rhubarb to taste.
Add the Jell-O.
Cook 5 minutes.
Add strawberries, if desired.

title: twice-baked potato puffs
directions: About 2 1/2 hours before serving, bake potatoes in 450° oven for 1 1/2 hours or until fork-tender.
Allow potatoes to cool until easy to handle.

title: layers casserole
directions: Break up meat in a 2-quart baking dish.
Put carrots on meat, then celery and so on.
Bake at 300° for 2 hours.

title: alpine chicken casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except nuts.
Spoon into 2-quart casserole; sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: mock lasagna
directions: Brown meat; drain off fat.
Layer all ingredients, starting with macaroni.
End with cheese on top.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes, or until bubbly.

title: brownies chocolate mousse crunch
directions: Bake brownies according to directions.
Let cool.

title: wine butter seafood sauce
directions: Slowly melt
butter and add remaining ingredients.
Use with shrimp, fish fillets and lobster.

title: peach pie
directions: Cream sugar, butter and flour; add well beaten eggs.
Line the pie shell with sliced peaches.
Pour mixture over.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until firm.

title: salsa
directions: If chunky salsa is preferred, dice tomatoes bite size.
Dice onion, green chiles and jalapenos and add to taste.
Add spices to taste.
Fresh cilantro may be added or dried coriander.
Mix all ingredients well.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: taco stew
directions: Brown beef. Drain and rinse. Combine all ingredients except chips and cheese. Simmer on low until all is warmed. Crumble chips and place in bottom of each bowl. Cover chips with "stew", then sprinkle with cheese.

title: scallop rice cheese casserole
directions: Brown onions in butter.
Add salt, sour cream, Worcestershire sauce, mushrooms and scallops.
Cook until heated through.
Place rice in buttered 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Pour heated scallop mixture over rice.
Top with cheese and cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts.

title: ron's recipe for baked trout or other whitefish(snapper, ling cod, cabezone, bass)
directions: Heat butter, lemon juice and white wine to a liquid.
Combine with onion and spices.

title: yellow squash casserole
directions: Mix
all ingredients except butter and cheese, place in 1 1/2 quart
baking dish (buttered).
Dot with the butter and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake in 350° oven until brown, about 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix well and bake in unbaked pie shell.
Bake until done.

title: doughnuts
directions: Measure potatoes into large bowl.
Add sugar; mix well.
Blend in eggs and shortening; mix well.
Add flour, baking powder and salt.
Add buttermilk, soda, vanilla and cinnamon.
Mix.
Cover and let stand 15 minutes.
Roll 1/4 inch thick and cut.
Fry in deep fat.

title: tawny pumpkin pie
directions: Combine pumpkin, sugar, salt, spices and flour in bowl; mix together.
Add eggs; mix well.

title: pudding brownies
directions: Cook pudding according to package directions.
Let cool 5 minutes.
Add dry cake mix.
Mix together.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake.
After baking, remove from oven and sprinkle with chocolate chips and chopped nuts.

title: dublin potato salad
directions: Combine vinegar, celery seed and mustard seed; set aside. Meanwhile, pare and cook potatoes in enough boiling, salted water to cover for 30 to 40 minutes until done.
Drain and cube.
While potato cubes are still warm, drizzle with the vinegar mixture. Sprinkle with sugar and the first 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Chill thoroughly.

title: bohemian sisky
directions: Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water. Add 2 c. of flour to milk that has been scalded and cooled to lukewarm, add salt, sugar and butter, mix in dissolved yeast, stir well and allow to stand in warm place covered until light and spongy. About 1 hour. Add egg yolks, vanilla and the remainder of the flour, mixing until thoroughly blended. Set to rise covered and in a warm

place, until double in bulk, about 2 hours. Then roll out on lightly floured board to 1/2 inch thick. Cut with doughnut cutter and let rise on board about 30 minutes before frying. Fry in hot fat at 370° with raised side down first. Then turn and fry until golden brown and done. Sprinkle with sugar after draining on crumpled paper or frost with powdered sugar frosting.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine sugar and
eggs.
Stir by hand until well mixed.
Then, add the next 3 ingredients; mix well by hand.
Add vanilla.
Pour into uncooked pie shells and bake for 45 minutes.
This recipe makes 2 pies.

title: yeast bread
directions: Combine; stir or mix until smooth.
Work in 2 cups flour. Knead until smooth (as a baby's bottom).
Let rise 1 hour, until doubled in size.
Punch down.
Shape into whatever.
Let rise 30 minutes.
Bake at 350°.
Three loaves, 30 minutes.
Cinnamon rolls, 12 to 15 minutes.
Orange Danish, 12 to 15 minutes.
Dinner Roll, 12 minutes (use soup can to cut).
Hamburger Bun, 15 minutes (use vegetable can to cut).
Oversized Bun 15 to 17 minutes (use large tuna can to cut).

title: wilted lettuce salad
directions: In large skillet over medium heat fry bacon until crisp. Remove bacon; drain on paper towels.
Reserve 3 tablespoons bacon drippings in skillet.
Add onions; saute until crisp-tender.
Stir in sugar, flour and salt; blend well.
Cook until mixture is smooth and bubbly; stirring constantly.
Gradually add water and vinegar; bring to a boil.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Add lettuce; toss just until leaves are coated and slightly wilted. Spoon into serving dish.
Sprinkle with cooked bacon and chopped egg.
Serve immediately.
Yields 8 servings.

title: sweet and sour chicken wings
directions: In a large saucepan, place chicken wings.
Add water to cover. Cover.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Drain.
Reserve 1/2 cup broth.

title: magnificent mushroom spread
directions: In large skillet, saute mushrooms in butter for 3 to 5 minutes.
Combine onion, mayonnaise, bacon, seasoned salt and mushrooms.
Spread in flat ovenproof dish.
Cover with Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Spread on cocktail rye rounds or crackers.
This may be assembled up to 2 days ahead.

title: butterscotch cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (325° for glass dish).
In medium saucepan, melt morsels and margarine.
Stir in crumbs and nuts. Press half
of mixture firmly onto bottom of greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Put all in casserole dish. Mix 1 cube butter or oleo with 1 tube of Ritz crackers. Spread on top. Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Melt marshmallows.
Add milk, crumbled vanilla wafers, cherries, nuts and coconut.
Pack in dish.
Chill.

title: coca cola pork chops
directions: Mix ketchup and Coca-Cola and pour over pork chops.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.

title: lazy day lasagna
directions: Cook noodles as directed on box.
Brown meat; add sauce.
Beat egg.
Add cottage cheese.
Add Mozzarella.
Put 2 noodles in bottom of pan.
Pour meat sauce over.
Repeat 2 times.

title: cheesy baked chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large shallow bowl, combine the cracker crumbs, sesame seed, parsley, salt, pepper and cayenne pepper.
Dip chicken in melted butter, then dip in cracker crumb mixture.
Place chicken in a baking pan that has been coated with nonstick spray and bake for about 30 minutes until chicken is golden and no pink remains.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Use 9 x 13-inch casserole dish and layer uncooked rice, 1 package onion soup mix, chicken breasts (cut in cubes), cream of mushroom soup (spread on top), 1 package onion soup mix and chicken broth.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, 1/2 hour and then bake, covered, 1/2 hour.

title: beat-n-eat frosting
directions: Stir all ingredients together, except boiling water.
Add boiling water.
Beat with mixer on high until stiff peaks form.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Cook chicken with onion, celery and carrot in water until done.
Mix soups, broth and mushrooms together.
Add 1/2 of this to stuffing mix.
Put in baking dish; lay chicken on top and pour remaining soup mixture on top.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: high fiber loaf
directions: Mix dry ingredients in large bowl.
Add oil, eggs and vanilla. Mix in remaining ingredients.
Pour into 2 greased loaf pans. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: peanut clusters
directions: Melt morsels together in a double boiler over water or microwave butterscotch, 1 cup at a time on Medium-high 1 minute. Stir. Continue at 10 to 20 second intervals.
Stir each time until smooth. Same way for chocolate only on High. Stir together with nuts until coated.
Drop by teaspoonful onto wax paper to cool and harden.

title: arkansas rice pudding
directions: In a large bowl, combine sugar, salt and flour; mix well. Then add cream, vanilla, brown sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg, butter, eggs and rice.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: lunch in skillet
directions: In a large skillet, over medium heat, cook bacon until crisp. Put on paper towels to drain.
Pour off all but 3 tablespoons of drippings.
Add potatoes and onions.
Cook, stirring occasionally, until potatoes brown, about 5 minutes.
Beat eggs with water, salt and dill.
Stir in bacon.
Pour over potato mixture in skillet. Cook, stirring occasionally, until eggs are cooked, but still moist.
Makes 6 servings.

title: oyster fritters
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients with oysters and some juice.
In electric skillet or pan with hot grease, fry until golden brown. Make single fry or as a fritter.

title: baked sausage and eggs
directions: Cook
sausage
according
to package directions.
Drain off fat;
set aside.
In a medium bowl toss Cheddar cheese and flour. Place in an ungreased 1 1/2 quart shallow round baking dish. Evenly
sprinkle
with
Jack
cheese.
In a medium bowl beat eggs, half
and half and Worcestershire sauce until well blended.
Pour over cheese.
Arrange sausages in spoke fashion on top.
Cover and refrigerate up to 24 hours.

title: unbaked cookies
directions: Mix oatmeal, pecans and salt in large bowl.
Cook butter, milk, sugar, cocoa and pecans together for 3 minutes.
Add vanilla.
Mix oatmeal with butter mixture in a hurry!
Drop on wax paper before mixture cools.
Refrigerate, ready to eat when completely cool.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Blend sugar and shortening.
Add eggs one at a time. Alternate with flour with salt stirred in.
Stir in flavoring. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cheese soup
directions: Mix ingredients in saucepan.
Simmer until cheese is melted.

title: rum cake
directions: Grease 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan with a small amount of unsalted margarine; sprinkle with 1 tablespoon sugar.
Spread chopped pecans in the bottom of the pan.
Set aside.

title: chinese chicken salad
directions: Combine vinegar, sugar and soy sauce in a small microwave cup. Heat 30 seconds, stir; heat another 20 seconds, stir repeating process until sugar is dissolved. Set aside to cool; when cool, add olive oil.

title: hawaiian cake
directions: Prepare cake mix and bake on greased cookie sheet (with sides) for 15 minutes at 350°.
Mix pudding with 1 cup milk and softened cream cheese.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Mix 1/2 cup drained pineapple with the pudding mixture and spread on cake.
Sprinkle the rest of the pineapple on cake with nuts and cherries.
Refrigerate.

title: apple yam delight
directions: Take half the jar of applesauce and spread bottom of pan. Sprinkle with 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Put 6 tablespoons of topping over applesauce.
Arrange yams evenly over applesauce.
Add remaining applesauce and cinnamon.
Add the rest of the topping and spread evenly.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: carolyn's mustard chicken
directions: Combine mustard, salt, pepper and water.
In another bowl, combine crumbs, flour and paprika.
Line shallow pan with foil and spray with cooking spray.
Dip chicken in mustard, then in bread crumbs.
Pour butter on top and sprinkle with lemon pepper. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: peanut butter delights
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa, milk, butter and salt.
Cook 3 minutes over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter, oats and vanilla.
Drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper to cool.
Makes 30 pieces.

title: jan's peanut brittle
directions: Cook over medium heat sugar, water, Karo, margarine and peanuts, stirring most
of	the time until temperature reaches hard crack stage (310°).
Stir constantly from about hard ball stage on.
Mixture gets
thick and brown.
Will scorch easily. You may need
to
try
different temperatures because altitude will make a difference.	(You
may
need to cook beyond 310°.) Remove from heat.	Add soda and vanilla.
Stir well.
(Mixture will turn olive drab	green.)
Pour
out
onto buttered cookie sheet.
Let set about 1 hour before breaking apart.
Best left uncovered when possible;
gets sticky in a container.

title: cabbage stew
directions: Brown meat with peppers and onion; drain.
Cook cabbage in a large pan for about 15 minutes, then add remaining ingredients and cook for about an hour.

title: mints
directions: Cream the cream cheese.
Add sugar and flavoring.
Work into a stiff dough.
Add green food coloring to tint, if desired.
Roll 1/2 teaspoon into a ball.
Dip into granulated sugar.
Press into a mold, then pop out.
Continue until all dough has been molded.

title: coconut candy balls
directions: Mix sugar with coconut
in a large bowl.
Add oleo, Eagle Brand milk and vanilla.
Mix together and add nuts.
Make balls with a cherry in the middle.
Makes about 80 balls or less.
Cut paraffin in small pieces in a double boiler.
Add chocolate chips and melt together.
Dip balls in melted chocolate mixture and place on waxed paper.

title: lemon angel torte
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake in a 12 inch x 15 inch greased pan at 275° for 1 hour.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix together and sift.
Store in jars.
Fill cup half full of mix and finish filling with hot water.
Makes a nice gift.

title: tortilla and chili roll
directions: Mix ingredients except for the tortillas.
Spread mix thinly on the flour tortilla; roll the tortilla tightly.
Wrap and chill. When ready to serve, slice into bite size slices.

title: e z stroganoff
directions: Brown beef; drain.
Turn heat to low and add soup mixes and enough water to keep mixture from sticking, but not soupy.
Simmer 10 to 30 minutes.
Add mushrooms.
Remove from heat and add sour cream.
Serve over noodles or rice.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Mix all ingredients, then mix with mayonnaise.
Refrigerate. Serve.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Season chicken breasts to taste.
Cut into bite size pieces. Heat oil (margarine) in Dutch oven.
Chop onion; saute in oil. Brown chicken slightly.
Add water to just cover chicken.
Cook over medium fire; bring to a boil.
Drop in bouillon cubes.
Add about 1 to 1 1/2 cups of water.
Bring to boil again.
Add uncooked rice; return to boil.
Lower heat to medium-low.
Cover Dutch oven and cook until rice is done (about 15 to 20 minutes).

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Boil zucchini until tender.
Melt butter and saute onions. Mix together onions, carrots, sour cream, soup, 1/2 of the zucchini and stuffing.
Put 1/2 zucchini on bottom of casserole dish.
Put remaining mixture on top of zucchini.
Bake at 350° about 45 minutes.

title: cheeseburger casserole
directions: In skillet, brown ground beef and onion.
Drain grease off. Add tomato sauce, ketchup and pepper to beef mixture.
Pour mixture into a casserole dish.
Top with slices of cheese and then the biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cheesy chicken chimichangas
directions: Saute onion and garlic in oil.
Add chicken. Stir in 1 cup of cheese. Set aside.
Separate rolls into 8 rectangles (seal perforations). Spread 1 tablespoon of salsa on each rectangle to within 1/2-inch of edge.
Spoon 1/3 cup of chicken mixture on half of the rectangle. Starting at end with chicken, roll up, pinching edges to seal.
Place seam side down on parchment lined cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 16 to 21 minutes. Remove. Top each with remaining cheese.
Return to oven to melt cheese. Serve with sour cream and salsa.

title: potato salad
directions: Wash potatoes.
Heat 1-inch salted water (1/2 teaspoon salt to 1 cup water) to boiling.
Add unpared potatoes; cover tightly. Heat to boiling and cook 30 to 35 minutes or until tender; drain, cool and peel.
Cut potatoes into cubes and combine in bowl with onion.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Mix with Italian salad dressing; cover.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours (overnight tastes even better).
Just before serving, add mayonnaise; toss until potatoes are well coated.
Stir in celery and eggs.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: world's best cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream the margarine and sugars until fluffy.
Add egg and mix.
Add oil and vanilla; mix.
Add oatmeal, cereal, coconut and nuts; stir well (low speed on mixer). Add flour and soda; mix well.
Mixture will be very thick.
Form small balls; place on ungreased cookie sheets.
Flatten with fork which has been dipped in water.
Bake for 12 minutes.
Cool on sheet.
Makes 5 to 6 dozen.

title: chicken and broccoli
directions: Coat chicken breast with soy sauce and garlic.
Marinate at room temperature for 20 to 30 minutes.
Cut broccoli into bite size pieces.
In wok or large skillet, heat oil.
Add broccoli; stir-fry for 2 minutes.
Add chicken and marinade.
Stir-fry until all meat turns white.
Stir cornstarch and water.
Add to wok; stir until thickens like gravy.
Serve with rice.

title: hot mulled punch
directions: Put sugar and spices in basket of coffee maker.
Perk juices through one cycle in 30 to 36-cup coffee maker.
Serve hot. Yields 40 punch cups.

title: swedish meat balls
directions: Combine ground beef, soy sauce, garlic powder, onions, eggs, pepper and ketchup and roll into small balls.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.
While these are baking, combine in a slow cooker:
cranberry sauce, lemon juice, brown sugar and chili sauce.
Place balls into sauce and simmer.
Set cooker on low. The longer the meat balls stay in the sauce, the better they will be.
I cook mine about 1 hour (or less).
They are good reheated. Serve over spaghetti or rice.

title: 3 hole chocolate cake
directions: Melt unsweetened chocolate.
Mix flour, sugar, salt and baking soda.
Make three holes.
Pour into holes the water, oil, cider vinegar and melted chocolate.
Mix with either spoon or electric mixer.

title: night before casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover and let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Uncover and bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
Tastes like chicken pie.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: seafoam candy
directions: Blend sugar, water and syrup until it spins a thread (approximately 280°).
Pour slowly over egg whites on high speed using an electric mixer.
Pour in nuts and flavorings.
Drop on wax paper and let cool.

title: german slaw
directions: Pour over cabbage and stir.
Refrigerate 4 to 6 hours.
Will keep for 1 month.

title: sugared pecans
directions: Beat 2 egg whites (at room temperature) until foamy. Add 1 cup sugar, 1 tablespoon at a time. Beat until stiff. Fold in 4 cups pecans. Melt 1 stick butter in bottom of oblong pan. Spread pecan mixture over this. Bake at 300° to 325° for 30 minutes, stirring every 10 minutes. Spread over wax paper to cool.

title: mom's fruit cake
directions: Place raisins, dates, sugar, water and shortening in saucepan and simmer for 20 minutes until thick.
Set aside until cool. Sift flour, soda, cloves, cinnamon and salt together.
Mix into cool mixture.
Stir in cherries, pineapple and nuts.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
When cool, wrap in cheesecloth saturated with red wine.
Every 3 to 5 days, unwrap and saturate cheesecloth again.
Re-wrap for 3 weeks.
Wrap with foil to keep moist.

title: heath bars
directions: Melt the butter and sugar in a heavy skillet until golden brown.
Add the cream of tartar as you remove the carameled mixture from the stove.
Pour on a flat-greased cookie sheet. Cover with the Hershey bars.
Cool completely and cut into bars.

title: london broil
directions: Score a London broil with fork on both sides.
Rub with 1/2 cup sugar on both sides.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Marinate meat in the marinade at least 1/2 hour.
Broil or cook on grill about 1/2 hour or until done to your liking.
Heat the remaining marinade to a boil and serve with the meat at the table.

title: tamale corn pie
directions: Use a 13 x 8-inch casserole dish, sprayed with "Pam." Open hot tamales, drain juice and remove from paper.
Cut tamales into 3 parts and arrange on bottom of dish.

title: grandma worsley's spice cake(ca 1930's)
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Beat well.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake until done.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Combine all in double boiler and melt. This is good to put over brownies or chocolate or white cake.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs.
Stir in zucchini, oil, sugar and vanilla.
Stir other ingredients into separate bowl, then add to zucchini mixture.
Blend well.
Pour into two greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook and drain spinach; mix sour cream and onion soup.
Toss it with spinach.
Mix well.
Put in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Melt the margarine; add bread crumbs and cheese.
Put on top. Bake in 325° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: stuffed zucchini
directions: Remove the center core of the cabbage.
Place it in a pan of boiling water and continue boiling until the cabbage is soft. Drain off the hot water into another pot, but save it for later.

title: triple chocolate vanilla cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine crumbs and margarine; press firmly on bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.
In large mixer bowl, beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in Eagle Brand until smooth.
Add eggs, flour and vanilla; mix well.
Divide batter in half.
Add chocolate to 1/2 of batter; mix well.
Pour into pan; top evenly with vanilla batter.
Bake 50 to 55 minutes or until cake springs back when lightly touched.
Cool.
Top with Chocolate Glaze.
Chill thoroughly.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: peach ice cream
directions: Peel peaches and set aside.
Mix all ingredients except peaches and stir until sugar is dissolved.
Squeeze in peeled peaches.
Churn until frozen.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: spinach stuffed pasta shells
directions: Preheat oven
to
Cook pasta shells according to package directions, omitting salt.	Mix remaining ingredients. Fill each
shell
with
mix, about 1 tablespoon per shell, and place in
baking
dish
lined with some sauce.
After stuffing shells, pour
remaining
sauce
over shells.
May garnish with grated Parmesan cheese.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes.

title: quick baked tamale
directions: Brown meat and
drain.
Add
seasonings
and onions and add corn and tomatoes.
Bring to boil. Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Spread cornbread
topping
over
meat
mixture.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes.

title: gourmet chicken casserole
directions: Cook rice according to package directions.
Saute onions in oleo; add soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and Worcestershire sauce. Heat and stir until smooth.
Gently fold in cooked rice, chicken, water chestnuts, mushrooms and pimento.
Spoon into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese and paprika and bake 5 more minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: l. g. t. pie crust(makes 2 crusts - 9-inch size)
directions: Mix egg and water.
Mix all and refrigerate overnight.

title: strawberry dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and Marshmallow Fluff together.

title: wassail
directions: Place the first four ingredients into large automatic percolator.
Place remaining ingredients into basket.
Allow to go through cycle; serve hot.

title: chutney
directions: Cook to a boil, then simmer for 5 minutes.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Cook chicken breasts until tender.
Cut into pieces.
Cook broccoli for 5 minutes; drain.
Put broccoli and chicken in 2-quart baking dish.

title: marshmallow brownies
directions: Prepare brownies according to package directions.
Bake.
Let cool for 5 minutes.
Put jar of Marshmallow Fluff on brownies and spread to cover.
Drop 3 to 4 tablespoons of chocolate frosting on Fluff and swirl.
Sprinkle with pecans on top.

title: microwave broccoli-pecan
directions: In a microwaveable 3 qt. casserole dish, combine the broccoli, water chestnuts, onion salt, and orange peel.
Dot with butter.
Microwave on high for 6-8 minutes or until the broccoli is crisp-tender.
Stir in the pecans before serving.
Serves 4.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together except American cheese and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Place cheese slices on top and put back in oven for 10 minutes to melt cheese.

title: mock whipped cream frosting
directions: Whip butter and shortening until fluffy.
Add sugar gradually. Add flour at low speed.
Turn speed to high; beat, return speed to low.
Add milk and vanilla.
Beat on high for 5 to 10 minutes.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes; cool, peel and cut in 1-inch thick slices.
Pare and core apples and slice into 1/2-inch rings.
Arrange potatoes and apples in alternating layers in greased baking dish.
Mix honey, salt and cinnamon; sprinkle part of mixture and lemon juice over each layer.
Dot with butter and water.
Cover and bake at 375° for 35 minutes.
Remove cover; cool about 10 minutes.
Yields 6 portions.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Crumble the crackers.
Melt butter and Cheez Whiz in large casserole dish.
Stir until smooth.
Add the Veg-All.
Stir until well mixed.
Spread crumbs on top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: icebox wafers
directions: Cream together cheese, butter, salt and pepper.
Add flour; form into roll or log.
Wrap in wax paper and put in the freezer.

title: creamed spinach
directions: Cook spinach according to directions, adding salt and onion to water.
Drain.
Add softened cream cheese and mix well.
Add salt and pepper.
Pour into greased casserole.
Sprinkle with crumbs, and then Parmesan cheese.
Dot with butter.
Bake in a 350° oven until bubbly and browned.
Serves 8.

title: mamaw's mexican cornbread
directions: Mix dry ingredients. Stir in corn, grated cheese, onions and peppers. Blend well. Stir in buttermilk, eggs and oil. Bake in greased 10 x 13 pan or iron skillet at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes or until firm and brown. Serve hot or cold.

title: jello salad
directions: Prepare lime Jell-O,
chill
until almost set.
Add all ingredients except
marshmallows.
After folding in all ingredients, add marshmallows.
Chill until set.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Cut cookie dough into slices 1/8-inch thick.
Line ungreased 14-inch pizza pan with slices, overlapping slightly.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.
Cool.

title: swiss chicken
directions: Place chicken in baking dish.
Salt and pepper lightly.
Place slices of cheese over chicken.
Mix soup and 1/4 cup water.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle dry stuffing into dish.
Melt butter. Pour on top.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: goulash
directions: Steam a little chopped onion in small amount of cooking oil. Brown ground beef; add vegetables, corn, spaghetti, tomato soup, chili powder, salt and pepper; add bell pepper and simmer 20 minutes.

title: orange freeze
directions: Mix together 1/2 cup orange juice and 1 cup orange sherbet. Blend together in blender and serve with straw.

title: molded cucumber salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Add vinegar, cold water and onion.
Let partially set and then blend in mayonnaise, sour cream and grated cucumbers.
Place in ring mold to set.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Mix Jell-O according to package.
Put in refrigerator until it starts to congeal.
Drain the pineapple; save the juice to use later.
Add pineapple to slightly congealed Jell-O and return to the refrigerator to congeal.
Mix Dream Whip according to directions on package; add cream cheese.
Spread this on congealed Jell-O; return to refrigerator.
Mix sugar and flour.
Beat egg slightly and add to sugar and flour along with the pineapple and lemon juice.
Cook over medium heat, stirring until it becomes thick; let cool.
Spread this on the top and sprinkle with pecans.

title: shrimp tofu puffs
directions: Clean shrimp and put through blender.
Drain tofu well and mix with shrimp and remaining ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonful into deep oil until puffed and golden brown.
Drain. Serve or use as a garnish.

title: fish chowder
directions: Dice the fish in small pieces and cook in salted water with the potatoes and onions until cooked.
Leave in the water, add canned milk and season with butter and pepper.

title: green bean and onion salad
directions: Cook green beans until done, but still firm. Drain. Add onions, salt, pepper, oil and vinegar. Toss. Serve at room temperature or chilled.

title: indian corn slaw
directions: In a 6-quart Dutch oven, heat the oil over moderately high heat.
Add the beef and cook, stirring frequently, for 8 minutes or until browned.
Lower heat; stir in green pepper, onion and garlic and simmer, uncovered, for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in tomatoes, corn, Worcestershire, pepper, chili powder and cayenne and bring to boil.
Lower the heat; cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Add the squash; simmer 5 minutes longer or until vegetables are tender.
Any extras may be frozen up to a month.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chocolate chip oatmeal cake
directions: Pour water over oatmeal and let stand 10 minutes.
Add sugar and oleo; stir until oleo melts.
Add eggs and mix.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add and mix.
Add half of the chocolate chips to batter and pour into pan.
Sprinkle rest of chocolate chips on top. Bake at 325° to 350° for 30 minutes or less.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients, except catsup; mix slightly.
Pat thoroughly, shape meat mixture into loaf pan.
Bake in moderate oven about 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Pour catsup over top and bake until done.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Boil chicken in 8 cups of water.
Dice into small bite-size pieces (save broth).
Spray 9 x 13-inch baking dish with Pam. Place dressing mix in casserole dish.
Moisten with chicken broth. Layer chicken over dressing.
Mix soups with 3/4 can of chicken broth and pour over chicken and dressing, making sure all chicken is covered.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: zucchini-carrot squares *
directions: Sprinkle zucchini with salt.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Squeeze out liquid.
Saute onions in oil until soft.
Remove from heat and combine with remaining ingredients, except margarine.
Put into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Dot top with margarine before baking.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for 1 hour.
Cover during last 15 minutes.
Cut into squares.
Serve hot.
Yield:
12 to 15 squares.

title: crab bacon roll
directions: Mix tomato juice and egg.
Add crab, bread crumbs, parsley, lemon juice, salt, Worcestershire sauce and pepper.
Mix thoroughly.
Roll into 18 fingers.
Wrap each roll with 1/2 slice bacon; fasten with wooden toothpicks.
Broil for about 10 minutes, turning often to brown evenly.
Serve hot.

title: tasty green beans
directions: Dissolve cube in 1/2 cup water in saucepan.
Add beans and simmer until tender.
Add pepper.
Serves 6.
Good for diets, no fat.

title: salmon fritters
