directions: Mix all together and drop by spoonful in buttered frying pan. Brown both sides and serve hot.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Cut peppers in half lengthwise. Remove seeds and wash. Combine beef, cooked rice, onions, salt, pepper and 1/2 can tomato sauce. Pile mixture into peppers in large baking dish. Pour sauce over each pepper. Cover tightly and bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours, basting occasionally.

title: mom's potato soup
directions: Peel and cube potatoes; cook with onion and bacon pieces in water. When done, mash ingredients. Do not pour off liquid as this retains valuable flavor and vitamins.
Add milk and stir in butter, salt and pepper to taste. Heat thoroughly, but do not boil, as this may cause milk to curdle.
Serves 4.

title: creamy banana pudding
directions: In a large bowl combine milk and water.
Add pudding mix and beat well.
Chill for 5 minutes.
Fold whipping cream into pudding mix after it has chilled and set.

title: mt. washington hot bread
directions: Combine sugar, egg and shortening.
Mix well.
Combine dry ingredients.
Beat two together, adding the milk as you beat. Bake in a "moderate oven" for about 30 minutes.

title: raspberry jello salad
directions: Dissolve raspberry and lemon-flavored gelatins in boiling water.
Stir in frozen raspberries, breaking up large pieces with fork.
Stir in cranberry-orange relish.
Slowly pour in lemon-lime beverage.
Stir gently and pour into a 6 1/2 cup mold.

title: rocky road brownie squares
directions: Beat margarine at medium speed with an electric mixer until creamy.
Gradually add sugar, beating well.
Add egg whites, beating until blended.
Stir in vanilla.
Combine flour and cocoa. Add to margarine mixture, stirring until blended.
Stir in marshmallows.
Spoon batter into an 8-inch square pan coated with cooking spray.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
(Do not overbake.)
Sprinkle with chocolate morsels and cool completely on a wire rack.
Cut into 9 squares.
Combine caramels and water in a small, heavy-duty zip top plastic bag.
Seal bag.
Microwave at Medium-high 45 seconds or until caramels melt.
Knead bag to blend caramels and water.
Snip a tiny hole in corner of bag.
Drizzle mixture over brownies.
Yield:
9 brownies; 197 calories/brownie, 6.8 g of fat/brownie, 0 mg cholesterol and 82 mg sodium.

title: on the wing - chicken wings
directions: Mix first 6 of ingredients in medium bowl.
Add chicken and toss to coat evenly.
Heat 2 teaspoons vegetable oil in roasting pan in oven for 5 minutes.
Add chicken and bake 40 minutes, turning wings after 20 minutes.

title: chicken alovette
directions: Unfold pastry.
Roll each sheet into a 14 x 12-inch rectangle on a lightly floured surface.
Cut sheets of pastry into 7 x 6-inch rectangles, then cut edges off to make a circle.
Spread Allovette cheese evenly over the pastry.
Sprinkle chicken breasts with salt and pepper.
Lightly moisten pastry edges with water.
Fold ends over chicken.
Fold sides over and press to seal.
Place seam side down on a lightly greased baking sheet.

title: broccoli salad supreme
directions: Toss together veggies, bacon, nuts and grapes.
Mix sugar, mayonnaise and vinegar for dressing.
Pour dressing over mixture and stir gently.
Refrigerate overnight or several hours for flavors to mix.

title: corn cornbread
directions: Bake in a dish at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: french apple pie
directions: Mix cinnamon and 2 Tbsp. flour, toss with apples.
Put in pie shell. Sprinkle with small amount of water.
Mix together butter, brown sugar, and flour till crumbly.
Place on top of apples.

title: creamy shake
directions: Cake Toppings:
Frost cakes with fruit pudding, softened cream cheese, jam or spread and spoon on topping.

title: crescent desserts
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In a small bowl, blend cream cheese and powdered sugar until smooth; stir in pineapple, walnuts, orange peel and vanilla.
Separate dough into eight triangles.
Place each triangle in ungreased muffin cup; press dough to cover bottom and sides, forming a 1/4-inch rim.
Spoon 1 teaspoon coconut into each cup.
Spoon 1 rounded tablespoonful pineapple mixture into each cup.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Remove from oven; sprinkle with remaining coconut.
Return to oven; bake an additional 3 to 8 minutes or until crust is golden brown.
Cool 5 minutes; remove from pans.
Store in refrigerator.
Serves 8.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cream together in a small bowl the butter, sugar and cinnamon.
Roll out biscuits.
Spread cinnamon mixture on biscuits.
Roll up and place on greased pie pans.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes.

title: ham loaf
directions: Mix the ingredients together.
Beat egg whites until stiff. Fold in meat mixture.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Remove grease.

title: nellie's summer supper microwave chicken
directions: Cook chicken breasts with butter in a casserole with lid. Microwave 6 minutes, Full power. Turn and cook 6 more minutes. Discard skins, pull meat off bone and dice.

title: hot dog chili
directions: Combine meat with onion.
Cook until brown.
Drain off any fat.
Add all the ingredients and simmer 1 hour.

title: gourmet potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes with skin on. Blend in butter, cheese, sour cream, onion, salt and pepper. Put in a 2 qt casserole dish. Sprinkle with paprika. Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix first seven ingredients together. In another bowl, mix rest of ingredients, then mix the two together.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch pan and cover with crushed potato chips.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: pam's sunday chicken bake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Wash and dry chicken.
Arrange in shallow baking dish.
Combine seasonings and melted butter; brush over chicken, coating well.
Sprinkle with almonds.
Pour cream around pieces.
Cover dish and bake 45 minutes.
Uncover and bake 10 to 15 minutes or until tender.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chicken and mushroom bake
directions: Dredge chicken in seasoned flour.
Melt butter in a shallow baking pan.
Arrange chicken in pan in a single layer, skin side down.
Bake in a moderate 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: cole slaw
directions: Chop cabbage.
Mix mayonnaise with milk, sugar, salt and pepper.
If thick, add milk to thin out.
Then mix in cabbage.
If you need more mayonnaise or sugar, add to your taste. Refrigerate.

title: potatoes in a packet
directions: Layer potatoes, onions, cheese, and seasoning.
Dot each layer with butter.
Top with cheese.

title: sandwich spread
directions: Grind peppers, green tomatoes and onions.
Drain.
Make paste of sugar, flour, celery seed, salt and vinegar.
Add to first mixture in a large pan.
Bring to a boil.
Add 1 quart of salad dressing and 1 cup French mustard.
Seal hot.

title: chocolate pecan cream cheese pie
directions: Beat together softened cream cheese, 1 egg, 1/4 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon vanilla until smooth.
Spread over bottom of unbaked pie shell.
Sprinkle with pecans.
In medium bowl beat 3 eggs slightly. Mix in Karo, 2 tablespoons sugar and salt.
Stir in melted chocolate and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Pour mixture over pecans.
Bake in preheated 375° oven about 35 minutes or until a knife in center comes out clean.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook spinach; drain well and while hot add cream cheese and 1/2 stick butter.
Mix well and season with salt and pepper.
Put in casserole and cover with dressing.
Pour in other half of butter, melted.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: old fashioned potato candy
directions: Beat potatoes until smooth or use 1 cup instant potatoes (warm).
Beat in sugar and zest.

title: liver skillet supper
directions: In a large skillet, cook bacon until crisp.
Remove to a paper towel to drain; reserve drippings in skillet.
Combine flour and half of the garlic salt, onion salt and pepper.
Cut liver into 2 x 1/2-inch strips.
Dredge in the flour mixture, coating well. Lightly brown liver in drippings.
Add potatoes and onion. Sprinkle with remaining seasonings.
Cook until the potatoes are browned and tender, stirring occasionally.
Crumble bacon over top.
Garnish with green pepper rings, if desired.
Yield: 4 to 6 servings.

title: lemon squares
directions: Combine 2 cups flour, butter and salt with fork into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes.
Cool crust, then pour lemon batter.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Mix chicken, onion, cheese, garlic salt, chili powder and tomatoes. Soften tortillas in boiling chicken stock. Line tortillas in baking dish. Add chicken mixture. Pour contents of 2 cans of soup over mixture. Bake at 350° about 35 minutes or until bubbly and hot.

title: "tasty" gingerbread cookies
directions: Melt butter; add molasses and sugar.
Heat until sugar is dissolved.
Set aside and cool.
(Cookies are good with no cooking, also.)
Blend all dry ingredients together; add to molasses mixture and mix well.

title: squash casserole
directions: Line large casserole with 1/2 stuffing mix and melted butter. Mix squash and other ingredients and pour over stuffing.
Cover with remaining stuffing and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: orange fluff
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together, then add the drained can of mandarin oranges.
Keep in the refrigerator. This is best fixed a day ahead.

title: "flying" fried chicken
directions: You will need a plastic storage bag.

title: pumpkin spice cookies
directions: Mix together; drop by teaspoonful onto cookie sheet.
Bake in a 350° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.
They may be iced.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: turkey stew
directions: Peel and cut up potatoes in large cubes.
Clean and slice carrots; cook both together, then drain all water.
Chop onion, green pepper and garlic; saute until brown in oil.
Chop turkey. Add turkey, green pepper and onion; mix with oil over potatoes and carrots and stir.
Serve.

title: quick caramel frosting
directions: Melt margarine	in
saucepan.
Stir
in brown sugar and salt. Cook 2 minutes over low heat, stirring constantly.	Add 4 tablespoons of milk, stirring constantly until mixture comes to a boil.
Remove
from
heat.	Stir
in gradually 2 1/2 cups confectioners
sugar
and	vanilla.
Enough
for
two
9-inch layers.
This is
especially
good	on Banana Nut Cake or on a yellow cake.

title: salmon-noodle bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350° in 3-quart saucepan.
Heat margarine; stir in flour, salt and mustard until blended.
Stir in milk and cook, stirring constantly, until mixture is thickened.
Remove from heat.
Add undrained salmon, stirring until flaked.
Stir in cheese and noodles.
Pour into
1 1/2-quart casserole and bake 30 minutes until bubbly hot.
Garnish with lime slices and tomatoes.

title: onion bread
directions: Combine onion and hot water.
Set aside.
Generously grease 2 (8 x 5-inch) loaf dishes.
Coat bottom and sides of each dish with fine cornflake crumbs.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Place chicken in casserole dish. Mix together vegetables and soups. Pour over chicken. Mix flour, mayo and milk. Pour on top and cook on 350 degrees for 1 1/2 hours.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Cook water, potatoes, onion, bouillon and broccoli for 20 to 30 minutes until potatoes are tender.
Add cans of soup and cheese.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Serve.
Freezes well.

title: chocolate caramel candy(yield: about 8 dozen)
directions: Combine the first three ingredients in a small saucepan, stir over low heat until melted and smooth.
Spread onto the bottom of a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Refrigerate until set.

title: texas hash
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large skillet, cook and stir meat, onions and green pepper (until meat is brown).
Drain off fat. Stir in other ingredients; heat through.
Pour into ungreased 2-quart casserole.
Cover and bake 1 hour.
Makes 4 servings.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: pizza-homemade
directions: Mix flour, salt, sugar, yeast and warm water until dough is elastic.
Add oil.
Mix flour until dough is stiff.
Rise until double, 1 to 2 hours.

title: taco dip
directions: Brown first three ingredients together and drain off fat. Add Velveeta to beef mixture and stir until cheese is melted. Add remaining ingredients and keep hot in crockpot.

title: tea cakes
directions: Cream shortening.
Add sugar and cream well.
Add eggs, buttermilk and vanilla; mix well.
Gradually add flour until dough forms.
Roll out to 1/2-inch or less thickness and cut with cookie cutter.
Bake at 375° on an insulated cookie sheet for 15 minutes. Cool a few minutes and remove cookies from cookie sheet.
For crisp cookies, use water.
For soft cookies, use buttermilk.

title: crabmeat chef's salad
directions: Drain crabmeat.
Remove remaining shell or cartilage.
Flake the crabmeat.
Cook asparagus spears.
Drain and chill.
Place 3 asparagus spears in each lettuce cup.
Place about 1/3 cup crabmeat on asparagus.
Cover with Lemon-Caper Dressing.
Top with 3 slices hard-boiled egg.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: dilled lemon chicken
directions: Cook chicken breast halves in margarine in 10-inch skillet, turning once until brown, about 5 minutes on each side.
Mix lemon juice, salt and dill weed; pour over chicken.
Place lemon slices on chicken.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat, cover and simmer until chicken is done, 10 to 15 minutes.
Remove chicken; keep warm. Sprinkle onions over chicken and serve.

title: banana punch
directions: Heat water and sugar and boil 5 minutes; let cool.
Mix all ingredients together.
Mash up 5 bananas and add just before serving with 1 bottle ginger ale.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Mix browned meat, onion, beans, Ro-Tel and mushroom soup.
In a greased casserole dish, layer the tortillas (torn in small pieces on the bottom of the dish) and meat mixture.
Bake in 350° oven until bubbly, then add topping of cheese and put back in the oven until the cheese has melted.
Serve hot.
Makes 6 servings.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Saute chopped onion, mushrooms and celery in 3 tablespoons bacon fat for 10 minutes.
Add to this mixture the flour, chili powder, sugar and juice of peas and tomatoes; simmer for 15 minutes, then add and heat the remaining ingredients.
Pour over rice.

title: herb roast chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Cut the chicken in half (or cut up chicken).
Arrange chicken, skin side up, in a roasting pan. Combine butter, lemon juice, oregano, rosemary, sage, salt and black pepper in a small bowl and mix well.
Brush the chicken with the butter mixture.
Roast until juices run clear, about 20 minutes.
Broil 6 inches from heat for 3 minutes.
You can skin the chicken if you prefer.

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: Mix cream cheese, Cheddar cheese and chilies.
Spread mixture evenly on tortillas.
Roll up (they'll resemble flautas or toquitos).
Wrap in plastic wrap or foil for a few hours or overnight.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Wash cranberries and place in cold water in a saucepan. Bring to a boil.
Cook cranberries until they start popping.
Add sugar and boil for 5 minutes.
Pour mixture over dry jellos. Chill until partially set, then add remaining ingredients.
Chill until set.

title: diet soup
directions: Cut vegetables into small pieces.
Combine all ingredients and simmer until tender.

title: bing cherry jello
directions: Bring crushed pineapple with juice to a boil. Add the lemon and cherry jello and dissolve over heat. Remove from heat and add 16 1/2 ounce can Bing cherries and 12 ounces Coke. Can add nuts, if desired. Let gel in the refrigerator.

title: mom jackson's cauliflower salad
directions: Cut all vegetables into small pieces and pour the bottle of dressing over and allow to stand in the refrigerator overnight. This is great with a holiday meal because it is so colorful!
Serve in a clear glass dish so all the colors will show through.

title: 1-2-3-4 cake
directions: Cream shortening.
Add sugar gradually; beat until light.
Add egg yolks; beat thoroughly.
Sift dry ingredients together; add alternately with milk to first mixture.
Stir in nuts and vanilla. Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour batter into 2 square cake pans (8 x 2 1/2-inches deep) and bake at 350° for 40 minutes, or until done.

title: weight watchers meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients into a loaf.
Put a hole in center. Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: sticky buns
directions: Sprinkle pecans in Bundt or streusel pan; arrange rolls over pecans.
Sprinkle pudding mix, brown sugar and cinnamon over rolls.
Drizzle butter over all.
Cover and let sit on counter overnight (at least 6 hours).
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Let sit 5 minutes and then invert on serving plate.

title: nut roll
directions: Crush vanilla wafers; add cut up marshmallows, chopped pecans and can of milk.
Shape into roll.
Wrap in wax paper.
Chill and slice.

title: spinach roll-ups
directions: Mix all ingredients and spread very thinly over tortilla; roll up.
Refrigerate overnight.
Cut into 1 inch pieces before serving.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Add sugar to crumbs.
Add melted butter, coconut and peanut butter.
Mix with hands.
Shape into small balls.
Dip into melted chocolate.

title: butterscotch cream pie
directions: Mix brown sugar, salt and cornstarch in a saucepan.
Add egg yolks, milk, water and butter.
Cook over medium heat until mixture thickens and boils.
Add vanilla.
Pour into 9-inch baked pie crust and top with meringue.
Bake to brown.

title: cole slaw dressing
directions: Mix well and pour over prepared cabbage slaw.

title: whole cranberry sauce
directions: Boil
sugar
and water together, until sugar dissolves. Add rinsed berries and cook over medium heat 15 minutes after mixture starts
to boil.
Cool.
Thickens as it cools.
Makes more than a quart of sauce.

title: cheese cake
directions: Add hot water to the lemon jello and add cream cheese.
Let stand until it gets cold.
May need to put in the refrigerator for a while.
Whip really well.
Add sugar and vanilla to chilled Milnot and whip.
Add Milnot to jello and whip with mixer.
While jello is chilling, roll graham crackers.
Add powdered sugar and melted butter.
Spread 1/2 of the graham cracker mixture in a long baking dish (9 x 13-inch).
Add the jello mixture and put the rest of the graham cracker mixture on top.
Chill before serving.

title: frozen fruit
directions: Heat and dissolve water and sugar.
Let cool.
Add frozen orange juice and 1 can of water.
Add undrained pineapple and diced bananas.
Let strawberries drain while thawing, then add. Stir occasionally while freezing.
Great summer snack!

title: pineapple orange sherbet
directions: Mix well and freeze or churn in ice cream maker.

title: manicotti
directions: Cook shells according to directions.
Mix cheeses with egg and spices. Stuff shells with cheese mixture.
Lay in large baking dish. Heat spaghetti sauce, ground beef and mushrooms. Pour sauce over top.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: aunt leola's apple turnovers
directions: Cook apples in small amount of water until done.
Stir in sugar, margarine and cinnamon, if desired.
Separate and roll out biscuits.
Spoon in apples on 1 side, then turn over and press together.
Fry in Crisco at 350° until brown.
Makes 10 turnovers.

title: chocolate chip cheesecake
directions: Combine crumbs and margarine; press onto bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Combine cream cheese, sugar and flour, mixing at medium speed on mixer until well blended. Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each addition. Blend in sour cream and vanilla. Stir in chocolate pieces; pour over crust. Bake at 325° for 55 minutes. Loosen cake from rim of pan; cool before removing rim of pan. Chill. Garnish with Cool Whip, if desired.

title: angel stuff
directions: Either bake or buy an angel food cake.
Break cake up and layer in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Prepare vanilla pudding according to box directions and pour over cake.
Chill for at least 30 minutes or more.
Mix together sour cream, Cool Whip, crushed pineapple and strawberries.
Pour mixture over cake. Sprinkle with pecans and serve.
No baking!

title: southern raised biscuits
directions: Combine yeast and warm water.
Let set 5 minutes. Add yeast to buttermilk; set aside.
Combine dry ingredients in a large bowl. Cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Add buttermilk mixture, mixing with a fork until dry ingredients are moistened. Turn dough onto floured surface; knead lightly 3 or 4 times.
Roll dough to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut biscuits; place on lightly greased cookie sheet; cover and let rise 1 hour.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Yields about 2 dozen.

title: scalloped cabbage
directions: Core and coarsely chop cabbage.
Place in pan with onion and a little water; cover and steam until tender.
Place in a greased casserole.

title: shrimp de jonghe
directions: To melted butter add next 5 ingredients.
Mix.
Add bread crumbs; mix.
Place shrimp in greased baking dish.
Spoon mixture of bread crumbs over shrimp.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes. Makes 6 to 8 servings.
Bon Appetit!

title: stuffed pumpkin (or winter squash)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Wash pumpkin; cut in half.
Saute pepper, onion, celery and garlic powder in bacon drippings until onion is transparent; remove from pan.
Brown sausage and drain. Add to other ingredients and fill pumpkin cavity.
Bake 1 hour or until fork penetrates the pumpkin easily.
For cooking time, cover with aluminum foil.

title: homemade vanilla ice cream
directions: No cooking, just eggs to beat and milk to measure.

title: easy brownies
directions: Melt cocoa and shortening; beat in sugar and eggs.
Combine dry ingredients and add to above mixture.
Bake in greased 8 x 8-inch pan for 30 minutes.

title: potato salad
directions: Put vegetables in a bowl.
Mix mustard, vinegar and mayonnaise or salad dressing.
Mix gently with the vegetables, salt and pepper.
Slice egg on top of salad.
Makes 2 servings, about 3/4 cup each.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cube zucchini and steam until just barely tender.
Combine eggs, milk, chilies, parsley, cheese, salt and baking powder.
Toss in zucchini and mix well.
Transfer mixture to buttered casserole that has been dusted with half of the bread crumbs.
Then sprinkle the top with remaining bread crumbs and dot with butter.
Bake for 45 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: german corn and mushroom soup
directions: Fry the bacon until crisp and then crumble into pieces.
Fry onion in bacon drippings.
Melt 3 tablespoons butter in heavy skillet.
Dice mushrooms into this and cook for five minutes over low fire.
Put all ingredients into a kettle and heat, stirring constantly.
When very hot, remove from fire.
Put aside to cool and then reheat before serving.
This soup tastes much better if prepared in advance and then reheated.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in 2-quart baking dish.
Mix flour, milk and sugar.
Pour into melted margarine.
Do not stir!
Add drained fruit (peaches, blueberries, apples, etc.).
Again, do not stir! When adding fruit, do so evenly in dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Serve warm with whipped topping.

title: cream of coconut cake
directions: Combine cake mix, egg whites, oil, milk and 1 can of coconut. Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350° in greased sheet cake pan.
Make holes in warm cake with fork and pour cream of coconut over cake.

title: grandma-donna's lemon mustard chicken
directions: Combine 2 tablespoons lemon rind and bread crumbs.
Combine 3 tablespoons of lemon juice, mustard and lime juice.
Melt margarine in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish in oven.
Rinse and dry chicken.
Coat with mustard mixture.
Roll coated chicken in bread crumbs and place in pan, meaty side down.
Bake 20 minutes.
Turn and bake another 20 minutes at 350°.

title: cherry delight
directions: Mix cream cheese and powdered sugar;
add only enough milk to make spreadable mixture.
Fold in whipped cream.
Spread into pie crust.
Top with pie filling.
Chill.

title: apple fritters
directions: Beat all wet ingredients.
Fold in Orange Peel, Salt and Baking Powder.
Fold in Flour, chopped Apples (do not overmix).
Drop by spoonfuls of batter in a 325 degree Oil.
Fry until golden.

title: red onions
directions: In frying pan, heat oil.
Add onions that have been cut in half from top to root and sliced thin into strips.
Cook until onions turn clear.
Add the unsweetened Concord type grape juice and cook until onions take on red color and get tender as desired. Makes 2 "vegetable" servings.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour together; beat egg yolks, and add milk to eggs.
Add milk mixture to dry ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients and cook on low heat until thick.

title: cream of parisian vegetable soup
directions: Cook vegetables in 2 cups water until tender.
Melt oleo and add celery and onion. Saute until onion is slightly clear.
Add flour and stir until well blended. Crush bouillon (you can use instant).
Add half to vegetables and half to onion and celery. Adding milk, stir until smooth and thickened.
Add cooked vegetables (broth and all), ham, pepper, Accent and salt, if desired.

title: bourbon dogs
directions: Combine ingredients; heat for 25 minutes in saucepan.
Makes approximately 50 appetizers.

title: strawberry-nut salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Fold in strawberries with juice, drained pineapple, bananas and nuts.
Turn half of the mixture into a 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish as first layer. Refrigerate until firm.
Evenly spread top with sour cream. Gently spoon on rest of strawberry mixture.
Refrigerate.
Cut into squares and place on lettuce for serving.

title: squaw bread
directions: Mix water, dry yeast, lard, salt and sugar together, then add flour until thick.
Turn out on floured surface.
Knead and work a little more flour into it.
Do not make real stiff.
Make into balls a little bigger than a black plum and stretch it out to about 2 inches thick or less.
Let rise until double in size and fry in hot grease until brown on both sides.
(Good eaten with butter and sometimes roll in sugar.)

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix sugar, eggs, oil and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients, mixing well.
Add apples and nuts.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: ranger cookies
directions: Sift flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt together. Cream butter, sugar and brown sugar in mixer bowl until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla; mix well.
Stir in dry ingredients. Add oats, cereal and chocolate chips, 1 cup at a time, stirring well after each addition.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto nonstick cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: lima bean casserole
directions: Cook beans until done; rinse under hot water and drain. Mix all
ingredients with hot beans in casserole.
Bake 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: 22 minute fudge cake
directions: Bake in 12 x 18-inch pan 20 minutes at 400°.

title: pecan pie cake
directions: Take out and set aside 2/3 cup cake mix.
Mix rest of cake mix with margarine and 1 egg.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Mix the 2/3 cup cake mix with brown sugar, vanilla, Karo and 3 eggs.
Pour over top of first layer and sprinkle pecans on top.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes longer at 350°.

title: angel food candy
directions: Use a heavy pan.
Combine brown sugar and syrup and boil to 290°.
Add baking soda.
Put in well greased 9 x 13-inch pan. When cold, break into pieces and dip pieces in melted chocolate.

title: swiss steak
directions: Cut meat into serving size pieces.
Brown meat (that has been seasoned and rolled in flour) in oil slowly.
Add onion to skillet and brown golden. Add the tomato sauce and 1 cup water with the Worcestershire sauce to the skillet of meat. Cover and simmer 2 hours or until tender.

title: bean 'n beef casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion; add in all other ingredients and stir occasionally.
Place in large casserole dish, uncovered.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Put cheese on top just before removing from oven.

title: skillet cookies
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients and cook slowly for 10 minutes. Set off fire; add Rice Krispies and nuts.
Roll into balls with wet hands and roll in coconut.

title: chicken divan
directions: In oblong baking dish, arrange broccoli and browned chicken pieces.
Combine soup and milk.
Pour over broccoli and chicken. Sprinkle cheese over top.
Combine bread crumbs and melted butter. Sprinkle over cheese.
Bake at 450° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: bacon appetizer crescents
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Beat cream cheese, bacon, Parmesan cheese, onion, parsley and milk in small mixing bowl at medium speed with mixer until well blended.
Separate dough into 8 rectangles; firmly press perforations together to seal.
Spread each rectangle with 2 rounded measuring tablespoonfuls of cream cheese mixture.
Cut each rectangle in half diagonally; repeat with opposite corners.
Cut in half crosswise to form 6 triangles. Roll up triangles, starting at short ends.
Place on greased cookie sheet; brush with combined egg and water.
Sprinkle with poppy seed, if desired.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve immediately.
Makes approximately 4 dozen appetizers.

title: german sweet chocolate cake
directions: Melt package of chocolate in the boiling water.
Cool.
Cream margarine and sugar until fluffy.
Add egg yolks, one at a time. Blend in vanilla and melted chocolate.
Add alternately with buttermilk, cake flour, baking soda and salt.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Bake in 3 greased 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cool.

title: sausage and rice casserole
directions: Brown sausage in pan and pour off grease.
Rinse with hot water.
Add chopped vegetables and simmer until tender.
Mix all ingredients and bake in large casserole dish for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: donna's punch
directions: Chill juice and ginger ale.
Mix in punch bowl and add scoops of sherbet.

title: hamburger noodle bake
directions: In skillet, cook beef and onion until meat is brown and onion is tender.
Drain off fat.
Combine meat with noodles, cheese, soup, 1 cup water, green pepper, chili sauce, pimientos, salt and dash of pepper.
Mix well.
Turn into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Combine crumbs and oleo.
Sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until hot.
Trim with green pepper rings, if desired.

title: oatmeal caramelitas
directions: Melt caramels in milk.
Cool slightly.
Combine all ingredients except chocolate chips and pecans in a large bowl. Press half of crumbs into bottom of an 11 x 7-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with chocolate chips and pecans.
Top with caramel mixture and sprinkle with remaining crumbs.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown. Chill 1 to 2 hours.
Cut into bars.

title: squash croquettes
directions: Mix all ingredients except corn meal together.
Use hands to mix thoroughly.
Form into oblong cocoon shape croquettes and roll in corn meal.
Fry in fat until golden brown.

title: pink kisses
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add all other ingredients. Spread onto well greased cookie sheet.
Bake in 200° oven for 1 1/4 hours.
Cut into small squares.

title: heath pie
directions: Melt Hershey bar.
Add Cool Whip and chips.
Pour into pie crust and chill.
Top with anything, more chocolate chips, Heath chips, grated chocolate, etc.

title: mrs. moragne's chili
directions: In a medium-size saucepan, brown ground beef.
Cut up the onion in the beef as it browns.
Add chili powder, mustard and catsup.
Simmer about 5 minutes.
It's great for hot dogs and chili potatoes.

title: giblet gravy(with gizzards, liver, heart)
directions: Place gizzards, liver and heart in water.
Add onion and simmer until tender, about 1 hour.
Keep adding water to retain 1 quart of liquid.
Mix butter or drippings with flour and brown. Strain stock and add slowly to flour and butter mixture.
Stir until smooth and thick, about 3 to 4 minutes.
Add salt; dice giblets and livers.

title: cheesy cornbread
directions: Combine ingredients, except cheese, in a large bowl.
Stir until combined (do not use mixer).
Pour 1/2 of mixture into a 9-inch greased cake pan.
Sprinkle grated cheese over batter. Pour remaining batter over cheese.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes. Serves 6.

title: sausage
directions: Mix all ingredients with your hands so all seasoning is mixed evenly through the meat.
Make into patties and freeze on cookie sheet until firm.
Wrap individually or with waxed paper between patties.
Keep frozen until ready to use.

title: angel corn bread
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Combine eggs, buttermilk and oil and add to dry ingredients, stirring until batter is smooth.
Spoon the batter into a buttered iron skillet or iron corn stick pan (1/2 full).
Cook at 450° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Combine ingredients and bring to hard boil then pour over carrots, onions and bell pepper.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli by directions on package until tender; drain. Mix with soup, eggs, mayonnaise, onions and water chestnuts.
Add salt and pepper.
Pour in 13 x 9 x 2-inch casserole dish and cover with cheese and butter.
Sprinkle herb stuffing mix on top.
Bake at 400° for approximately 30 minutes.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: marietta's sugar cookies
directions: Cream together first 5 ingredients.
In a separate bowl, mix dry ingredients.
Then slowly mix the ingredients together. Refrigerate for at least 1/2 hour.
Roll into small balls and mash with a damp fork.
You can add different flavors or chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: springtime lime salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water. Cool slightly. Stir in evaporated milk. Chill until as thick as unbeaten egg whites. Fold in pineapple, lemon juice, cheese, nuts, celery and mayonnaise.
Pour into 8-inch square pan or 5-cup mold. Chill until firm. Serves 8 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Cook broccoli, potatoes, onion and bouillon cubes in water for 1 hour.
Add soups and cheese. Simmer for a few minutes. Serve hot.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Brown ground beef.
Stir all ingredients in large pot.
Simmer at least 1 hour.

title: brownies
directions: Beat eggs well. Add sugar and mix well.
Melt Crisco, margarine and chocolate.
Set aside to cool.
Add to egg mixture. Sift flour, baking powder and salt. Add to chocolate mixture. Stir in vanilla and nuts.
Bake in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: moon cake
directions: Mix
water
and
butter or margarine.
Bring to a boil. Add flour, all at once, and stir rapidly until mixture forms a ball. Remove
from heat and cool for a little while.
Beat in 4 eggs, one
at
a time, beating well with a spoon or a mixer. Spread on an
ungreased
cookie
sheet.
Bake
at 400° for 30 minutes. Cool.
Cake
will
look like the moon's surface.
Do not prick. Leave cake as is.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Clean whole strawberries and arrange in baked pie shell.
Cook sugar, water, salt, cornstarch and syrup until thick and fairly clear.
Take from stove and add jello and enough food coloring to give bright red color.
Pour over berries, making sure to cover every berry.
Let set before serving.
Serve with whipped topping.

title: breakfast pudding
directions: Pour melted butter into a 13x9x2-inch baking dish.
Set aside. Combine eggs, milk, flour, and salt in a large bowl.
Beat at medium speed of an electric mixer until well blended.
Pour egg mixture into prepared baking dish.
Arrange sausage slices over egg mixture.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Serve immediately with warm maple syrup.
Yields 6-8 servings.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding with cold milk according to package directions. Chill 5 minutes.
Stir pudding, Eagle Brand milk and Cool Whip together.
Layer bananas, wafers and filling alternately.
Chill.

title: irish potato cake
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Mix alternately with coffee. Add eggs, one at a time, then add raisins, nuts, etc.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Makes three layers.
Use your favorite chocolate frosting.

title: snowballs
directions: Melt chocolate and allow to cool.
Combine crumbs, nuts, dates and cherries in bowl and mix in milk.
Add chocolate and mix well. Form into walnut-sized balls.
Roll in coconut.
Refrigerate.

title: hot shrimp dip
directions: Chop green onions and tops.
Melt butter.
Add onions.
Cook a few minutes, then add cream cheese and shrimp over low heat until combined.
Keep warm in chafing dish or on warming tray.
Serve with vegetables or crackers.

title: chocolate chip sour cream cookies
directions: Sift together:
flour, baking powder, salt and soda.
Cream butter and brown sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla to butter and sugar mixture.
Add sour cream, chopped nuts and chocolate chips.
Add sifted dry ingredients.
Bake at 375° until lightly browned.

title: fried corn
directions: Saute bacon, onion, green pepper and butter over low heat about 10 minutes. Add corn, sugar, paprika and seasoned pepper. Cook about 1 hour over low heat. Add more liquid (water) if needed.

title: bev's chocolate chunk cookies
directions: Chop chocolate into small chunks; set aside.
Cream butter until soft.
Add sugars, eggs and vanilla; beat until light and fluffy.
Blend in flour, soda and salt.
Stir in chocolate pieces and nuts.
Drop from teaspoon onto ungreased baking sheets about 2-inches apart.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Makes 4 to 5 dozen.

title: zucchini bread(the best)
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, oil and vanilla.
Add zucchini.
Add flour mixture.
Stir in pineapple, nuts and raisins.
Bake in 2 loaf pans for 1 hour at 325°.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Place chopped chicken in bottom of greased 2-quart baking dish.
Melt 1 stick margarine and pour over the chicken.
Sprinkle with pepper.
Add 1 can mixed veggies.
Mix together flour, milk, baking powder and salt.
Spread over chicken and veggies.
Heat 1 can of chicken broth with 1 can cream of celery soup (just as it comes from the can).
Pour this over chicken pie last of all. Bake until brown and done (approximately 1 to 1 1/2 hours).

title: orange cake
directions: Beat egg yolks.
Add sugar gradually, then add orange juice, flour and baking powder.
Beat egg whites until stiff; add to mixture.
Bake in tube cake tin at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Beat eggs until light colored.
Blend in sugar and drained mandarin oranges with electric mixer.
Sift flour, salt and soda together.
Add; beat on low speed setting for 4 minutes.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes, or until center tests done.
Pour topping over cake as soon as it comes out of the oven.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and pepper together. Drain. Add soup and enchilada sauce. Salt and pepper to taste. Spread chips on bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan. Add hamburger mixture.
Put cheese on top and bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: ground beef medley
directions: In colander in 3-quart casserole, microwave (High) ground beef, onion and green pepper for 4 to 6 minutes, stirring twice. Pour off drippings.
Blend with macaroni, tomato juice, corn, water, ketchup, chili powder, salt and pepper.
Microwave (High) covered, 8 to 10 minutes, stirring halfway through cooking. Sprinkle top with soup mix.
Microwave (High), covered 6 to 8 minutes.
Rest, covered, 5 to 10 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: christmas wreaths
directions: Melt margarine. Add marshmallows. Stir in until all melted. Add coloring, then cornflakes.
Spoon out 18 piles of mixture onto wax paper. With buttered fingers, shape into wreaths.
Decorate with red hots.
